to para mis compras en línea.","en":"I need to apply for a new credit card for my online purchases."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cambio","english_text":"Change","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the act or result of making something different; a transformation or alteration","main_translations_es":["Modificación","Alteración","Variación"],"collocations":["make a change","change of pace","change your mind","change the subject"],"synonyms_en":["alteration","modification","shift"],"example_sentence":"I need a career change.","example_es":"Necesito un cambio de carrera.","example_en":"I need a career change.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cashier handing over a cambio of coins, instantly creating a fresh change.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito un cambio de carrera.","en":"I need a career change."}]},{"spanish_text":"Recibo","english_text":"Receipt","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written acknowledgment that something has been received, often confirming a payment.","main_translations_es":["Comprobante","Factura","Ticket"],"collocations":["receipt of payment","receipt number","receipt printer","receipt confirmation"],"synonyms_en":["proof of purchase","sales slip","transaction record"],"example_sentence":"The receipt from the purchase is on the table.","example_es":"El recibo de la compra está sobre la mesa.","example_en":"The receipt from the purchase is on the table.","mnemonic_en":"I keep a receipt (recibo) in my wallet as proof.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El recibo de la compra está sobre la mesa.","en":"The receipt from the purchase is on the table."}]},{"spanish_text":"Barato","english_text":"Cheap","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Low in price; inexpensive.","main_translations_es":["Económico","Asequible","Baratillo"],"collocations":["cheap and cheerful","cheap as chips","cheap thrill","cheap shot"],"synonyms_en":["inexpensive","low-cost","budget"],"example_sentence":"This restaurant is very cheap.","example_es":"Este restaurante es muy barato.","example_en":"This restaurant is very cheap.","mnemonic_en":"A cheep bird perched on a cheap sign shouts Barato.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Este restaurante es muy barato.","en":"This restaurant is very cheap."}]},{"spanish_text":"Caro","english_text":"Expensive","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Costing a lot of money; having a high price.","main_translations_es":["Costoso","Elevado","Carísimo"],"collocations":["expensive taste","expensive purchase","expensive item","expensive price"],"synonyms_en":["costly","pricey","high-priced"],"example_sentence":"That car is very expensive.","example_es":"Ese coche es muy caro.","example_en":"That car is very expensive.","mnemonic_en":"A shiny car named Caro costs an expensive price.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Ese coche es muy caro.","en":"That car is very expensive."}]},{"spanish_text":"Oferta","english_text":"Sale","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A transaction in which goods or services are sold, often at a reduced price.","main_translations_es":["Descuento","Promoción","Rebaja"],"collocations":["on sale","sale price","sale event","sale season"],"synonyms_en":["discount","bargain","clearance"],"example_sentence":"Take advantage of the 50% off sale at the store.","example_es":"Aprovecha la oferta de 50% de descuento en la tienda.","example_en":"Take advantage of the 50% off sale at the store.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a SALE banner with a loud Oferta shouted by a street vendor.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Aprovecha la oferta de 50% de descuento en la tienda.","en":"Take advantage of the 50% off sale at the store."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abierto","english_text":"Open","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not closed or blocked, allowing access or passage.","main_translations_es":["Desplegado","Libre","Sin cerrar"],"collocations":["open the door","open a book","open to suggestions"],"synonyms_en":["unlocked","unsealed","available"],"example_sentence":"The restaurant is open.","example_es":"El restaurante está abierto.","example_en":"The restaurant is open.","mnemonic_en":"Open the door and hear a crowd shout abierto as the light spills in","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El restaurante está abierto.","en":"The restaurant is open."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cerrado","english_text":"Closed","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not open; shut.","main_translations_es":["Clausurado","Bloqueado","Sellado"],"collocations":["closed door","closed account","closed caption","closed meeting"],"synonyms_en":["shut","sealed","locked"],"example_sentence":"The restaurant is closed.","example_es":"El restaurante está cerrado.","example_en":"The restaurant is closed.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a closed door stamped with the word cerrado","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El restaurante está cerrado.","en":"The restaurant is closed."}]},{"spanish_text":"Oficina","english_text":"Office","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A room or set of rooms where people work, especially in a business or organization.","main_translations_es":["Despacho","Establecimiento","Local"],"collocations":["office hours","home office","office space","office manager"],"synonyms_en":["workplace","bureau","workroom"],"example_sentence":"I work in an office downtown.","example_es":"Trabajo en una oficina en el centro de la ciudad.","example_en":"I work in an office downtown.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a busy office where every file is stamped with the word oficina.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Trabajo en una oficina en el centro de la ciudad.","en":"I work in an office downtown."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reunión","english_text":"Meeting","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A gathering of people for discussion or decision-making.","main_translations_es":["Junta","Encuentro","Asamblea"],"collocations":["team meeting","board meeting","meeting minutes","meeting agenda"],"synonyms_en":["gathering","assembly","session"],"example_sentence":"The meeting will start at ten o''clock in the morning.","example_es":"La reunión comenzará a las diez de la mañana.","example_en":"The meeting will start at ten o''clock in the morning.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a meat‑ing where everyone reunites around a grill.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La reunión comenzará a las diez de la mañana.","en":"The meeting will start at ten o''clock in the morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Compañero","english_text":"Coworker","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who works together with someone else in the same organization or on the same project.","main_translations_es":["Colega","Compañero de trabajo","Compañero laboral"],"collocations":["my coworker","a coworker of mine","work with a coworker","coworker relationship"],"synonyms_en":["colleague","workmate","associate"],"example_sentence":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","example_es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","example_en":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cow at a desk working with your compañero, the friendly coworker.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","en":"My coworker helped me finish the report."}]},{"spanish_text":"Jefe","english_text":"Boss","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who is in charge of others, especially at work.","main_translations_es":["Jefe","Patrón","Superior"],"collocations":["the boss is coming","call the boss","boss level","boss around"],"synonyms_en":["supervisor","manager","chief"],"example_sentence":"My boss gave me a raise last week.","example_es":"Mi jefe me dio un aumento la semana pasada.","example_en":"My boss gave me a raise last week.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine the jefe wearing a boss crown, shouting BOSS like a real boss.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mi jefe me dio un aumento la semana pasada.","en":"My boss gave me a raise last week."}]},{"spanish_text":"Clase","english_text":"Class","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A group of students who are taught together, or a category of objects or ideas that share common characteristics.","main_translations_es":["Categoría","Tipo","Grupo"],"collocations":["class schedule","first class","classroom","class action"],"synonyms_en":["category","lesson","group"],"example_sentence":"The class is cancelled today.","example_es":"La clase está cancelada hoy.","example_en":"The class is cancelled today.","mnemonic_en":"I picture a teacher ringing a bell for each class, shouting Clase to start the lesson.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La clase está cancelada hoy.","en":"The class is cancelled today."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tarea","english_text":"Homework","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"School assignments given to be completed outside of class.","main_translations_es":["deber","trabajo","encargo"],"collocations":["do homework","homework assignment","homework help","homework deadline"],"synonyms_en":["assignment","schoolwork","task"],"example_sentence":"I have to finish my homework before dinner.","example_es":"Tengo que terminar mi tarea antes de la cena.","example_en":"I have to finish my homework before dinner.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a house (home) with a big ''tarea'' sign on the door—homework.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que terminar mi tarea antes de la cena.","en":"I have to finish my homework before dinner."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estudiar","english_text":"Study","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To devote time and attention to acquiring knowledge or skill in a subject.","main_translations_es":["Aprender","Repasar","Prepararse"],"collocations":["study hard","study abroad","study for the exam","study group"],"synonyms_en":["learn","review","research"],"example_sentence":"I have to study for the exam.","example_es":"Tengo que estudiar para el examen.","example_en":"I have to study for the exam.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a stew bubbling in a pot labeled Estudiar as you study.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que estudiar para el examen.","en":"I have to study for the exam."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aprender","english_text":"Learn","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To acquire knowledge or skill through study, experience, or instruction.","main_translations_es":["Estudiar","Adquirir conocimientos","Instruirse"],"collocations":["learn by heart","learn the ropes","learn quickly","learn from experience"],"synonyms_en":["study","acquire knowledge","master"],"example_sentence":"I want to learn to play the guitar.","example_es":"Quiero aprender a tocar la guitarra.","example_en":"I want to learn to play the guitar.","mnemonic_en":"I press the switch (prender) to learn the lesson.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero aprender a tocar la guitarra.","en":"I want to learn to play the guitar."}]},{"spanish_text":"Descansar","english_text":"Rest","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of relaxation or inactivity intended to recover strength.","main_translations_es":["Reposar","Tomar un descanso","Relajarse"],"collocations":["rest and recover","rest assured","take a rest","rest of the day"],"synonyms_en":["relax","take a break","repose"],"example_sentence":"I need to rest after work.","example_es":"Necesito descansar después del trabajo.","example_en":"I need to rest after work.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a weary traveler sitting on a rest bench called descANSAR for a quick rest","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito descansar después del trabajo.","en":"I need to rest after work."}]},{"spanish_text":"Horario","english_text":"Schedule","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan that lists the times at which events or tasks are intended to occur.","main_translations_es":["Calendario","Programa","Agenda"],"collocations":["keep a schedule","schedule a meeting","on schedule","schedule changes"],"synonyms_en":["timetable","agenda","program"],"example_sentence":"What is the meeting schedule?","example_es":"¿Cuál es el horario de la reunión?","example_en":"What is the meeting schedule?","mnemonic_en":"I picture a school board with the word horario, and the schedule (sked-ule) pinned beside it.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"¿Cuál es el horario de la reunión?","en":"What is the meeting schedule?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Hoy","english_text":"Today","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"The current day; the day that is happening now.","main_translations_es":["En el día de hoy","Esta jornada","En la fecha actual"],"collocations":["today is the day","as of today","today''s agenda","today and tomorrow"],"synonyms_en":["now","this day","the present"],"example_sentence":"Today I am going to the market.","example_es":"Hoy voy al mercado.","example_en":"Today I am going to the market.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a bright toy today, saying ''hoy'' as you hold it.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Hoy voy al mercado.","en":"Today I am going to the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mañana","english_text":"Tomorrow","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"The day after today.","main_translations_es":["El día siguiente","Al día siguiente","En la mañana"],"collocations":["Tomorrow morning","See you tomorrow","Tomorrow night","Tomorrow will be better"],"synonyms_en":["the next day","the following day","day after today"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow we will go to the park.","example_es":"Mañana iremos al parque.","example_en":"Tomorrow we will go to the park.","mnemonic_en":"Tomorrow I picture the sunrise and hear \"mañana\" whispering in my ear.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mañana iremos al parque.","en":"Tomorrow we will go to the park."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ayer","english_text":"Yesterday","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"the day before today","main_translations_es":["el día anterior","el día de ayer","el día previo"],"collocations":["Yesterday morning","Yesterday evening","Yesterday I went","Yesterday was a good day"],"synonyms_en":["the day before","the previous day"],"example_sentence":"Yesterday we went to the cinema and watched an action movie.","example_es":"Ayer fuimos al cine y vimos una película de acción.","example_en":"Yesterday we went to the cinema and watched an action movie.","mnemonic_en":"Yesterday sounds like Spanish ''ayer'', picture the day before today fading away.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Ayer fuimos al cine y vimos una película de acción.","en":"Yesterday we went to the cinema and watched an action movie."}]},{"spanish_text":"Esta semana","english_text":"This week","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"the current week, referring to the seven-day period that includes today","main_translations_es":["Esta semana","La semana actual","La presente semana"],"collocations":["later this week","by this week","this week only","this week''s schedule"],"synonyms_en":["the current week","the present week"],"example_sentence":"This week I go to the gym every day.","example_es":"Esta semana voy al gimnasio todos los días.","example_en":"This week I go to the gym every day.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a calendar saying esta week on the page linking this week to Spanish esta semana","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Esta semana voy al gimnasio todos los días.","en":"This week I go to the gym every day."}]},{"spanish_text":"Fin de semana","english_text":"Weekend","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The period of Saturday and Sunday, or the days at the end of the week, when most people are not working.","main_translations_es":["fin de semana","el fin de semana"],"collocations":["weekend getaway","weekend plans","weekend vibes"],"synonyms_en":["off days","rest days","free time"],"example_sentence":"This weekend I''m going to visit my grandparents.","example_es":"Este fin de semana voy a visitar a mis abuelos.","example_en":"This weekend I''m going to visit my grandparents.","mnemonic_en":"Picture the week ending, a weekend, the fin of the week.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Este fin de semana voy a visitar a mis abuelos.","en":"This weekend I''m going to visit my grandparents."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rápido","english_text":"Fast","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Moving or capable of moving at high speed.","main_translations_es":["Veloz","Ágil","Ligero"],"collocations":["fast food","fast track","fast lane","fast pace"],"synonyms_en":["quick","rapid","swift"],"example_sentence":"The car is fast.","example_es":"El coche es rápido.","example_en":"The car is fast.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a rabbit saying rapido as it darts fast.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El coche es rápido.","en":"The car is fast."}]},{"spanish_text":"Despacio","english_text":"Slowly","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a slow manner; at a low speed.","main_translations_es":["Lentamente","Con calma","A paso lento"],"collocations":["slowly but surely","take it slowly","move slowly"],"synonyms_en":["gradually","at a slow pace","leisurely"],"example_sentence":"Walk slowly so you don''t slip.","example_es":"Camina despacio para no resbalar.","example_en":"Walk slowly so you don''t slip.","mnemonic_en":"A snail whispers despacio as it slides, reminding you everything moves slowly.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Camina despacio para no resbalar.","en":"Walk slowly so you don''t slip."}]},{"spanish_text":"Espera un momento","english_text":"Wait a moment","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite request to pause briefly.","main_translations_es":["Un momento","Espera un segundo","Aguarda un momento"],"collocations":["Wait a moment, please","Hold on a moment","Just wait a moment","Wait a moment while I check"],"synonyms_en":["Hold on","Just a sec","One moment"],"example_sentence":"Wait a moment while I look up the information.","example_es":"Espera un momento, voy a buscar la información.","example_en":"Wait a moment while I look up the information.","mnemonic_en":"I wait hearing the Spanish espera echo in the quiet hallway","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Espera un momento, voy a buscar la información.","en":"Wait a moment while I look up the information."}]},{"spanish_text":"Perdón","english_text":"Excuse me","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"interjection","definition_en":"A polite phrase used to get someone''s attention or to apologize for a minor offense.","main_translations_es":["Disculpa","Lo siento","Con permiso"],"collocations":["Excuse me, could you repeat that?","Excuse me, I have a question","Excuse me, may I sit here?"],"synonyms_en":["Pardon","Sorry","I beg your pardon"],"example_sentence":"Excuse me, can you pass me the salt?","example_es":"Perdón, ¿puedes pasarme la sal?","example_en":"Excuse me, can you pass me the salt?","mnemonic_en":"Excuse me, I''m a robot that says ''per‑done'' when I apologize.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Perdón, ¿puedes pasarme la sal?","en":"Excuse me, can you pass me the salt?"}]},{"spanish_text":"De nada","english_text":"You are welcome","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite response indicating that the speaker is happy to have helped.","main_translations_es":["No hay de qué","Con gusto","A la orden"],"collocations":["You’re welcome!","No problem","Anytime","My pleasure"],"synonyms_en":["No problem","My pleasure","Don''t mention it"],"example_sentence":"You''re welcome, it was a pleasure to help you.","example_es":"De nada, fue un placer ayudarle.","example_en":"You''re welcome, it was a pleasure to help you.","mnemonic_en":"Hear ''De nada'' and picture a door opening, saying ''You are welcome'' to the visitor.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"De nada, fue un placer ayudarle.","en":"You''re welcome, it was a pleasure to help you."}]},{"spanish_text":"Nos vemos luego","english_text":"See you later","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A casual way to say goodbye, indicating that you will meet again later.","main_translations_es":["Hasta luego","Nos vemos después","Hasta pronto"],"collocations":["See you later, alligator","See you later, gator","See you later, buddy"],"synonyms_en":["Catch you later","Talk to you later","Until next time"],"example_sentence":"See you later at the cafe.","example_es":"Nos vemos luego en el café.","example_en":"See you later at the cafe.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a friend waving and shouting nos vemos, then you both smile and think see you later","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Nos vemos luego en el café.","en":"See you later at the cafe."}]},{"spanish_text":"Buenas noches","english_text":"Good night","section_name":"Daily Life","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A polite phrase used to wish someone a pleasant night, typically said when parting in the evening.","main_translations_es":["Buenas noches","Que tengas una buena noche","Que descanses"],"collocations":["Good night, sweet dreams","Good night, see you tomorrow","Good night, everyone","Good night, sleep tight"],"synonyms_en":["sleep well","sweet dreams","nighttime"],"example_sentence":"Good night, see you 