h Basics","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"The day before today.","main_translations_es":["El día anterior","Ayer mismo"],"collocations":["I saw him yesterday","Yesterday was a good day","Yesterday''s news","Yesterday, I went to the park"],"synonyms_en":["the day before","the previous day"],"example_sentence":"Yesterday I went to the market and bought fruit.","example_es":"Ayer fui al mercado y compré frutas.","example_en":"Yesterday I went to the market and bought fruit.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a yawn (ayer) at sunrise, the day before today, that was yesterday.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Ayer fui al mercado y compré frutas.","en":"Yesterday I went to the market and bought fruit."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lunes","english_text":"Monday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Monday is the day of the week after Sunday and before Tuesday.","main_translations_es":["Lunes","el lunes","día lunes"],"collocations":["on Monday","Monday morning","Monday night","Monday blues"],"synonyms_en":["start of the week","first weekday","beginning of the week"],"example_sentence":"On Monday I go to the market.","example_es":"El lunes voy al mercado.","example_en":"On Monday I go to the market.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bright moon on Monday lighting the word lunes on a calendar.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El lunes voy al mercado.","en":"On Monday I go to the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Martes","english_text":"Tuesday","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Tuesday is the second day of the week, following Monday and preceding Wednesday.","main_translations_es":["Martes","el martes","día martes"],"collocations":["on Tuesday","next Tuesday","Tuesday morning","Tuesday night"],"synonyms_en":["Tues.","the second day of the week"],"example_sentence":"Next Tuesday we will go to the movies.","example_es":"El próximo martes iremos al cine.","example_en":"Next Tuesday we will go to the m