ing, extending from the hip to the foot.","main_translations_es":["Pierna","Extremidad inferior","Miembro inferior"],"collocations":["leg of a table","leg day","leg injury","leg room"],"synonyms_en":["limb","lower limb","appendage"],"example_sentence":"My leg hurts after running.","example_es":"Me duele la pierna después de correr.","example_en":"My leg hurts after running.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a leg leaning on a pier, the pier says na to keep it steady.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la pierna después de correr.","en":"My leg hurts after running."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pie","english_text":"Foot","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The lower extremity of the leg on which a person stands and walks.","main_translations_es":["pie","extremidad inferior","parte inferior del cuerpo"],"collocations":["foot of the mountain","foot the bill","foot traffic","foot in the door"],"synonyms_en":["tarsus","pedal","lower extremity"],"example_sentence":"My foot hurts after running.","example_es":"Me duele el pie después de correr.","example_en":"My foot hurts after running.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a foot stepping on a tasty pie, because foot sounds just like the Spanish word pie.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele el pie después de correr.","en":"My foot hurts after running."}]},{"spanish_text":"Espalda","english_text":"Back","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The rear surface of a person or object, opposite the front.","main_translations_es":["dorso","parte posterior","espalda"],"collocations":["back up","back down","back and forth","back to basics"],"synonyms_en":["rear","posterior","hind"],"example_sentence":"My back hurts after running.","example_es":"Me duele la espalda después de correr.","example_en":"My back hurts after running.","mnemonic_en":"I turned my back and felt my espalda ache.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la espalda después de correr.","en":"My back hurts after running."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cara","english_text":"Face","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The front part of a person''s head that includes the eyes, nose, and mouth.","main_translations_es":["rostro","faz","semblante"],"collocations":["face value","face the music","in your face","face-to-face"],"synonyms_en":["countenance","visage","front"],"example_sentence":"She has a very friendly face.","example_es":"Ella tiene una cara muy amable.","example_en":"She has a very friendly face.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bright cara painted on every face you meet.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Ella tiene una cara muy amable.","en":"She has a very friendly face."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pelo","english_text":"Hair","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Hair is the thin strands that grow from the skin of humans and animals, especially on the head.","main_translations_es":["Cabello","Cabellera"],"collocations":["hair cut","hair color","hair style","hair loss"],"synonyms_en":["locks","tresses","mane"],"example_sentence":"I cut my hair yesterday.","example_es":"Me corté el pelo ayer.","example_en":"I cut my hair yesterday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a single hair as a tiny ''pelo'' dancing on a breeze.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me corté el pelo ayer.","en":"I cut my hair yesterday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Oreja","english_text":"Ear","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The organ of hearing located on each side of the head.","main_translations_es":["oreja","oído","lóbulo"],"collocations":["lend an ear","in one ear and out the other","ear to the ground"],"synonyms_en":["auricle","hearing organ","auditory organ"],"example_sentence":"My right ear hurts.","example_es":"Me duele la oreja derecha.","example_en":"My right ear hurts.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an ear shaped like an OREJA, the Spanish word, catching sound waves.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me duele la oreja derecha.","en":"My right ear hurts."}]},{"spanish_text":"Agua","english_text":"Water","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A clear, colorless, odorless, and tasteless liquid that makes up seas, lakes, rivers, and rain, and is essential for most life.","main_translations_es":["agua","el agua","el líquido"],"collocations":["bottled water","running water","water supply","water bottle"],"synonyms_en":["H2O","liquid","aqua"],"example_sentence":"I need to drink water.","example_es":"Necesito beber agua.","example_en":"I need to drink water.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a blue aqua (agua) faucet gushing water.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito beber agua.","en":"I need to drink water."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pan","english_text":"Bread","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A staple food made from flour and water, typically baked.","main_translations_es":["pan","pan de trigo","pan integral"],"collocations":["bread and butter","break bread","earn your bread","breadwinner"],"synonyms_en":["loaf","baked good","grain product"],"example_sentence":"I like to eat fresh bread every morning.","example_es":"Me gusta comer pan recién horneado cada mañana.","example_en":"I like to eat fresh bread every morning.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a pan of dough turning into fresh bread.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta comer pan recién horneado cada mañana.","en":"I like to eat fresh bread every morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Leche","english_text":"Milk","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Milk is the white liquid produced by the mammary glands of mammals, commonly consumed as a beverage and used in cooking.","main_translations_es":["leche","producto lácteo","leche fresca"],"collocations":["a glass of milk","milk the cow","milk chocolate","milkshake"],"synonyms_en":["dairy","cow''s milk","lacteal fluid"],"example_sentence":"I like to drink milk before going to bed.","example_es":"Me gusta tomar leche antes de dormir.","example_en":"I like to drink milk before going to bed.","mnemonic_en":"Milk sounds like mil—imagine a cow saying leche as it gives you fresh milk.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me gusta tomar leche antes de dormir.","en":"I like to drink milk before going to bed."}]},{"spanish_text":"Manzana","english_text":"Apple","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A round fruit with red, green, or yellow skin and a sweet, crisp flesh, typically grown on apple trees.","main_translations_es":["manzana","poma","fruta"],"collocations":["apple pie","apple of my eye","big apple","apple orchard"],"synonyms_en":["fruit","pome","Malus domestica"],"example_sentence":"I bought an apple at the market.","example_es":"Compré una manzana en el mercado.","example_en":"I bought an apple at the market.","mnemonic_en":"A man bites a crisp apple and shouts zana!","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Compré una manzana en el mercado.","en":"I bought an apple at the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Perro","english_text":"Dog","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A domesticated carnivorous mammal commonly kept as a pet or used for work, known for its loyalty and barking.","main_translations_es":["can","chucho","cachorro"],"collocations":["dog house","dog days","dog bark","dog tag"],"synonyms_en":["canine","pooch","hound"],"example_sentence":"The dog runs in the park.","example_es":"El perro corre en el parque.","example_en":"The dog runs in the park.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dog wearing a pair of O-shaped medals around its neck.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El perro corre en el parque.","en":"The dog runs in the park."}]},{"spanish_text":"Gato","english_text":"Cat","section_name":"English Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A small domesticated carni