tion_en":"A piece of furniture with a flat top and legs, used for working, eating, or placing items.","main_translations_es":["mesa","mesa de comedor","mesa de escritorio"],"collocations":["dinner table","table of contents","round table","table tennis"],"synonyms_en":["desk","chart","list"],"example_sentence":"I placed the book on the table.","example_es":"Puse el libro sobre la mesa.","example_en":"I placed the book on the table.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a wooden table shaped like a flat mesa in the desert, supporting plates.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Puse el libro sobre la mesa.","en":"I placed the book on the table."}]},{"spanish_text":"Silla","english_text":"Chair","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A piece of furniture with a seat, back, and legs, used for sitting.","main_translations_es":["butaca","asiento","sillón"],"collocations":["chair the meeting","chair of the board","rocking chair","chairperson"],"synonyms_en":["seat","stool","armchair"],"example_sentence":"The chair is next to the table.","example_es":"La silla está junto a la mesa.","example_en":"The chair is next to the table.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a chair with a seal (cilla) perched, cheering you to sit.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La silla está junto a la mesa.","en":"The chair is next to the table."}]},{"spanish_text":"Menú","english_text":"Menu","section_name":"Cafe Counter Basics","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A list of dishes offered by a restaurant or a set of selectable options in a software program.","main_translations_es":["Carta","Lista de platos","Selección"],"collocations":["menu options","menu board","menu item","menu planning"],"synonyms_en":["list of dishes","food list","bill of fare"],"example_sentence":"Can you pass me the menu, please?","example_es":"¿Puedes pasarme el menú, por favor?","example_en":"Can you pass me the menu, please?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a menu where the word men serve y