e plan as a feast in a viable garden, showing it can be done.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto es viable si conseguimos más financiación.","en":"The project is feasible if we secure more funding."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sostenible","english_text":"Sustainable","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Capable of being maintained over the long term without depleting resources or causing harm.","main_translations_es":["Sustentable","Duradero","Ecoamigable"],"collocations":["sustainable development","sustainable growth","sustainable energy","sustainable practices"],"synonyms_en":["viable","eco‑friendly","renewable"],"example_sentence":"This company has implemented sustainable practices to reduce its carbon footprint.","example_es":"Esta empresa ha implementado prácticas sostenibles para reducir su huella de carbono.","example_en":"This company has implemented sustainable practices to reduce its carbon footprint.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a sturdy table that can sustain, its label reads SOSTENIBLE, showing it''s sustainable.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Esta empresa ha implementado prácticas sostenibles para reducir su huella de carbono.","en":"This company has implemented sustainable practices to reduce its carbon footprint."}]},{"spanish_text":"Controvertido","english_text":"Controversial","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Describing something that provokes public disagreement or debate.","main_translations_es":["Polémico","Discutido","Contencioso"],"collocations":["controversial issue","controversial figure","controversial topic","controversial decision"],"synonyms_en":["disputed","contentious","debated"],"example_sentence":"The issue of euthanasia remains controversial in many countries.","example_es":"El tema de la eutanasia sigue siendo controvertido en muchos países.","example_en":"The issue of euthanasia remains controversial in many countries.","mnemonic_en":"A heated debate turns the article into a contra verse, making it controversial.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El tema de la eutanasia sigue siendo controvertido en muchos países.","en":"The issue of euthanasia remains controversial in many countries."}]},{"spanish_text":"Generalizado","english_text":"Widespread","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Existing or occurring over a large area or among many people.","main_translations_es":["Extenso","General","Difuso"],"collocations":["widespread use","widespread adoption","widespread problem","widespread belief"],"synonyms_en":["extensive","prevalent","common"],"example_sentence":"The use of mobile phones has become very widespread throughout the country.","example_es":"El uso de los teléfonos móviles se ha vuelto muy generalizado en todo el país.","example_en":"The use of mobile phones has become very widespread throughout the country.","mnemonic_en":"A wide spread of general news blankets the town, like a generalizado blanket.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El uso de los teléfonos móviles se ha vuelto muy generalizado en todo el país.","en":"The use of mobile phones has become very widespread throughout the country."}]},{"spanish_text":"Predominante","english_text":"Predominant","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Being the most common, strongest, or most important element in a group or situation.","main_translations_es":["principal","dominante","preponderante"],"collocations":["predominant theme","predominant factor","predominant position","predominant in"],"synonyms_en":["dominant","prevalent","principal"],"example_sentence":"The color blue is predominant in the room''s decor.","example_es":"El color azul es predominante en la decoración de la habitación.","example_en":"The color blue is predominant in the room''s decor.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a PRE-DOMINANT lion, the king before any other, just like a predominante leader.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El color azul es predominante en la decoración de la habitación.","en":"The color blue is predominant in the room''s decor."}]},{"spanish_text":"Subyacente","english_text":"Underlying","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Existing beneath the surface or forming the basis of something.","main_translations_es":["subyacente","latente","de base"],"collocations":["underlying cause","underlying principle","underlying assumption","underlying issue"],"synonyms_en":["fundamental","basic","foundational"],"example_sentence":"The underlying problem is the lack of communication.","example_es":"El problema subyacente es la falta de comunicación.","example_en":"The underlying problem is the lack of communication.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a submarine (sub) hidden under the waves, the underlying secret.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El problema subyacente es la falta de comunicación.","en":"The underlying problem is the lack of communication."}]},{"spanish_text":"Trascender","english_text":"Transcend","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To go beyond or rise above something, especially limits, expectations, or ordinary experience.","main_translations_es":["sobrepasar","ir más allá","superar"],"collocations":["transcend boundaries","transcend the ordinary","transcend time","transcend expectations"],"synonyms_en":["go beyond","exceed","surpass"],"example_sentence":"Van Gogh''s art manages to transcend time and continues to inspire new generations.","example_es":"El arte de Van Gogh logra trascender el tiempo y sigue inspirando a nuevas generaciones.","example_en":"Van Gogh''s art manages to transcend time and continues to inspire new generations.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a ladder that trascends the clouds, letting you rise beyond all limits.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El arte de Van Gogh logra trascender el tiempo y sigue inspirando a nuevas generaciones.","en":"Van Gogh''s art manages to transcend time and continues to inspire new generations."}]},{"spanish_text":"Perjudicar","english_text":"Undermine","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To weaken or damage something gradually or subtly.","main_translations_es":["dañar","desmejorar","afectar negativamente"],"collocations":["undermine confidence","undermine authority","undermine credibility","undermine efforts"],"synonyms_en":["weaken","sabotage","subvert"],"example_sentence":"Constant criticism can undermine the team''s confidence.","example_es":"Las críticas constantes pueden perjudicar la confianza del equipo.","example_en":"Constant criticism can undermine the team''s confidence.","mnemonic_en":"A miner digs under the bridge, causing it to collapse and perjudicar the village.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Las críticas constantes pueden perjudicar la confianza del equipo.","en":"Constant criticism can undermine the team''s confidence."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir","english_text":"Comply with","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to act in accordance with a rule, request, or demand","main_translations_es":["Obedecer","Acatar","Cumplir con"],"collocations":["comply with regulations","comply with the law","comply with standards","comply with requirements"],"synonyms_en":["obey","conform to","adhere to"],"example_sentence":"It is important to comply with the safety regulations.","example_es":"Es importante cumplir con las normas de seguridad.","example_en":"It is important to comply with the safety regulations.","mnemonic_en":"See a cumulative pile of rules you must comply with.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante cumplir con las normas de seguridad.","en":"It is important to comply with the safety regulations."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ajustarse a","english_text":"Adhere to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to follow or comply with a rule, guideline, or request","main_translations_es":["adaptarse a","cumplir con","acatar"],"collocations":["adhere to guidelines","adhere to the policy","adhere to standards","adhere to a schedule"],"synonyms_en":["follow","stick to","comply with"],"example_sentence":"It is important to adhere to the company''s rules.","example_es":"Es importante ajustarse a las normas de la empresa.","example_en":"It is important to adhere to the company''s rules.","mnemonic_en":"A deer adjusts to the fence, just like you adhere to rules.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante ajustarse a las normas de la empresa.","en":"It is important to adhere to the company''s rules."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dar lugar a","english_text":"Give rise to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to cause something to happen or exist","main_translations_es":["Provocar","Causar","Originar"],"collocations":["give rise to problems","give rise to controversy","give rise to questions","give rise to a new trend"],"synonyms_en":["cause","lead to","bring about"],"example_sentence":"The new policy can give rise to massive protests.","example_es":"La nueva política puede dar lugar a protestas masivas.","example_en":"The new policy can give rise to massive protests.","mnemonic_en":"A river gives rise to a new path, just like \"dar\" creates space for something to happen.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La nueva política puede dar lugar a protestas masivas.","en":"The new policy can give rise to massive protests."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tener en cuenta","english_text":"Take into account","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To consider or regard something when making a decision.","main_translations_es":["Considerar","Tomar en consideración","Tener presente"],"collocations":["take into account the fact that","take into account the costs","take into account the risks"],"synonyms_en":["consider","keep in mind","factor in"],"example_sentence":"You should take into account the weather before going out.","example_es":"Debes tener en cuenta el clima antes de salir.","example_en":"You should take into account the weather before going out.","mnemonic_en":"Take a taco, then count the beans—cuenta reminds you to take into account.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Debes tener en cuenta el clima antes de salir.","en":"You should take into account the weather before going out."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a la conclusión","english_text":"Reach the conclusion","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to arrive at a final decision or judgment after considering the evidence","main_translations_es":["Llegar a una conclusión","Concluir","Llegar a la conclusión"],"collocations":["reach the conclusion that","reach the conclusion after","reach the conclusion based on","reach the conclusion that it is"],"synonyms_en":["draw a conclusion","come to a conclusion","conclude"],"example_sentence":"After reviewing all the data, we reached the conclusion that the project is viable.","example_es":"Después de revisar todos los datos, llegamos a la conclusión de que el proyecto es viable.","example_en":"After reviewing all the data, we reached the conclusion that the project is viable.","mnemonic_en":"I reach out and grab the final ''conclusión'' banner at the race finish.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Después de revisar todos los datos, llegamos a la conclusión de que el proyecto es viable.","en":"After reviewing all the data, we reached the conclusion that the project is viable."}]},{"spanish_text":"En gran medida","english_text":"To a large extent","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"It means that something is true or applies to a great degree.","main_translations_es":["En gran medida","En gran parte","Considerablemente"],"collocations":["It is true to a large extent","The impact is felt to a large extent","Results vary to a large extent"],"synonyms_en":["greatly","significantly","substantially"],"example_sentence":"The success of the project depends, to a large extent, on the team''s collaboration.","example_es":"El éxito del proyecto depende, en gran medida, de la colaboración del equipo.","example_en":"The success of the project depends, to a large extent, on the team''s collaboration.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a huge tent covering a big measure of land","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El éxito del proyecto depende, en gran medida, de la colaboración del equipo.","en":"The success of the project depends, to a large extent, on the team''s collaboration."}]},{"spanish_text":"A corto plazo","english_text":"In the short term","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"During a brief period of time, referring to the near future.","main_translations_es":["En el corto plazo","A corto plazo","En el futuro cercano"],"collocations":["In the short term, we expect...","In the short term, the company will...","In the short term, this will improve"],"synonyms_en":["short‑term","temporarily","in the near term"],"example_sentence":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%.","example_es":"A corto plazo, la empresa planea aumentar sus ventas en un 10%.","example_en":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a short \"corto\" rope that snaps quickly, just like the short term.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"A corto plazo, la empresa planea aumentar sus ventas en un 10%.","en":"In the short term, the company plans to increase its sales by 10%."}]},{"spanish_text":"A largo plazo","english_text":"In the long run","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"refers to what will happen over a long period of time","main_translations_es":["A largo plazo","A futuro","En el futuro"],"collocations":["In the long run, it will pay off","In the long run, the benefits outweigh the costs","In the long run, we see improvement"],"synonyms_en":["eventually","over time","ultimately"],"example_sentence":"In the long run, investment in education will reduce inequality.","example_es":"A largo plazo, la inversión en educación reducirá la desigualdad.","example_en":"In the long run, investment in education will reduce inequality.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a long (largo) race that stretches far into the future.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"A largo plazo, la inversión en educación reducirá la desigualdad.","en":"In the long run, investment in education will reduce inequality."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desde mi punto de vista","english_text":"From my perspective","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something is being considered from one''s own point of view.","main_translations_es":["Según mi punto de vista","A mi parecer","En mi opinión"],"collocations":["From my perspective, ...","From my perspective it seems that ...","From my perspective we can see ..."],"synonyms_en":["In my view","As I see it","My perspective"],"example_sentence":"From my perspective, education should be free.","example_es":"Desde mi punto de vista, la educación debería ser gratuita.","example_en":"From my perspective, education should be free.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a point (punto) on a map, and you view it from your own perspective.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Desde mi punto de vista, la educación debería ser gratuita.","en":"From my perspective, education should be free."}]},{"spanish_text":"En última instancia","english_text":"Ultimately","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the end, after everything else has been considered.","main_translations_es":["Al fin de cuentas","En definitiva","Al final"],"collocations":["ultimately decided","ultimately leads to","ultimately result","ultimately important"],"synonyms_en":["in the end","finally","eventually"],"example_sentence":"Ultimately, the decision depends on you.","example_es":"En última instancia, la decisión depende de ti.","example_en":"Ultimately, the decision depends on you.","mnemonic_en":"Picture the final ''última'' page flipping, revealing the ultimate outcome.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En última instancia, la decisión depende de ti.","en":"Ultimately, the decision depends on you."}]},{"spanish_text":"En lo que respecta a","english_text":"As far as ... is concerned","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that something is being considered or discussed in relation to a particular subject.","main_translations_es":["En cuanto a","Con respecto a","En lo que se refiere a"],"collocations":["as far as I''m concerned","as far as you''re concerned","as far as the matter is concerned","as far as the law is concerned"],"synonyms_en":["regarding","with respect to","as for"],"example_sentence":"As far as safety is concerned, the company has implemented new measures.","example_es":"En lo que respecta a la seguridad, la empresa ha implementado nuevas medidas.","example_en":"As far as safety is concerned, the company has implemented new measures.","mnemonic_en":"See a faraway A (as) looking concerned at a sign reading en lo que respecta a.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En lo que respecta a la seguridad, la empresa ha implementado nuevas medidas.","en":"As far as safety is concerned, the company has implemented new measures."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cabe destacar","english_text":"It is worth noting","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something should be emphasized or remembered.","main_translations_es":["Hay que destacar","Vale la pena señalar","Es importante señalar"],"collocations":["It is worth noting that...","It is worth noting the following...","It is worth noting the fact that..."],"synonyms_en":["It should be noted","Note that","It is notable"],"example_sentence":"It is worth noting that the research revealed new findings about the climate.","example_es":"Cabe destacar que la investigación reveló nuevos hallazgos sobre el clima.","example_en":"It is worth noting that the research revealed new findings about the climate.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cape (cabe) that highlights a worth‑noting treasure.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Cabe destacar que la investigación reveló nuevos hallazgos sobre el clima.","en":"It is worth noting that the research revealed new findings about the climate."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vale la pena señalar","english_text":"It is worth pointing out","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"idiomatic expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something should be highlighted or mentioned.","main_translations_es":["Cabe destacar","Hay que señalar","Vale la pena mencionar"],"collocations":["It is worth pointing out that...","It is worth pointing out the fact that...","It is worth pointing out the importance of..."],"synonyms_en":["It''s notable","It''s worth mentioning","One should note"],"example_sentence":"It is worth pointing out that the report contains several errors.","example_es":"Vale la pena señalar que el informe contiene varios errores.","example_en":"It is worth pointing out that the report contains several errors.","mnemonic_en":"A valuable pen points out the secret.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Vale la pena señalar que el informe contiene varios errores.","en":"It is worth pointing out that the report contains several errors."}]},{"spanish_text":"No cabe duda de que","english_text":"There is no doubt that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something is certain and unquestionable.","main_translations_es":["Sin duda","No hay duda de que","Indudablemente"],"collocations":["There is no doubt that…","There is no doubt about it.","No doubt that…"],"synonyms_en":["Undoubtedly","Without a doubt","No question that"],"example_sentence":"There is no doubt that the new policy will improve the country''s economy.","example_es":"No cabe duda de que la nueva política mejorará la economía del país.","example_en":"There is no doubt that the new policy will improve the country''s economy.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cabbage (cabe) with the doubt question mark crossed out—no doubt.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No cabe duda de que la nueva política mejorará la economía del país.","en":"There is no doubt that the new policy will improve the country''s economy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resulta evidente que","english_text":"It is evident that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to state that something is clearly apparent or obvious.","main_translations_es":["Es evidente que","Resulta claro que","Se ve que"],"collocations":["It is evident that...","It is evident that the data shows...","It is evident that there is a problem","It is evident that this is the case"],"synonyms_en":["clearly","obviously","it is clear that"],"example_sentence":"It is evident that air pollution is worsening public health.","example_es":"Resulta evidente que la contaminación del aire está empeorando la salud pública.","example_en":"It is evident that air pollution is worsening public health.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a neon sign flashing EVIDENT above a Spanish street, shouting evidente for everyone to see.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Resulta evidente que la contaminación del aire está empeorando la salud pública.","en":"It is evident that air pollution is worsening public health."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sin perjuicio de","english_text":"Without prejudice to","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase indicating that something does not affect or limit another matter.","main_translations_es":["sin que ello implique","sin afectar","sin menoscabar"],"collocations":["without prejudice to the rights of","without prejudice to any claim","without prejudice to the above","without prejudice to further action"],"synonyms_en":["subject to","notwithstanding","without affecting"],"example_sentence":"Without prejudice to what has been agreed, the company may change the working hours.","example_es":"Sin perjuicio de lo acordado, la empresa podrá modificar los horarios.","example_en":"Without prejudice to what has been agreed, the company may change the working hours.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sinless judge clearing the record: without prejudice.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Sin perjuicio de lo acordado, la empresa podrá modificar los horarios.","en":"Without prejudice to what has been agreed, the company may change the working hours."}]},{"spanish_text":"En aras de","english_text":"For the sake of","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to indicate that something is done in order to achieve or benefit something else.","main_translations_es":["con el fin de","a fin de","por el bien de"],"collocations":["for the sake of argument","for the sake of clarity","for the sake of completeness"],"synonyms_en":["in order to","for the benefit of","for the purpose of"],"example_sentence":"For the sake of safety, they closed the road during the storm.","example_es":"En aras de la seguridad, cerraron la carretera durante la tormenta.","example_en":"For the sake of safety, they closed the road during the storm.","mnemonic_en":"Run a race for the sake of victory.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En aras de la seguridad, cerraron la carretera durante la tormenta.","en":"For the sake of safety, they closed the road during the storm."}]},{"spanish_text":"De ahí que","english_text":"Hence","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"As a result; for that reason.","main_translations_es":["Por eso","Así que","De esa forma"],"collocations":["henceforth","hence the","hence we can","hence the result"],"synonyms_en":["Therefore","Thus","Consequently"],"example_sentence":"It was raining heavily, hence they cancelled the match.","example_es":"Estaba lloviendo mucho, de ahí que cancelaron el partido.","example_en":"It was raining heavily, hence they cancelled the match.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hen seeing a clue, so from that (hence) you know the answer.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Estaba lloviendo mucho, de ahí que cancelaron el partido.","en":"It was raining heavily, hence they cancelled the match."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dado que","english_text":"Given that","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"Considering that; used to introduce a reason or condition.","main_translations_es":["Considerando que","Puesto que","Ya que"],"collocations":["Given that you are here","Given that it''s raining","Given that we have no choice","Given that the data is correct"],"synonyms_en":["considering that","since","as"],"example_sentence":"Given that it is raining, we will cancel the picnic.","example_es":"Dado que está lloviendo, cancelaremos el picnic.","example_en":"Given that it is raining, we will cancel the picnic.","mnemonic_en":"Picture giving a dice called dado to someone, so you’re given that.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Dado que está lloviendo, cancelaremos el picnic.","en":"Given that it is raining, we will cancel the picnic."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aunque","english_text":"Albeit","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"It means ''although'' or ''even though''.","main_translations_es":["aunque","aun cuando","si bien"],"collocations":["albeit briefly","albeit unlikely","albeit not","albeit with reservations"],"synonyms_en":["although","even though","though"],"example_sentence":"Albeit he was tired, he kept working late.","example_es":"Aunque estaba cansado, siguió trabajando hasta tarde.","example_en":"Albeit he was tired, he kept working late.","mnemonic_en":"Albeit sounds like Spanish aunque, picture a tiny al bridge letting a though pass.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Aunque estaba cansado, siguió trabajando hasta tarde.","en":"Albeit he was tired, he kept working late."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mientras que","english_text":"Whereas","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"conjunction","definition_en":"Used to introduce a contrast or comparison between two statements.","main_translations_es":["En cambio","A diferencia de","Mientras"],"collocations":["as opposed to","in contrast to","whereas the former","whereas the latter"],"synonyms_en":["while","although"],"example_sentence":"I prefer tea, whereas my brother prefers coffee.","example_es":"Yo prefiero el té, mientras que mi hermano prefiere el café.","example_en":"I prefer tea, whereas my brother prefers coffee.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sign saying WHERE next to a WHILE (mientras) sign, showing contrast – that''s WHEREAS.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Yo prefiero el té, mientras que mi hermano prefiere el café.","en":"I prefer tea, whereas my brother prefers coffee."}]},{"spanish_text":"En cambio","english_text":"By contrast","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverbial phrase","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that is different from or opposite to what has just been mentioned.","main_translations_es":["Por el contrario","En contraste","A diferencia"],"collocations":["by contrast, ...","by contrast with","by contrast to"],"synonyms_en":["in comparison","on the other hand","conversely"],"example_sentence":"I prefer tea; by contrast, my brother always chooses coffee.","example_es":"Yo prefiero el té; en cambio, mi hermano siempre elige café.","example_en":"I prefer tea; by contrast, my brother always chooses coffee.","mnemonic_en":"By contrast the picture flips like a cambio in a comic","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Yo prefiero el té; en cambio, mi hermano siempre elige café.","en":"I prefer tea; by contrast, my brother always chooses coffee."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asimismo","english_text":"Likewise","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the same way or manner; similarly.","main_translations_es":["Igualmente","De igual manera","Del mismo modo"],"collocations":["Likewise, thank you","Likewise, I agree","Likewise, we will proceed","Likewise, the same applies"],"synonyms_en":["Similarly","In the same way","Also"],"example_sentence":"Likewise, we must consider the costs before making a decision.","example_es":"Asimismo, debemos considerar los costos antes de tomar una decisión.","example_en":"Likewise, we must consider the costs before making a decision.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a twin saying likewise, holding a banner that reads asimismo.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Asimismo, debemos considerar los costos antes de tomar una decisión.","en":"Likewise, we must consider the costs before making a decision."}]},{"spanish_text":"Por consiguiente","english_text":"Consequently","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a way that indicates a result or effect; therefore.","main_translations_es":["En consecuencia","Por lo tanto","Así que"],"collocations":["Consequently, the results were significant","Consequently, we decided to proceed","Consequently, the project was delayed"],"synonyms_en":["as a result","therefore","hence"],"example_sentence":"Consequently, the project was delayed by a week.","example_es":"Por consiguiente, el proyecto se retrasó una semana.","example_en":"Consequently, the project was delayed by a week.","mnemonic_en":"The word CONSEQUENTLY starts with cons-, reminding me of por consiguiente.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Por consiguiente, el proyecto se retrasó una semana.","en":"Consequently, the project was delayed by a week."}]},{"spanish_text":"No obstante","english_text":"Nevertheless","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"in spite of that; however","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","Aun así","Con todo"],"collocations":["Nevertheless, ...","Nevertheless, we must","Nevertheless, it is","Nevertheless, she continued"],"synonyms_en":["however","still","nonetheless"],"example_sentence":"Nevertheless, he decided to continue with the project.","example_es":"No obstante, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","example_en":"Nevertheless, he decided to continue with the project.","mnemonic_en":"Picture no obst(acle) ahead, so you say nevertheless and keep moving forward.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No obstante, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","en":"Nevertheless, he decided to continue with the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aun así","english_text":"Even so","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that contrasts with or qualifies what has just been said.","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","No obstante","Aun así"],"collocations":["Even so, ...","Even so, he continued","Even so, the outcome changed","Even so, they agreed"],"synonyms_en":["Nevertheless","Nonetheless","Still"],"example_sentence":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain.","example_es":"Aun así, decidió ir al concierto a pesar de la lluvia.","example_en":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize an even number holding a so sign, echoing aun así.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Aun así, decidió ir al concierto a pesar de la lluvia.","en":"Even so, he decided to go to the concert despite the rain."}]},{"spanish_text":"Poner de relieve","english_text":"Highlight","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To emphasize or make something stand out.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Destacar","Subrayar"],"collocations":["highlight the main points","highlight a problem","highlight in yellow","highlight the differences"],"synonyms_en":["Emphasize","Feature","Underline"],"example_sentence":"The report highlights the importance of early education.","example_es":"El informe pone de relieve la importancia de la educación temprana.","example_en":"The report highlights the importance of early education.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a high lighthouse lighting a relief map, bringing the details into view.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El informe pone de relieve la importancia de la educación temprana.","en":"The report highlights the importance of early education."}]},{"spanish_text":"Poner en tela de juicio","english_text":"Call into question","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to express doubt about the truth or validity of something.","main_translations_es":["Cuestionar","Poner en duda","Poner en entredicho"],"collocations":["call into question the validity","call into question the results","call into question his motives","call into question the decision"],"synonyms_en":["question","doubt","challenge"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to call into question the validity of the report.","example_es":"El comité decidió poner en tela de juicio la validez del informe.","example_en":"The committee decided to call into question the validity of the report.","mnemonic_en":"I call the judge, asking if his fabric is questionable.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió poner en tela de juicio la validez del informe.","en":"The committee decided to call into question the validity of the report."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sacar provecho de","english_text":"Capitalize on","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to take advantage of something for one''s benefit","main_translations_es":["Aprovechar","Explotar","Beneficiarse de"],"collocations":["capitalize on opportunities","capitalize on trends","capitalize on the situation","capitalize on his strengths"],"synonyms_en":["take advantage of","exploit","leverage"],"example_sentence":"The company knew how to capitalize on the new regulations to cut its costs.","example_es":"La empresa supo sacar provecho de la nueva normativa para reducir sus costos.","example_en":"The company knew how to capitalize on the new regulations to cut its costs.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cap pulling out (sacar) cash from a piggy bank, showing you capitalize on profit.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La empresa supo sacar provecho de la nueva normativa para reducir sus costos.","en":"The company knew how to capitalize on the new regulations to cut its costs."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hacer frente a","english_text":"Cope with","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to deal effectively with something difficult or challenging","main_translations_es":["Enfrentar","Lidiar con","Hacer frente a"],"collocations":["cope with stress","cope with loss","cope with change","cope with difficulties"],"synonyms_en":["manage","deal with","handle"],"example_sentence":"It''s hard to cope with the loss of a loved one.","example_es":"Es difícil hacer frente a la pérdida de un ser querido.","example_en":"It''s hard to cope with the loss of a loved one.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a cup (copa) placed right in front (frente) of you to help you cope.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es difícil hacer frente a la pérdida de un ser querido.","en":"It''s hard to cope with the loss of a loved one."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asumir la responsabilidad","english_text":"Take responsibility","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To accept or assume accountability for something.","main_translations_es":["Asumir la responsabilidad","Hacerse cargo","Responsabilizarse"],"collocations":["take responsibility for","take responsibility seriously","take responsibility of","take responsibility and act"],"synonyms_en":["accept accountability","assume the blame","own up"],"example_sentence":"It is important to take responsibility for your actions.","example_es":"Es importante asumir la responsabilidad de tus actos.","example_en":"It is important to take responsibility for your actions.","mnemonic_en":"Take a taco and carry the huge RESPONSIBILITY banner, just like asumir la responsabilidad.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante asumir la responsabilidad de tus actos.","en":"It is important to take responsibility for your actions."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a un acuerdo","english_text":"Reach an agreement","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To come to a mutual understanding or settlement.","main_translations_es":["Acuerdan","Llegar a un pacto","Cerrar un trato"],"collocations":["reach an agreement on","reach an agreement with","reach a final agreement","reach an agreement quickly"],"synonyms_en":["settle","come to terms","strike a deal"],"example_sentence":"After lengthy negotiations, we finally managed to reach an agreement.","example_es":"Después de largas negociaciones, finalmente logramos llegar a un acuerdo.","example_en":"After lengthy negotiations, we finally managed to reach an agreement.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hand reaching to seal an accord, a firm handshake of agreement.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Después de largas negociaciones, finalmente logramos llegar a un acuerdo.","en":"After lengthy negotiations, we finally managed to reach an agreement."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tomar medidas","english_text":"Take action","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To do something in order to achieve a result.","main_translations_es":["Actuar","Emprender acciones","Hacer algo"],"collocations":["take action now","take action against","take decisive action","take action to"],"synonyms_en":["act","intervene","make a move"],"example_sentence":"It''s time to take action to reduce pollution.","example_es":"Es hora de tomar medidas para reducir la contaminación.","example_en":"It''s time to take action to reduce pollution.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a tomato measuring with a ruler, then taking action.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es hora de tomar medidas para reducir la contaminación.","en":"It''s time to take action to reduce pollution."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dar prioridad a","english_text":"Prioritize","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give priority to something, treating it as more important than other things.","main_translations_es":["Priorizar","Dar preferencia a","Poner en primer lugar"],"collocations":["prioritize tasks","prioritize safety","prioritize customer needs","prioritize the budget"],"synonyms_en":["give precedence to","rank","favor"],"example_sentence":"We must prioritize education in our budget.","example_es":"Debemos dar prioridad a la educación en nuestro presupuesto.","example_en":"We must prioritize education in our budget.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a PRIORITY stamp on a prize, showing you give it first place.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Debemos dar prioridad a la educación en nuestro presupuesto.","en":"We must prioritize education in our budget."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pasar por alto","english_text":"Overlook","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To fail to notice or consider something.","main_translations_es":["Ignorar","Desatender","Omitir"],"collocations":["overlook the details","overlook a mistake","overlook the fact"],"synonyms_en":["ignore","miss","disregard"],"example_sentence":"You shouldn''t overlook the important details of the contract.","example_es":"No deberías pasar por alto los detalles importantes del contrato.","example_en":"You shouldn''t overlook the important details of the contract.","mnemonic_en":"I stand on a high overlook and watch a passing pasar train go by.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No deberías pasar por alto los detalles importantes del contrato.","en":"You shouldn''t overlook the important details of the contract."}]},{"spanish_text":"Contrarrestar","english_text":"Counteract","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To act against something in order to reduce or neutralize its effect.","main_translations_es":["neutralizar","compensar","mitigar"],"collocations":["counteract the effects","counteract the damage","counteract the influence"],"synonyms_en":["neutralize","offset","counterbalance"],"example_sentence":"The new drug helps to counteract the side effects of the treatment.","example_es":"El nuevo medicamento ayuda a contrarrestar los efectos secundarios del tratamiento.","example_en":"The new drug helps to counteract the side effects of the treatment.","mnemonic_en":"A counter acts against a spill, so it counteracts the mess.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El nuevo medicamento ayuda a contrarrestar los efectos secundarios del tratamiento.","en":"The new drug helps to counteract the side effects of the treatment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reforzar","english_text":"Reinforce","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To strengthen or support something, often by adding material or effort.","main_translations_es":["Fortalecer","Consolidar","Robustecer"],"collocations":["reinforce the argument","reinforce the structure","reinforce security measures","reinforce the message"],"synonyms_en":["strengthen","bolster","support"],"example_sentence":"The coach decided to reinforce the team''s defense before the next match.","example_es":"El entrenador decidió reforzar la defensa del equipo antes del próximo partido.","example_en":"The coach decided to reinforce the team''s defense before the next match.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a REINFORCEing robot REINFORCING a wall, like a Spanish REFORZAR.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El entrenador decidió reforzar la defensa del equipo antes del próximo partido.","en":"The coach decided to reinforce the team''s defense before the next match."}]},{"spanish_text":"Debilitar","english_text":"Weaken","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To make something less strong, less effective, or less able to resist.","main_translations_es":["Atenuar","Mermar","Desgastar"],"collocations":["weaken the economy","weaken the argument","weaken the resolve"],"synonyms_en":["debilitate","diminish","undermine"],"example_sentence":"The intense cold began to weaken the garden''s plants.","example_es":"El frío intenso comenzó a debilitar las plantas del jardín.","example_en":"The intense cold began to weaken the garden''s plants.","mnemonic_en":"A weak rope debil snaps, making the bridge weaken","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El frío intenso comenzó a debilitar las plantas del jardín.","en":"The intense cold began to weaken the garden''s plants."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desencadenar","english_text":"Trigger","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to cause something to happen or to start a process.","main_translations_es":["Provocar","Desatar","Iniciar"],"collocations":["trigger a reaction","trigger an alarm","trigger a response","trigger the event"],"synonyms_en":["activate","initiate","set off"],"example_sentence":"The discovery of the new particle could trigger a revolution in physics.","example_es":"El descubrimiento de la nueva partícula podría desencadenar una revolución en la física.","example_en":"The discovery of the new particle could trigger a revolution in physics.","mnemonic_en":"Pull the trigger and watch the chain snap, desencadenar the action.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El descubrimiento de la nueva partícula podría desencadenar una revolución en la física.","en":"The discovery of the new particle could trigger a revolution in physics."}]},{"spanish_text":"Prever","english_text":"Anticipate","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To expect or look forward to something and act in advance based on that expectation.","main_translations_es":["predecir","anticipar","prever"],"collocations":["anticipate the outcome","anticipate a problem","anticipate the results","anticipate the future"],"synonyms_en":["expect","foresee","predict"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to anticipate problems before they happen.","example_es":"Es importante prever los problemas antes de que ocurran.","example_en":"It''s important to anticipate problems before they happen.","mnemonic_en":"I anticipate the test by pre-veer my study notes ahead","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante prever los problemas antes de que ocurran.","en":"It''s important to anticipate problems before they happen."}]},{"spanish_text":"Logro","english_text":"Achievement","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A successful result or accomplishment that someone has attained.","main_translations_es":["Éxito","Triunfo","Conquista"],"collocations":["a great achievement","personal achievement","significant achievement","achievement unlocked"],"synonyms_en":["accomplishment","success","attainment"],"example_sentence":"This is my greatest achievement so far.","example_es":"Este es mi mayor logro hasta ahora.","example_en":"This is my greatest achievement so far.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a log rolling downhill, each roll marking an achievement.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Este es mi mayor logro hasta ahora.","en":"This is my greatest achievement so far."}]},{"spanish_text":"Retroceso","english_text":"Setback","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A reversal or hindrance that delays progress.","main_translations_es":["Retroceso","Reversión","Retrogradación"],"collocations":["a major setback","temporary setback","suffer a setback","setback in progress"],"synonyms_en":["obstacle","reversal","drawback"],"example_sentence":"The project suffered an unexpected setback after the loss of funding.","example_es":"El proyecto sufrió un retroceso inesperado después de la pérdida de financiación.","example_en":"The project suffered an unexpected setback after the loss of funding.","mnemonic_en":"When you set back a car, it rolls into a retroceso, a backward slip.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto sufrió un retroceso inesperado después de la pérdida de financiación.","en":"The project suffered an unexpected setback after the loss of funding."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aporte","english_text":"Contribution","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something given or offered, especially to help achieve a common goal.","main_translations_es":["Contribución","Aportación","Colaboración"],"collocations":["make a contribution","significant contribution","financial contribution","contribute to the cause"],"synonyms_en":["donation","input","help"],"example_sentence":"His contribution to the project was essential for its success.","example_es":"Su aporte al proyecto fue fundamental para su éxito.","example_en":"His contribution to the project was essential for its success.","mnemonic_en":"A port unloads crates as an aporte, the contribution.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Su aporte al proyecto fue fundamental para su éxito.","en":"His contribution to the project was essential for its success."}]},{"spanish_text":"Carencia","english_text":"Shortcoming","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A fault, deficiency, or lack of a desired quality.","main_translations_es":["Falta","Escasez","Déficit"],"collocations":["a shortcoming of","address the shortcoming","shortcoming in","the shortcoming is"],"synonyms_en":["deficiency","flaw","weakness"],"example_sentence":"His lack of experience was his greatest shortcoming.","example_es":"Su falta de experiencia fue su mayor carencia.","example_en":"His lack of experience was his greatest shortcoming.","mnemonic_en":"A shortcoming is a short car lacking its engine, just like a carencia, a lack.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Su falta de experiencia fue su mayor carencia.","en":"His lack of experience was his greatest shortcoming."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aseveración","english_text":"Assertion","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A confident statement that something is true.","main_translations_es":["afirmación","declaración","aseguramiento"],"collocations":["make an assertion","assertion of fact","assertion of rights","assertion that"],"synonyms_en":["statement","claim","affirmation"],"example_sentence":"His assertion that the project would be finished on time turned out to be false.","example_es":"Su aseveración de que el proyecto terminaría a tiempo resultó ser falsa.","example_en":"His assertion that the project would be finished on time turned out to be false.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lawyer shouting assertion while brandishing a giant Spanish aseveración banner.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Su aseveración de que el proyecto terminaría a tiempo resultó ser falsa.","en":"His assertion that the project would be finished on time turned out to be false."}]},{"spanish_text":"Integridad","english_text":"Integrity","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the quality of being honest and having strong moral principles","main_translations_es":["Honestidad","Rectitud","Honradez"],"collocations":["maintain integrity","integrity and honesty","integrity of the data","integrity in the workplace"],"synonyms_en":["honesty","probity","uprightness"],"example_sentence":"The integrity of the data is essential for the system''s security.","example_es":"La integridad de los datos es fundamental para la seguridad del sistema.","example_en":"The integrity of the data is essential for the system''s security.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an integral ID badge glued together, never broken, embodying integridad.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La integridad de los datos es fundamental para la seguridad del sistema.","en":"The integrity of the data is essential for the system''s security."}]},{"spanish_text":"Fiabilidad","english_text":"Reliability","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being trustworthy and consistently performing as expected.","main_translations_es":["Confiabilidad","Seguridad","Estabilidad"],"collocations":["high reliability","reliability of the system","reliability engineering","test reliability"],"synonyms_en":["dependability","trustworthiness","consistency"],"example_sentence":"The reliability of this car is impressive.","example_es":"La fiabilidad de este coche es impresionante.","example_en":"The reliability of this car is impressive.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a reliable robot you can rely on, just as a ''fiable'' person never lets you down.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La fiabilidad de este coche es impresionante.","en":"The reliability of this car is impressive."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rendición de cuentas","english_text":"Accountability","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The obligation to accept responsibility for one''s actions and decisions.","main_translations_es":["Responsabilidad","Justificación","Transparencia"],"collocations":["accountability measures","accountability framework","hold someone accountable","accountability standards"],"synonyms_en":["responsibility","answerability","liability"],"example_sentence":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","example_es":"La rendición de cuentas es esencial para la transparencia en el gobierno.","example_en":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a giant accountant with a super‑power to answer every ''cuenta''—that''s accountability.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La rendición de cuentas es esencial para la transparencia en el gobierno.","en":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government."}]},{"spanish_text":"Transparencia","english_text":"Transparency","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being clear, open, and easily understood, or the condition of allowing light to pass through so that objects behind can be seen.","main_translations_es":["Claridad","Visibilidad","Nítido"],"collocations":["transparency in government","financial transparency","transparency and accountability","transparent communication"],"synonyms_en":["openness","clarity","candor"],"example_sentence":"Transparency in government is essential for citizens'' trust.","example_es":"La transparencia en el gobierno es esencial para la confianza de los ciudadanos.","example_en":"Transparency in government is essential for citizens'' trust.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a transparent sea where you can see every fish, just like the word transparencia.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La transparencia en el gobierno es esencial para la confianza de los ciudadanos.","en":"Transparency in government is essential for citizens'' trust."}]},{"spanish_text":"Imparcial","english_text":"Impartial","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Not favoring one side over another; unbiased.","main_translations_es":["Objetivo","Neutral","Sin sesgo"],"collocations":["impartial judge","impartial decision","impartial opinion","impartial observer"],"synonyms_en":["unbiased","neutral","objective"],"example_sentence":"The judge must be impartial when delivering his verdict.","example_es":"El juez debe ser imparcial al dictar su veredicto.","example_en":"The judge must be impartial when delivering his verdict.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an impartial judge, his scales perfectly balanced, echoing the Spanish imparcial.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El juez debe ser imparcial al dictar su veredicto.","en":"The judge must be impartial when delivering his verdict."}]},{"spanish_text":"Parcial","english_text":"Biased","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Showing an unfair preference or prejudice toward something or someone.","main_translations_es":["Sesgado","Tendencioso","Parcial"],"collocations":["biased opinion","biased view","biased towards","biased against"],"synonyms_en":["partial","prejudiced","one-sided"],"example_sentence":"The judge was biased in his decision.","example_es":"El juez fue parcial en su decisión.","example_en":"The judge was biased in his decision.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a biased judge who only counts the parcial scores, ignoring the rest.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El juez fue parcial en su decisión.","en":"The judge was biased in his decision."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rigurosidad","english_text":"Rigor","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"strictness or exactness in standards, procedures, or conduct","main_translations_es":["rigor","exigencia","precisión"],"collocations":["scientific rigor","rigor of the law","rigor in methodology"],"synonyms_en":["strictness","severity","exactness"],"example_sentence":"The rigor of the scientific method ensures reliable results.","example_es":"La rigurosidad del método científico garantiza resultados fiables.","example_en":"The rigor of the scientific method ensures reliable results.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a strict foreman on a construction rig, his rigor forcing every bolt to fit perfectly.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La rigurosidad del método científico garantiza resultados fiables.","en":"The rigor of the scientific method ensures reliable results."}]},{"spanish_text":"Coexistir","english_text":"Coexist","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To exist together at the same time or in the same place.","main_translations_es":["convivir","cohabitar","coexistir"],"collocations":["coexist peacefully","coexist with","coexist in harmony","coexist side by side"],"synonyms_en":["live together","share space","cohabit"],"example_sentence":"The different cultural groups must learn to coexist in harmony.","example_es":"Los diferentes grupos culturales deben aprender a coexistir en armonía.","example_en":"The different cultural groups must learn to coexist in harmony.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a cow and a snail coexisting on a sunny meadow","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Los diferentes grupos culturales deben aprender a coexistir en armonía.","en":"The different cultural groups must learn to coexist in harmony."}]},{"spanish_text":"Conciliar","english_text":"Reconcile","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To restore harmony between parties or to make different ideas consistent.","main_translations_es":["reconciliar","armonizar","comprometer"],"collocations":["reconcile differences","reconcile accounts","reconcile with","reconcile the data"],"synonyms_en":["settle","make up","harmonize"],"example_sentence":"The mediator managed to reconcile the two parties in conflict.","example_es":"El mediador logró conciliar a las dos partes en conflicto.","example_en":"The mediator managed to reconcile the two parties 