ovechar al máximo los recursos disponibles.","en":"We must harness the available resources to the fullest."}]},{"spanish_text":"Percepción","english_text":"Perception","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of recognizing, interpreting, and organizing sensory information.","main_translations_es":["Percepción","Sensación","Observación"],"collocations":["public perception","perception of reality","visual perception"],"synonyms_en":["awareness","recognition","sensation"],"example_sentence":"His perception of the problem changed after hearing the data.","example_es":"Su percepción del problema cambió después de escuchar los datos.","example_en":"His perception of the problem changed after hearing the data.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a pear (pera) in a cage, you get the perception of its shape.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Su percepción del problema cambió después de escuchar los datos.","en":"His perception of the problem changed after hearing the data."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tendencia","english_text":"Trend","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A general direction in which something is developing or changing.","main_translations_es":["Moda","Corriente","Dirección"],"collocations":["upward trend","trend towards","trend analysis","trend line"],"synonyms_en":["fashion","tendency","movement"],"example_sentence":"The current trend is to work from home.","example_es":"La tendencia actual es trabajar desde casa.","example_en":"The current trend is to work from home.","mnemonic_en":"A new trend makes everyone tend to the same style","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La tendencia actual es trabajar desde casa.","en":"The current trend is to work from home."}]},{"spanish_text":"Repercusiones","english_text":"Repercussions","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the unintended or indirect consequences of an action or event, especially negative ones","main_translations_es":["Consecuencias","Efectos","Secuelas"],"collocations":["face the repercussions","have serious repercussions","the repercussions were felt","repercussions of the decision"],"synonyms_en":["consequences","effects","ramifications"],"example_sentence":"The repercussions of the decision were unexpected.","example_es":"Las repercusiones de la decisión fueron inesperadas.","example_en":"The repercussions of the decision were unexpected.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a drum''s re-percussion sending waves that look like the Spanish word repercusiones.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Las repercusiones de la decisión fueron inesperadas.","en":"The repercussions of the decision were unexpected."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plausible","english_text":"Plausible","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Reasonable or probable; appearing worthy of belief.","main_translations_es":["verosímil","creíble","probable"],"collocations":["plausible explanation","plausible deniability","plausible scenario","plausible argument"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"It is plausible that we will arrive on time.","example_es":"Es plausible que lleguemos a tiempo.","example_en":"It is plausible that we will arrive on time.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es plausible que lleguemos a tiempo.","en":"It is plausible that we will arrive on time."}]},{"spanish_text":"Inevitable","english_text":"Inevitable","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Impossible to avoid or prevent; certain to happen.","main_translations_es":["inevitable","inexorable","ineludible"],"collocations":["inevitable outcome","inevitable consequence","inevitable result"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"It was inevitable that the project would fail.","example_es":"Era inevitable que el proyecto fracasara.","example_en":"It was inevitable that the project would fail.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Era inevitable que el proyecto fracasara.","en":"It was inevitable that the project would fail."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rentable","english_text":"Cost-effective","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Providing good value or results relative to the amount spent.","main_translations_es":["económico","asequible","de bajo costo"],"collocations":["cost-effective solution","cost-effective strategy","cost-effective approach","cost-effective measure"],"synonyms_en":["economical","budget-friendly","money-saving"],"example_sentence":"This car is very cost-effective for the company.","example_es":"Este coche es muy rentable para la empresa.","example_en":"This car is very cost-effective for the company.","mnemonic_en":"A cost-effective deal feels as rentable as a cheap apartment you can rent.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Este coche es muy rentable para la empresa.","en":"This car is very cost-effective for the company."}]},{"spanish_text":"Práctica arraigada","english_text":"Entrenched practice","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A practice that is firmly established and difficult to change.","main_translations_es":["costumbre arraigada","práctica consolidada","hábito profundo"],"collocations":["deeply entrenched practice","long‑standing entrenched practice","entrenched practice of","entrenched practice in"],"synonyms_en":["established custom","deep‑rooted habit","ingrained tradition"],"example_sentence":"The entrenched practice of working overtime without extra pay is affecting the team''s morale.","example_es":"La práctica arraigada de trabajar horas extras sin paga adicional está afectando la moral del equipo.","example_en":"The entrenched practice of working overtime without extra pay is affecting the team''s morale.","mnemonic_en":"A train (en tren) plants roots into a practice, making it entrenched.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La práctica arraigada de trabajar horas extras sin paga adicional está afectando la moral del equipo.","en":"The entrenched practice of working overtime without extra pay is affecting the team''s morale."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir con las expectativas","english_text":"Meet expectations","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To fulfill or satisfy the standards or requirements that are anticipated.","main_translations_es":["Estar a la altura de las expectativas","Satisfacer las expectativas","Cumplir las expectativas"],"collocations":["meet expectations","live up to expectations","exceed expectations","fall short of expectations"],"synonyms_en":["fulfill expectations","live up to expectations","satisfy expectations"],"example_sentence":"The new employee managed to meet expectations of the company from his first day.","example_es":"El nuevo empleado logró cumplir con las expectativas de la empresa desde su primer día.","example_en":"The new employee managed to meet expectations of the company from his first day.","mnemonic_en":"In a meeting, a perfect cake fulfills everyone''s expectations.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El nuevo empleado logró cumplir con las expectativas de la empresa desde su primer día.","en":"The new employee managed to meet expectations of the company from his first day."}]},{"spanish_text":"Superar las expectativas","english_text":"Exceed expectations","section_name":"English C1 Vocabulary","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To go beyond what is expected.","main_translations_es":["Ir más allá de lo esperado","Superar lo esperado","Sobrepasar las expectativas"],"collocations":["exceed expectations","exceed expectations by","exceed expectations consistently","exceed expectations in performance"],"synonyms_en":["surpass expectations","go beyond expectations","outperform expectations"],"example_sentence":"Our team managed to exceed the client''s expectations with the final project.","example_es":"Nuestro equipo logró superar las expectativas del cliente con el proyecto final.","example_en":"Our team managed to exceed the client''s expectations with the final project.","mnemonic_en":"A superhero leaps over a bar, exceeding expectations.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Nuestro equipo logró superar las expectativas del cliente con el proyecto final.","en":"Our team managed to exceed the client''s expectations with the final project."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
