kes place.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo que programar una reunión con el cliente mañana.","en":"I have to schedule a meeting with the client tomorrow."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aplazar","english_text":"Postpone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To delay or put off something to a later time.","main_translations_es":["Posponer","Diferir","Atrasar"],"collocations":["postpone the meeting","postpone the deadline","postpone the launch","postpone the decision"],"synonyms_en":["delay","defer","put off"],"example_sentence":"We decided to postpone the meeting until next week.","example_es":"Decidimos aplazar la reunión para la próxima semana.","example_en":"We decided to postpone the meeting until next week.","mnemonic_en":"I post a plaque that says Aplazar to delay the meeting.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Decidimos aplazar la reunión para la próxima semana.","en":"We decided to postpone the meeting until next week."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reprogramar","english_text":"Reschedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrange for something to occur at a different time.","main_translations_es":["Posponer","Cambiar la fecha","Reagendar"],"collocations":["reschedule the meeting","reschedule an appointment","reschedule for next week","reschedule at a later date"],"synonyms_en":["postpone","defer","move to a later date"],"example_sentence":"I will reschedule the meeting for Friday.","example_es":"Voy a reprogramar la reunión para el viernes.","example_en":"I will reschedule the meeting for Friday.","mnemonic_en":"Think of reprogramming the TV schedule, so you reschedule the shows","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a reprogramar la reunión para el viernes.","en":"I will reschedule the meeting for Friday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Agenda","english_text":"Agenda","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A list of items to be discussed or acted upon, especially at a meeting.","main_translations_es":["programa","calendario","planificador"],"collocations":["set the agenda","agenda item","agenda for the meeting","agenda of the day"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"I checked my agenda before the meeting.","example_es":"Revisé mi agenda antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I checked my agenda before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Revisé mi agenda antes de la reunión.","en":"I checked my agenda before the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Punto del orden del día","english_text":"Agenda item","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific topic scheduled for discussion on an agenda.","main_translations_es":["Punto de la agenda","Tema del orden del día","Asunto del día"],"collocations":["add an agenda item","agenda item for discussion","agenda item number","agenda item to be addressed"],"synonyms_en":["discussion point","topic","meeting item"],"example_sentence":"The next agenda item will be the approval of the budget.","example_es":"El siguiente punto del orden del día será la aprobación del presupuesto.","example_en":"The next agenda item will be the approval of the budget.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a point on a calendar agenda marking today’s item.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El siguiente punto del orden del día será la aprobación del presupuesto.","en":"The next agenda item will be the approval of the budget."}]},{"spanish_text":"Acta","english_text":"Minutes","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written record of the discussions and decisions made during a meeting.","main_translations_es":["registro","acta de reunión","minuta"],"collocations":["take minutes","meeting minutes","minutes of the meeting","record the minutes"],"synonyms_en":["record","notes","proceedings"],"example_sentence":"The minutes of the meeting were approved.","example_es":"El acta de la reunión se aprobó.","example_en":"The minutes of the meeting were approved.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an act‑a written fast, like recording meeting minutes in just a few minutes.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El acta de la reunión se aprobó.","en":"The minutes of the meeting were approved."}]},{"spanish_text":"Punto de acción","english_text":"Action item","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific task or piece of work that needs to be completed.","main_translations_es":["Elemento de acción","Tarea","Acción pendiente"],"collocations":["action item list","action item owner","action item follow‑up","action item deadline"],"synonyms_en":["task","to‑do","assignment"],"example_sentence":"The action item for the next meeting is to review the budget.","example_es":"El punto de acción para la próxima reunión es revisar el presupuesto.","example_en":"The action item for the next meeting is to review the budget.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a red point on a checklist marking the action item.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El punto de acción para la próxima reunión es revisar el presupuesto.","en":"The action item for the next meeting is to review the budget."}]},{"spanish_text":"Fecha límite","english_text":"Deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A date or time by which something must be completed or submitted.","main_translations_es":["Plazo","Fecha de entrega","Vencimiento"],"collocations":["meet the deadline","deadline approaching","miss the deadline","deadline extension"],"synonyms_en":["due date","time limit","cutoff"],"example_sentence":"The deadline to submit the report is Monday at 5 p.m.","example_es":"La fecha límite para entregar el informe es el lunes a las 5 p.m.","example_en":"The deadline to submit the report is Monday at 5 p.m.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dead line at the final date, the fecha límite.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La fecha límite para entregar el informe es el lunes a las 5 p.m.","en":"The deadline to submit the report is Monday at 5 p.m."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hito","english_text":"Milestone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A significant event or point in development that marks progress or a turning point.","main_translations_es":["evento importante","punto de referencia","marca"],"collocations":["milestone birthday","milestone achievement","milestone event","milestone in history"],"synonyms_en":["landmark","turning point","benchmark"],"example_sentence":"This project reached a major milestone when we completed the testing phase.","example_es":"Este proyecto alcanzó un hito importante cuando completamos la fase de pruebas.","example_en":"This project reached a major milestone when we completed the testing phase.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a giant stone you hit to mark a milestone.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Este proyecto alcanzó un hito importante cuando completamos la fase de pruebas.","en":"This project reached a major milestone when we completed the testing phase."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entregable","english_text":"Deliverable","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A tangible or intangible item that must be completed and handed over as part of a project or contract.","main_translations_es":["producto","resultado","entrega"],"collocations":["project deliverable","deliverable deadline","deliverable item","deliverable schedule"],"synonyms_en":["output","product","submission"],"example_sentence":"The deliverable must be submitted before Friday.","example_es":"El entregable debe enviarse antes del viernes.","example_en":"The deliverable must be submitted before Friday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a delivery truck dropping a box labeled Entregable on a doorstep.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El entregable debe enviarse antes del viernes.","en":"The deliverable must be submitted before Friday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Carga de trabajo","english_text":"Workload","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The amount of work assigned to or expected from a person or group.","main_translations_es":["Carga laboral","Volumen de trabajo","Trabajo acumulado"],"collocations":["heavy workload","manage the workload","reduce the workload","workload increase"],"synonyms_en":["task load","job load","burden"],"example_sentence":"My workload has increased a lot this month.","example_es":"Mi carga de trabajo ha aumentado mucho este mes.","example_en":"My workload has increased a lot this month.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cargo of files stacked high, the heavy workload.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mi carga de trabajo ha aumentado mucho este mes.","en":"My workload has increased a lot this month."}]},{"spanish_text":"Priorizar","english_text":"Prioritize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrange or deal with tasks, items, or goals in order of importance, giving precedence to the most important ones.","main_translations_es":["Dar prioridad","Poner en primer lugar","Priorizar"],"collocations":["prioritize tasks","prioritize safety","prioritize customer needs"],"synonyms_en":["give precedence to","rank","order by importance"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to prioritize the most urgent tasks before starting the project.","example_es":"Es importante priorizar las tareas más urgentes antes de comenzar el proyecto.","example_en":"It''s important to prioritize the most urgent tasks before starting the project.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a priority list where each item shouts priorizar as you prioritize the tasks","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante priorizar las tareas más urgentes antes de comenzar el proyecto.","en":"It''s important to prioritize the most urgent tasks before starting the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Escalar un problema","english_text":"Escalate an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To raise an issue to a higher level of authority or attention.","main_translations_es":["Elevar un problema","Derivar un problema","Remitir un problema"],"collocations":["escalate an issue to management","escalate an issue quickly","escalate an issue when necessary","escalate an issue promptly"],"synonyms_en":["raise an issue","bring up a problem","elevate the issue"],"example_sentence":"If it isn''t resolved quickly, we will have to escalate an issue to the support team.","example_es":"Si no se resuelve rápidamente, tendremos que escalar un problema al equipo de soporte.","example_en":"If it isn''t resolved quickly, we will have to escalate an issue to the support team.","mnemonic_en":"Climb the ladder to raise the issue.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Si no se resuelve rápidamente, tendremos que escalar un problema al equipo de soporte.","en":"If it isn''t resolved quickly, we will have to escalate an issue to the support team."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resolver un problema","english_text":"Resolve an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To find a solution to a problem or difficulty.","main_translations_es":["Solucionar un problema","Arreglar un problema","Encontrar una solución a un problema"],"collocations":["resolve an issue quickly","resolve an issue promptly","resolve an issue with the team","resolve an issue before deadline"],"synonyms_en":["fix a problem","address a problem","settle a matter"],"example_sentence":"I need to resolve a problem before the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito resolver un problema antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I need to resolve a problem before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a resolver robot untangling a tangled issue like a problem knot.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito resolver un problema antes de la reunión.","en":"I need to resolve a problem before the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ponerse al día","english_text":"Catch up","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To reach the same level or position as someone else after having fallen behind.","main_translations_es":["Actualizarse","Ponerse al corriente","Poner al día"],"collocations":["catch up on","catch up with","catch up later","catch up to"],"synonyms_en":["keep up","get up to speed","bring up to date"],"example_sentence":"After the holidays, I had to catch up with work.","example_es":"Después de las vacaciones, tuve que ponerme al día con el trabajo.","example_en":"After the holidays, I had to catch up with work.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize catching a fish and lifting it up to the day to stay current.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Después de las vacaciones, tuve que ponerme al día con el trabajo.","en":"After the holidays, I had to catch up with work."}]},{"spanish_text":"Informe de progreso","english_text":"Progress report","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document that details the status and developments of a project or task.","main_translations_es":["Reporte de avance","Informe de avances","Informe de progreso"],"collocations":["submit a progress report","annual progress report","progress report template","progress report deadline"],"synonyms_en":["status update","performance review","update report"],"example_sentence":"The team submitted the progress report before the deadline.","example_es":"El equipo entregó el informe de progreso antes de la fecha límite.","example_en":"The team submitted the progress report before the deadline.","mnemonic_en":"A pro writes a report on his progress, just like an informe de progreso.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El equipo entregó el informe de progreso antes de la fecha límite.","en":"The team submitted the progress report before the deadline."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estado actual","english_text":"Current status","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The present condition or situation of something.","main_translations_es":["Situación actual","Estado presente","Condición actual"],"collocations":["current status update","check the current status","current status report","as per the current status"],"synonyms_en":["present condition","existing state","ongoing situation"],"example_sentence":"The current status of the project is uncertain.","example_es":"El estado actual del proyecto es incierto.","example_en":"The current status of the project is uncertain.","mnemonic_en":"A flowing current tells the state that está now.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El estado actual del proyecto es incierto.","en":"The current status of the project is uncertain."}]},{"spanish_text":"Retrasado","english_text":"Behind schedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adverbial phrase","definition_en":"Later than planned or expected; not on time.","main_translations_es":["Atrasado","Demorado","Tardío"],"collocations":["fall behind schedule","get behind schedule","run behind schedule","be behind schedule"],"synonyms_en":["delayed","running late","late"],"example_sentence":"The project is behind schedule and will not be finished on time.","example_es":"El proyecto está retrasado y no se completará a tiempo.","example_en":"The project is behind schedule and will not be finished on time.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a delayed trash truck re‑trash‑ado stuck behind schedule","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto está retrasado y no se completará a tiempo.","en":"The project is behind schedule and will not be finished on time."}]},{"spanish_text":"Adelantado","english_text":"Ahead of schedule","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Occurring earlier than the planned time.","main_translations_es":["Anticipado","Previo","Por delante"],"collocations":["finish ahead of schedule","be ahead of schedule","run ahead of schedule","complete ahead of schedule"],"synonyms_en":["early","ahead of time","in advance"],"example_sentence":"The project is ahead of schedule and we will finish earlier than planned.","example_es":"El proyecto está adelantado y terminaremos antes de lo previsto.","example_en":"The project is ahead of schedule and we will finish earlier than planned.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a runner ahead shouting adelante to stay ahead of schedule","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto está adelantado y terminaremos antes de lo previsto.","en":"The project is ahead of schedule and we will finish earlier than planned."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir el plazo","english_text":"Meet the deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To complete something before or at the specified time limit.","main_translations_es":["Respetar el plazo","Entregar a tiempo","Cumplir la fecha límite"],"collocations":["to meet the deadline","hard to meet the deadline","meet the deadline on time","struggle to meet the deadline"],"synonyms_en":["hit the deadline","make the deadline","finish on time"],"example_sentence":"We have to meet the deadline to submit the report.","example_es":"Tenemos que cumplir el plazo para presentar el informe.","example_en":"We have to meet the deadline to submit the report.","mnemonic_en":"I meet the deadline by arriving at the plaza clock right on time.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Tenemos que cumplir el plazo para presentar el informe.","en":"We have to meet the deadline to submit the report."}]},{"spanish_text":"Incumplir el plazo","english_text":"Miss the deadline","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To fail to meet a deadline.","main_translations_es":["No cumplir el plazo","Pasar la fecha límite","Atrasarse en la entrega"],"collocations":["miss the deadline","missed the deadline","to miss a deadline","deadline missed"],"synonyms_en":["fail to meet the deadline","be late","miss the due date"],"example_sentence":"I don''t want to miss the deadline for submission.","example_es":"No quiero incumplir el plazo de entrega.","example_en":"I don''t want to miss the deadline for submission.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a Miss ignoring the plaza sign and therefore missing the deadline.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No quiero incumplir el plazo de entrega.","en":"I don''t want to miss the deadline for submission."}]},{"spanish_text":"Disponibilidad","english_text":"Availability","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The state of being ready for use or obtainable.","main_translations_es":["Disponibilidad","Accesibilidad","Libre disponibilidad"],"collocations":["check availability","availability of resources","availability schedule","availability status"],"synonyms_en":["readiness","accessibility","presence"],"example_sentence":"The availability of seats is limited.","example_es":"La disponibilidad de los asientos es limitada.","example_en":"The availability of seats is limited.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dispenser of time, showing my availability.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La disponibilidad de los asientos es limitada.","en":"The availability of seats is limited."}]},{"spanish_text":"Franja horaria","english_text":"Time slot","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific period of time allocated for an activity or appointment.","main_translations_es":["Horario","Intervalo de tiempo","Periodo"],"collocations":["book a time slot","available time slot","reserve a time slot","time slot allocation"],"synonyms_en":["time window","time period","schedule slot"],"example_sentence":"What is your available time slot for the meeting?","example_es":"¿Cuál es tu franja horaria disponible para la reunión?","example_en":"What is your available time slot for the meeting?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a striped clock, each franja marking a different time slot","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"¿Cuál es tu franja horaria disponible para la reunión?","en":"What is your available time slot for the meeting?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Conflicto de horario","english_text":"Scheduling conflict","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A situation where two or more events are planned for the same time, making it impossible to attend all of them.","main_translations_es":["Conflicto de agenda","Choque de horarios","Solapamiento de horarios"],"collocations":["due to a scheduling conflict","resolve a scheduling conflict","avoid scheduling conflicts","schedule conflict"],"synonyms_en":["time clash","calendar clash","appointment overlap"],"example_sentence":"I have a scheduling conflict and won''t be able to attend the meeting.","example_es":"Tengo un conflicto de horario y no podré asistir a la reunión.","example_en":"I have a scheduling conflict and won''t be able to attend the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a calendar and a clock in a fight, a scheduling conflict.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo un conflicto de horario y no podré asistir a la reunión.","en":"I have a scheduling conflict and won''t be able to attend the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plantilla","english_text":"Template","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A pre-designed format or pattern used as a starting point for creating something.","main_translations_es":["Modelo","Formato","Plantilla"],"collocations":["template file","template design","template engine"],"synonyms_en":["pattern","model","prototype"],"example_sentence":"The template of the report is available on the intranet.","example_es":"La plantilla del informe está disponible en la intranet.","example_en":"The template of the report is available on the intranet.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a plant sprouting from a template sheet, like a green leaf in a paper mold.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La plantilla del informe está disponible en la intranet.","en":"The template of the report is available on the intranet."}]},{"spanish_text":"Borrador","english_text":"Draft","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A preliminary version of a document or plan.","main_translations_es":["Esbozo","Boceto","Proyecto"],"collocations":["draft a letter","draft legislation","draft version","draft copy"],"synonyms_en":["outline","sketch","preliminary version"],"example_sentence":"I will review the draft of the report before sending it.","example_es":"Voy a revisar el borrador del informe antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"I will review the draft of the report before sending it.","mnemonic_en":"A cold draft sneaks through the borrador door, reminding you it''s a draft.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a revisar el borrador del informe antes de enviarlo.","en":"I will review the draft of the report before sending it."}]},{"spanish_text":"Presupuesto","english_text":"Budget","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan that estimates expected income and expenses over a specific period.","main_translations_es":["Presupuesto","Plan financiero","Estimación de costos"],"collocations":["budget plan","budget cuts","budget meeting","budget allocation"],"synonyms_en":["financial plan","spending plan","allocation"],"example_sentence":"The budget for the project was approved last week.","example_es":"El presupuesto para el proyecto se aprobó la semana pasada.","example_en":"The budget for the project was approved last week.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bud getting a giant receipt labeled ''presupuesto'' – that''s your budget.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El presupuesto para el proyecto se aprobó la semana pasada.","en":"The budget for the project was approved last week."}]},{"spanish_text":"Previsión","english_text":"Forecast","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A prediction or estimate of future events, such as weather or economic conditions.","main_translations_es":["Pronóstico","Predicción","Proyección"],"collocations":["weather forecast","sales forecast","forecast the future"],"synonyms_en":["prediction","projection","prognosis"],"example_sentence":"The forecast predicts rain for tomorrow.","example_es":"La previsión del tiempo indica lluvia para mañana.","example_en":"The forecast predicts rain for tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a forecaster casting a crystal ball, foreseeing the future like a clear prevision.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La previsión del tiempo indica lluvia para mañana.","en":"The forecast predicts rain for tomorrow."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estimación","english_text":"Estimate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An approximate calculation or judgment of the value, size, or amount of something.","main_translations_es":["Cálculo","Valoración","Aproximación"],"collocations":["estimate the cost","rough estimate","estimate the time","make an estimate"],"synonyms_en":["approximation","guess","assessment"],"example_sentence":"According to the meteorologist''s estimate, it will rain tomorrow.","example_es":"Según la estimación del meteorólogo, lloverá mañana.","example_en":"According to the meteorologist''s estimate, it will rain tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a scientist saying estimate while holding a chart titled Estimación, calculating the unknown","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Según la estimación del meteorólogo, lloverá mañana.","en":"According to the meteorologist''s estimate, it will rain tomorrow."}]},{"spanish_text":"Alcance","english_text":"Scope","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the extent or range of something''s coverage, influence, or operation","main_translations_es":["Ámbito","Cobertura","Extensión"],"collocations":["out of scope","scope of work","broad scope","scope creep"],"synonyms_en":["range","extent","breadth"],"example_sentence":"The scope of the project includes the implementation of new technologies.","example_es":"El alcance del proyecto incluye la implementación de nuevas tecnologías.","example_en":"The scope of the project includes the implementation of new technologies.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a telescope''s scope reaching far, just like the Spanish alcance meaning reach.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El alcance del proyecto incluye la implementación de nuevas tecnologías.","en":"The scope of the project includes the implementation of new technologies."}]},{"spanish_text":"Requisito","english_text":"Requirement","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something that is needed or demanded.","main_translations_es":["exigencia","condición","requerimiento"],"collocations":["meeting the requirement","as a requirement","requirement for","mandatory requirement"],"synonyms_en":["necessity","prerequisite","condition"],"example_sentence":"The requirement to enroll in the course is to be at least 18 years old.","example_es":"El requisito para inscribirse en el curso es tener al menos 18 años.","example_en":"The requirement to enroll in the course is to be at least 18 years old.","mnemonic_en":"The teacher demands a requisito, the requirement, on the board.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El requisito para inscribirse en el curso es tener al menos 18 años.","en":"The requirement to enroll in the course is to be at least 18 years old."}]},{"spanish_text":"Dependencia","english_text":"Dependency","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A condition in which a person, group, or thing relies on or is controlled by another for support or aid.","main_translations_es":["subordinación","adicción","sujeción"],"collocations":["dependency injection","dependency graph","dependency management","dependency relationship"],"synonyms_en":["reliance","dependence","subordination"],"example_sentence":"The dependency on fossil fuels is an environmental problem.","example_es":"La dependencia de los combustibles fósiles es un problema ambiental.","example_en":"The dependency on fossil fuels is an environmental problem.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a DEPENDENT dog clutching a DEPENDENCY rope, never letting go.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La dependencia de los combustibles fósiles es un problema ambiental.","en":"The dependency on fossil fuels is an environmental problem."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cuello de botella","english_text":"Bottleneck","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A narrow point or stage that restricts flow or progress, causing a delay.","main_translations_es":["Obstáculo","Punto crítico","Cuello de botella"],"collocations":["bottleneck in production","traffic bottleneck","bottleneck effect","bottleneck situation"],"synonyms_en":["obstacle","constraint","impediment"],"example_sentence":"The project was delayed because there was a bottleneck in production.","example_es":"El proyecto se retrasó porque hubo un cuello de botella en la producción.","example_en":"The project was delayed because there was a bottleneck in production.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a bottle neck squeezing traffic like a bottleneck.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El proyecto se retrasó porque hubo un cuello de botella en la producción.","en":"The project was delayed because there was a bottleneck in production."}]},{"spanish_text":"Riesgo","english_text":"Risk","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the possibility of loss, injury, or other adverse outcome","main_translations_es":["peligro","amenaza","contingencia"],"collocations":["take a risk","risk assessment","risk management","high risk"],"synonyms_en":["danger","hazard","peril"],"example_sentence":"Investing in that company carries a great risk.","example_es":"Invertir en esa empresa conlleva un gran riesgo.","example_en":"Investing in that company carries a great risk.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dice rolling off a cliff, shouting Riesgo as it falls.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Invertir en esa empresa conlleva un gran riesgo.","en":"Investing in that company carries a great risk."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mitigación","english_text":"Mitigation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of reducing the severity, seriousness, or harmful effects of something.","main_translations_es":["Reducción","Alivio","Atenuación"],"collocations":["risk mitigation","climate change mitigation","mitigation measures","mitigation strategies"],"synonyms_en":["reduction","alleviation","lessening"],"example_sentence":"Mitigation of climate change requires urgent actions.","example_es":"La mitigación del cambio climático requiere acciones urgentes.","example_en":"Mitigation of climate change requires urgent actions.","mnemonic_en":"A mitten (miti) covers the garden, showing mitigation protects the area.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La mitigación del cambio climático requiere acciones urgentes.","en":"Mitigation of climate change requires urgent actions."}]},{"spanish_text":"Lanzamiento","english_text":"Launch","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of sending a product, vehicle, or spacecraft into operation or into the air.","main_translations_es":["Despegue","Salida","Emisión"],"collocations":["launch a product","launch a rocket","launch a campaign","launch into space"],"synonyms_en":["initiate","start","send off"],"example_sentence":"The launch of the new phone will be next month.","example_es":"El lanzamiento del nuevo teléfono será el próximo mes.","example_en":"The launch of the new phone will be next month.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a rocket launch where the crew yells Lanz as they throw the payload skyward.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El lanzamiento del nuevo teléfono será el próximo mes.","en":"The launch of the new phone will be next month."}]},{"spanish_text":"Despliegue","english_text":"Rollout","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of introducing or launching a new product, service, or system to the market or users.","main_translations_es":["Implementación","Lanzamiento","Puesta en marcha"],"collocations":["rollout plan","product rollout","rollout schedule","rollout strategy"],"synonyms_en":["deployment","launch","implementation"],"example_sentence":"The rollout of the new software is scheduled for next Monday.","example_es":"El despliegue del nuevo software está programado para el próximo lunes.","example_en":"The rollout of the new software is scheduled for next Monday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a giant carpet being rolled out, like a deployment (despliegue) across the floor.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El despliegue del nuevo software está programado para el próximo lunes.","en":"The rollout of the new software is scheduled for next Monday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Incorporación","english_text":"Onboarding","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of integrating new employees into an organization.","main_translations_es":["Integración","Admisión","Incorporación"],"collocations":["employee onboarding","customer onboarding","onboarding process","onboarding program"],"synonyms_en":["orientation","induction","training"],"example_sentence":"The onboarding of the new employees will take place next week.","example_es":"La incorporación de los nuevos empleados se realizará la próxima semana.","example_en":"The onboarding of the new employees will take place next week.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself stepping onto a board, incorporating yourself into the crew—that''s onboarding.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La incorporación de los nuevos empleados se realizará la próxima semana.","en":"The onboarding of the new employees will take place next week."}]},{"spanish_text":"Capacitación","english_text":"Training","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of teaching or developing skills and knowledge.","main_translations_es":["Entrenamiento","Formación","Adiestramiento"],"collocations":["training program","on-the-job training","training session","training manual"],"synonyms_en":["instruction","coaching","education"],"example_sentence":"Staff training is essential to improve productivity.","example_es":"La capacitación del personal es esencial para mejorar la productividad.","example_en":"Staff training is essential to improve productivity.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a trainer handing a cap and saying capacitación to start the training.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La capacitación del personal es esencial para mejorar la productividad.","en":"Staff training is essential to improve productivity."}]},{"spanish_text":"Retroalimentación","english_text":"Feedback","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Information or reactions given about a performance, product, or behavior, used to guide improvement.","main_translations_es":["comentarios","opinión","valoración"],"collocations":["give feedback","receive feedback","constructive feedback","feedback loop"],"synonyms_en":["response","input","reaction"],"example_sentence":"User feedback is essential for improving the product.","example_es":"La retroalimentación de los usuarios es esencial para mejorar el producto.","example_en":"User feedback is essential for improving the product.","mnemo