{"es":"Después de tres años de trabajo duro, recibió un ascenso.","en":"After three years of hard work, he received a promotion."}]},{"spanish_text":"Renuncia","english_text":"Resignation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of voluntarily giving up a job or position.","main_translations_es":["Dimisión","Renuncia","Abandono"],"collocations":["letter of resignation","resignation letter","accept resignation","submit resignation"],"synonyms_en":["quit","stepping down","departure"],"example_sentence":"His resignation from the position surprised everyone.","example_es":"Su renuncia al cargo sorprendió a todos.","example_en":"His resignation from the position surprised everyone.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a boss handing a letter that says renuncia, signaling his resignation","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Su renuncia al cargo sorprendió a todos.","en":"His resignation from the position surprised everyone."}]},{"spanish_text":"Contratación","english_text":"Hiring","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of employing someone for a job.","main_translations_es":["Reclutamiento","Selección de personal","Incorporación"],"collocations":["hiring process","hiring manager","hiring freeze","hiring spree"],"synonyms_en":["recruiting","staffing","employment"],"example_sentence":"Hiring new employees is a priority this quarter.","example_es":"La contratación de nuevos empleados es una prioridad este trimestre.","example_en":"Hiring new employees is a priority this quarter.","mnemonic_en":"When hiring, picture a contract—contratación reminds you of a signed deal.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La contratación de nuevos empleados es una prioridad este trimestre.","en":"Hiring new employees is a priority this quarter."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entrevista","english_text":"Interview","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A formal meeting where one person asks questions and another provides answers, often to assess suitability for a job or to gather information.","main_translations_es":["Entrevista","Charla","Entrevista laboral"],"collocations":["job interview","interview process","interview panel","interview questions"],"synonyms_en":["conversation","questioning","meeting"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow I have a job interview at ten o''clock.","example_es":"Mañana tengo una entrevista de trabajo a las diez.","example_en":"Tomorrow I have a job interview at ten o''clock.","mnemonic_en":"Enter the vista, the doorway to the interview.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mañana tengo una entrevista de trabajo a las diez.","en":"Tomorrow I have a job interview at ten o''clock."}]},{"spanish_text":"Candidato","english_text":"Candidate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who is seeking or being considered for a position, office, or honor.","main_translations_es":["aspirante","postulante","concursante"],"collocations":["job candidate","candidate for office","candidate selection","candidate profile"],"synonyms_en":["applicant","contender","nominee"],"example_sentence":"The candidate won the election with a large majority.","example_es":"El candidato ganó las elecciones con una amplia mayoría.","example_en":"The candidate won the election with a large majority.","mnemonic_en":"The candidate shows a candid photo to a taco vendor at the door.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El candidato ganó las elecciones con una amplia mayoría.","en":"The candidate won the election with a large majority."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vacante","english_text":"Opening","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A position or opportunity that is available, especially a job vacancy.","main_translations_es":["Puesto disponible","Posición vacante","Oferta de empleo"],"collocations":["job opening","opening ceremony","opening hours","opening statement"],"synonyms_en":["vacancy","position","opportunity"],"example_sentence":"There is an opening for a software engineer at the company.","example_es":"Hay una vacante para ingeniero de software en la empresa.","example_en":"There is an opening for a software engineer at the company.","mnemonic_en":"Picture opening a vacant (vacante) door to a new job.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Hay una vacante para ingeniero de software en la empresa.","en":"There is an opening for a software engineer at the company."}]},{"spanish_text":"Descripción del puesto","english_text":"Job description","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written statement outlining the duties, responsibilities, and requirements of a particular job.","main_translations_es":["Perfil del puesto","Resumen del puesto","Descripción del cargo"],"collocations":["write a job description","review the job description","job description template","job description format"],"synonyms_en":["position summary","role outline","job profile"],"example_sentence":"The job description includes project management responsibilities.","example_es":"La descripción del puesto incluye responsabilidades de gestión de proyectos.","example_en":"The job description includes project management responsibilities.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a job posting wearing a big badge that reads descripción del puesto","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La descripción del puesto incluye responsabilidades de gestión de proyectos.","en":"The job description includes project management responsibilities."}]},{"spanish_text":"Trabajo remoto","english_text":"Remote work","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A work arrangement in which an employee performs their job duties from a location outside the employer''s premises, typically using digital communication tools.","main_translations_es":["Teletrabajo","Trabajo a distancia","Trabajo desde casa"],"collocations":["remote work policy","remote work arrangement","remote work opportunities","remote work culture"],"synonyms_en":["telecommuting","working from home","flexible work"],"example_sentence":"I work remotely from home every day.","example_es":"Trabajo remoto desde casa todos los días.","example_en":"I work remotely from home every day.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a remote control typing a report while sitting on a couch like a remoto office.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Trabajo remoto desde casa todos los días.","en":"I work remotely from home every day."}]},{"spanish_text":"Trabajo híbrido","english_text":"Hybrid work","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A work arrangement that combines remote and on‑site duties.","main_translations_es":["Modelo híbrido de trabajo","Trabajo mixto","Trabajo a distancia y presencial"],"collocations":["hybrid work model","hybrid work arrangement","flexible hybrid work","remote and on‑site hybrid work"],"synonyms_en":["flexible work","blended work","remote‑office model"],"example_sentence":"I prefer hybrid work because it combines office and remote work.","example_es":"Prefiero el trabajo híbrido porque combina la oficina y el teletrabajo.","example_en":"I prefer hybrid work because it combines office and remote work.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a half‑robot employee at a desk, because hybrid work sounds like the Spanish híbrido for mixed.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Prefiero el trabajo híbrido porque combina la oficina y el teletrabajo.","en":"I prefer hybrid work because it combines office and remote work."}]},{"spanish_text":"Presencial","english_text":"On-site","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"Located or occurring at the place where the activity takes place.","main_translations_es":["en persona","cara a cara","presencial"],"collocations":["on-site support","on-site training","on-site inspection","on-site meeting"],"synonyms_en":["in person","at the location","on location"],"example_sentence":"The course will be on-site, so you''ll have to attend in person.","example_es":"El curso será presencial, así que tendrás que asistir en persona.","example_en":"The course will be on-site, so you''ll have to attend in person.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a presenter on a construction site shouting \"presencial\" as the on‑site meeting begins.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El curso será presencial, así que tendrás que asistir en persona.","en":"The course will be on-site, so you''ll have to attend in person."}]},{"spanish_text":"Compañero de trabajo","english_text":"Coworker","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person who works with you, typically in the same organization or workplace.","main_translations_es":["Colega","Compañero de oficina","Colega de trabajo"],"collocations":["my coworker","coworker relationship","coworker collaboration","coworker support"],"synonyms_en":["colleague","workmate","associate"],"example_sentence":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","example_es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","example_en":"My coworker helped me finish the report.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cow at the office, your coworker, because cow plus work sounds like coworker","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mi compañero de trabajo me ayudó a terminar el informe.","en":"My coworker helped me finish the report."}]},{"spanish_text":"Parte interesada","english_text":"Stakeholder","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or group that has an interest or concern in something, especially a business or project.","main_translations_es":["parte interesada","interesado","grupo de interés"],"collocations":["key stakeholder","stakeholder engagement","stakeholder analysis","primary stakeholder"],"synonyms_en":["interested party","concerned party","shareholder"],"example_sentence":"The stakeholder approved the new project plan.","example_es":"La parte interesada aprobó el nuevo plan del proyecto.","example_en":"The stakeholder approved the new project plan.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a steak holder serving the interested party, because stakeholder sounds like steak holder.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La parte interesada aprobó el nuevo plan del proyecto.","en":"The stakeholder approved the new project plan."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cliente","english_text":"Client","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or organization that receives professional services or purchases goods from a business.","main_translations_es":["Cliente","Comprador","Consumidor"],"collocations":["client base","client meeting","client relationship","client service"],"synonyms_en":["customer","patron","buyer"],"example_sentence":"The client requested a refund.","example_es":"El cliente pidió una devolución.","example_en":"The client requested a refund.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a client handing a contract labeled Cliente.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El cliente pidió una devolución.","en":"The client requested a refund."}]},{"spanish_text":"Proveedor","english_text":"Vendor","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or company that sells goods or services.","main_translations_es":["Suministrador","Distribuidor","Abastecedor"],"collocations":["vendor management","preferred vendor","vendor contract","vendor list"],"synonyms_en":["seller","supplier","merchant"],"example_sentence":"The vendor delivered the goods on time.","example_es":"El proveedor entregó la mercancía a tiempo.","example_en":"The vendor delivered the goods on time.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a vendor handing out a ''proveedor'' badge while selling his wares.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El proveedor entregó la mercancía a tiempo.","en":"The vendor delivered the goods on time."}]},{"spanish_text":"Negociar","english_text":"Negotiate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To discuss terms and reach an agreement.","main_translations_es":["tratar","concertar","llegar a un acuerdo"],"collocations":["negotiate a deal","negotiate terms","negotiate a contract","negotiate with"],"synonyms_en":["bargain","mediate","hammer out"],"example_sentence":"We will negotiate the terms of the contract tomorrow.","example_es":"Vamos a negociar los términos del contrato mañana.","example_en":"We will negotiate the terms of the contract tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"I negotiate while the word negociar echoes like a courtroom gavel.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Vamos a negociar los términos del contrato mañana.","en":"We will negotiate the terms of the contract tomorrow."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a un consenso","english_text":"Reach a consensus","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To arrive at a shared agreement among all parties.","main_translations_es":["Alcanzar un consenso","Lograr un consenso","Conseguir un consenso"],"collocations":["reach a consensus on","reach a consensus among stakeholders","reach a consensus quickly","reach a consensus about"],"synonyms_en":["agree","come to an agreement","find common ground"],"example_sentence":"After long discussions, we finally managed to reach a consensus on the project.","example_es":"Después de largas discusiones, finalmente logramos llegar a un consenso sobre el proyecto.","example_en":"After long discussions, we finally managed to reach a consensus on the project.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine reaching out to take a census, everyone agreeing on the count.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Después de largas discusiones, finalmente logramos llegar a un consenso sobre el proyecto.","en":"After long discussions, we finally managed to reach a consensus on the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Alinearse","english_text":"Align on","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to agree upon or adopt a common position or plan","main_translations_es":["coordinarse","ponerse de acuerdo","ajustarse"],"collocations":["align on goals","align on strategy","align on expectations","align on priorities"],"synonyms_en":["agree on","concur on","reach consensus on"],"example_sentence":"The teams must align on the company''s objectives.","example_es":"Los equipos deben alinearse con los objetivos de la empresa.","example_en":"The teams must align on the company''s objectives.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a line of ants aligning on a rope, just like ''alinearse'' means to line up.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Los equipos deben alinearse con los objetivos de la empresa.","en":"The teams must align on the company''s objectives."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aclarar expectativas","english_text":"Clarify expectations","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To make the expectations clear.","main_translations_es":["Alinear expectativas","Establecer expectativas claras","Definir expectativas"],"collocations":["clarify expectations with the team","clarify expectations early","clarify expectations beforehand"],"synonyms_en":["Set clear expectations","Explain expectations","Define expectations"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to clarify expectations before starting the project.","example_es":"Es importante aclarar expectativas antes de iniciar el proyecto.","example_en":"It''s important to clarify expectations before starting the project.","mnemonic_en":"Clear glass clears the fog, just as ''aclarar'' clears expectations.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante aclarar expectativas antes de iniciar el proyecto.","en":"It''s important to clarify expectations before starting the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asumir responsabilidad","english_text":"Take ownership","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To accept responsibility for something.","main_translations_es":["Asumir la responsabilidad","Hacerse cargo","Responsabilizarse"],"collocations":["take ownership of the project","take ownership of your actions","take ownership and lead","take ownership of the issue"],"synonyms_en":["Assume responsibility","Take charge","Own up"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to take ownership of your mistakes.","example_es":"Es importante asumir responsabilidad por tus errores.","example_en":"It''s important to take ownership of your mistakes.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine you take the own ship, assuming full responsibility.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante asumir responsabilidad por tus errores.","en":"It''s important to take ownership of your mistakes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Delegar","english_text":"Delegate","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To entrust a task or responsibility to another person.","main_translations_es":["Encargar","Asignar","Transferir"],"collocations":["delegate authority","delegate tasks","delegate responsibilities","delegate decision‑making"],"synonyms_en":["assign","empower","appoint"],"example_sentence":"I learned to delegate tasks to be more efficient.","example_es":"Aprendí a delegar tareas para ser más eficiente.","example_en":"I learned to delegate tasks to be more efficient.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a delegate handing a leg to a gar, passing the work to someone else.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Aprendí a delegar tareas para ser más eficiente.","en":"I learned to delegate tasks to be more efficient."}]},{"spanish_text":"Transferir una tarea","english_text":"Hand over a task","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To give responsibility for a task to someone else.","main_translations_es":["Ceder una tarea","Entregar una tarea","Pasar una tarea"],"collocations":["hand over a task to a colleague","hand over the task","hand over tasks","hand over the responsibility"],"synonyms_en":["delegate a task","assign a task","pass on a task"],"example_sentence":"I will hand over a task to my colleague so they can finish it sooner.","example_es":"Voy a transferir una tarea a mi colega para que la termine antes.","example_en":"I will hand over a task to my colleague so they can finish it sooner.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself handing a ''tarea'' folder across the desk to a colleague.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a transferir una tarea a mi colega para que la termine antes.","en":"I will hand over a task to my colleague so they can finish it sooner."}]},{"spanish_text":"Aprobar","english_text":"Approve","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To officially accept or give consent to something.","main_translations_es":["Autorizar","Ratificar","Aceptar"],"collocations":["approve of","approve the budget","give approval","receive approval"],"synonyms_en":["endorse","sanction","ratify"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to approve the new policy.","example_es":"El comité decidió aprobar la nueva política.","example_en":"The committee decided to approve the new policy.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a pro giving a nod, saying ''Apro'' as they approve the plan.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió aprobar la nueva política.","en":"The committee decided to approve the new policy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rechazar","english_text":"Reject","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To refuse to accept, consider, or agree with something.","main_translations_es":["Denegar","Rehusar","Rechazar"],"collocations":["reject the proposal","reject the offer","reject the hypothesis","reject the application"],"synonyms_en":["refuse","turn down","dismiss"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to reject the proposed tariff increase.","example_es":"El comité decidió rechazar la propuesta de aumento de tarifas.","example_en":"The committee decided to reject the proposed tariff increase.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a chef shouting REJECT, sounding like reh-CHAHZAR, as he throws a burnt cake into the trash.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió rechazar la propuesta de aumento de tarifas.","en":"The committee decided to reject the proposed tariff increase."}]},{"spanish_text":"Revisar","english_text":"Review","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To examine or assess something again or in detail.","main_translations_es":["Repasar","Examinar","Corregir"],"collocations":["review the literature","performance review","review meeting","review process"],"synonyms_en":["examine","inspect","assess"],"example_sentence":"I will review the report before sending it.","example_es":"Voy a revisar el informe antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"I will review the report before sending it.","mnemonic_en":"I RE-VIEW the report, just like I revisar a document.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a revisar el informe antes de enviarlo.","en":"I will review the report before sending it."}]},{"spanish_text":"Redactar","english_text":"Draft","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To prepare a preliminary version of a document or text.","main_translations_es":["Escribir","Elaborar","Redactar"],"collocations":["draft a letter","draft a proposal","draft an email","draft a contract"],"synonyms_en":["outline","sketch","preliminary version"],"example_sentence":"I will draft the report before the meeting.","example_es":"Voy a redactar el informe antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I will draft the report before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a red act drafting a paper, linking Redactar to Draft.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a redactar el informe antes de la reunión.","en":"I will draft the report before the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resumir","english_text":"Summarize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give a brief statement of the main points of something.","main_translations_es":["Sintetizar","Hacer un resumen","Abreviar"],"collocations":["summarize the main points","summarize the findings","summarize the report","summarize briefly"],"synonyms_en":["condense","recap","give a synopsis"],"example_sentence":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","example_es":"Por favor, resume el artículo en tres frases.","example_en":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","mnemonic_en":"I take the sum of facts and then summarize, just like resumir neatly wraps them up.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, resume el artículo en tres frases.","en":"Please summarize the article in three sentences."}]},{"spanish_text":"Destacar","english_text":"Highlight","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To emphasize or make something stand out.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Subrayar","Enfatizar"],"collocations":["highlight the main points","highlight a problem","highlight in yellow","highlight the differences"],"synonyms_en":["emphasize","underscore","spotlight"],"example_sentence":"The report should highlight last year''s achievements.","example_es":"El informe debe destacar los logros del año pasado.","example_en":"The report should highlight last year''s achievements.","mnemonic_en":"A bright spotlight high lights the actor, so he destacar on the stage.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El informe debe destacar los logros del año pasado.","en":"The report should highlight last year''s achievements."}]},{"spanish_text":"Plantear una inquietud","english_text":"Raise a concern","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To bring up or express a worry or issue.","main_translations_es":["Expresar una inquietud","Manifestar una preocupación","Elevar una queja"],"collocations":["raise a concern about","raise a concern with","raise a concern to","raise a concern regarding"],"synonyms_en":["express worry","voice a concern","bring up an issue"],"example_sentence":"I wanted to raise a concern about the new work schedule.","example_es":"Quería plantear una inquietud sobre el nuevo horario de trabajo.","example_en":"I wanted to raise a concern about the new work schedule.","mnemonic_en":"Raise a concern like planting a root of worry in the ground","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Quería plantear una inquietud sobre el nuevo horario de trabajo.","en":"I wanted to raise a concern about the new work schedule."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abordar un asunto","english_text":"Address an issue","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To deal with or discuss a problem or topic.","main_translations_es":["Tratar un tema","Enfrentar un problema","Lidiar con un asunto"],"collocations":["address an issue promptly","address an issue head-on","address an issue in the meeting","address an issue with management"],"synonyms_en":["deal with a problem","tackle a problem","handle a matter"],"example_sentence":"We need to address the issue of safety in the company as soon as possible.","example_es":"Necesitamos abordar el asunto de la seguridad en la empresa lo antes posible.","example_en":"We need to address the issue of safety in the company as soon as possible.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a dress (address) patching a torn issue.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesitamos abordar el asunto de la seguridad en la empresa lo antes posible.","en":"We need to address the issue of safety in the company as soon as possible."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir con el seguimiento","english_text":"Follow through","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To continue an action or plan until it is completed.","main_translations_es":["dar seguimiento","realizar el seguimiento","llevar a cabo el seguimiento"],"collocations":["follow through on a promise","follow through with a plan","follow through on commitments"],"synonyms_en":["carry out","see it through","execute"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to follow through with patient follow-up after surgery.","example_es":"Es importante cumplir con el seguimiento de los pacientes después de la cirugía.","example_en":"It''s important to follow through with patient follow-up after surgery.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a fulfillment arrow that follows through a tunnel to the finish line.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante cumplir con el seguimiento de los pacientes después de la cirugía.","en":"It''s important to follow through with patient follow-up after surgery."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cerrar el circuito","english_text":"Close the loop","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To complete a process by providing the missing information or final step.","main_translations_es":["Completar el circuito","Cerrar el lazo","Finalizar el circuito"],"collocations":["close the loop on","close the loop with","close the loop in the process","close the loop for feedback"],"synonyms_en":["complete the cycle","wrap up","finalize"],"example_sentence":"To prevent a short circuit, we must close the loop before turning on the device.","example_es":"Para evitar el cortocircuito, debemos cerrar el circuito antes de encender el dispositivo.","example_en":"To prevent a short circuit, we must close the loop before turning on the device.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a closed loop of wire you shut, just like cerrar el circuito","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Para evitar el cortocircuito, debemos cerrar el circuito antes de encender el dispositivo.","en":"To prevent a short circuit, we must close the loop before turning on the device."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mantener informado","english_text":"Keep posted","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To keep someone informed about developments.","main_translations_es":["Mantener al tanto","Mantener al corriente","Mantener informado"],"collocations":["keep me posted","keep us posted","keep them posted"],"synonyms_en":["stay updated","keep informed","let someone know"],"example_sentence":"Please keep the customers posted about the schedule changes.","example_es":"Por favor, mantén a los clientes informados sobre los cambios en el horario.","example_en":"Please keep the customers posted about the schedule changes.","mnemonic_en":"I place the post on the mantel to keep it posted.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, mantén a los clientes informados sobre los cambios en el horario.","en":"Please keep the customers posted about the schedule changes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hilo de correo","english_text":"Email thread","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A series of related email messages that share the same subject line, showing the progression of a conversation.","main_translations_es":["Cadena de correo","Conversación de correo","Hilo de email"],"collocations":["follow the email thread","reply to the email thread","email thread history","email thread view"],"synonyms_en":["mail chain","conversation thread","message chain"],"example_sentence":"I reviewed the email thread to find the information I needed.","example_es":"Revisé el hilo de correo para encontrar la información que necesitaba.","example_en":"I reviewed the email thread to find the information I needed.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a heel (hilo) stitching together a line of emails like a thread","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Revisé el hilo de correo para encontrar la información que necesitaba.","en":"I reviewed the email thread to find the information I needed."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llamada breve","english_text":"Quick call","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A brief telephone conversation.","main_translations_es":["Llamada corta","Llamada rápida","Llamada breve"],"collocations":["give me a quick call","quick call back","quick call to discuss","schedule a quick call"],"synonyms_en":["brief call","short call","fast call"],"example_sentence":"I''ll make a quick call to confirm the time.","example_es":"Haré una llamada breve para confirmar la hora.","example_en":"I''ll make a quick call to confirm the time.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a quick call as a brief llamada that darts like a hummingbird.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Haré una llamada breve para confirmar la hora.","en":"I''ll make a quick call to confirm the time."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reunión individual","english_text":"One-on-one meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A private meeting between two individuals, often a manager and an employee, conducted face‑to‑face.","main_translations_es":["Entrevista individual","Reunión cara a cara","Reunión personal"],"collocations":["schedule a one-on-one meeting","have a one-on-one meeting","one-on-one meeting agenda","one-on-one meeting follow-up"],"synonyms_en":["private meeting","individual session","personal meeting"],"example_sentence":"I have a one-on-one meeting with my supervisor tomorrow at ten.","example_es":"Tengo una reunión individual con mi supervisor mañana a las diez.","example_en":"I have a one-on-one meeting with my supervisor tomorrow at ten.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a single person saying ''uno a uno'' at a reunion, meaning a one‑on‑one meeting.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo una reunión individual con mi supervisor mañana a las diez.","en":"I have a one-on-one meeting with my supervisor tomorrow at ten."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sesión de lluvia de ideas","english_text":"Brainstorming session","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A meeting where participants generate ideas and solutions through spontaneous discussion.","main_translations_es":["Sesión creativa","Reunión de ideas","Jornada de lluvia de ideas"],"collocations":["kick off the brainstorming session","schedule a brainstorming session","productive brainstorming session","brainstorming session agenda"],"synonyms_en":["idea generation meeting","creative workshop","thought‑storming meeting"],"example_sentence":"Tomorrow we will have a brainstorming session to improve the product.","example_es":"Mañana tendremos una sesión de lluvia de ideas para mejorar el producto.","example_en":"Tomorrow we will have a brainstorming session to improve the product.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a brain catching rain, each drop a new idea in the brainstorming session.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mañana tendremos una sesión de lluvia de ideas para mejorar el producto.","en":"Tomorrow we will have a brainstorming session to improve the product."}]},{"spanish_text":"Presentación","english_text":"Presentation","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A formal introduction or display of information, such as a talk, demonstration, or visual material.","main_translations_es":["Exposición","Introducción","Charla"],"collocations":["make a presentation","give a presentation","presentation slides","presentation skills"],"synonyms_en":["demonstration","display","exhibition"],"example_sentence":"The presentation of the project was very clear.","example_es":"La presentación del proyecto fue muy clara.","example_en":"The presentation of the project was very clear.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a presenter opening a gift box labeled presentación on stage","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La presentación del proyecto fue muy clara.","en":"The presentation of the project was very clear."}]},{"spanish_text":"Diapositiva","english_text":"Slide","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A single page of a presentation, typically shown on a screen.","main_translations_es":["diapositiva","lámina","transparencia"],"collocations":["slide show","slide deck","slide transition","slide into"],"synonyms_en":["presentation page","visual aid","overhead"],"example_sentence":"The slide shows the results of the experiment.","example_es":"La diapositiva muestra los resultados del experimento.","example_en":"The slide shows the results of the experiment.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a playground slide built from a huge Diapositiva picture you can glide down.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La diapositiva muestra los resultados del experimento.","en":"The slide shows the results of the experiment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Propuesta","english_text":"Proposal","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A plan or suggestion put forward for consideration or discussion.","main_translations_es":["Propuesta","Oferta","Iniciativa"],"collocations":["proposal for","proposal to","proposal was accepted","proposal meeting"],"synonyms_en":["suggestion","offer","plan"],"example_sentence":"The committee''s proposal was approved unanimously.","example_es":"La propuesta del comité fue aprobada por unanimidad.","example_en":"The committee''s proposal was approved unanimously.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a pro chef posing a proposal on a propuesta menu.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La propuesta del comité fue aprobada por unanimidad.","en":"The committee''s proposal was approved unanimously."}]},{"spanish_text":"Factura","english_text":"Invoice","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document itemizing goods or services provided and requesting payment.","main_translations_es":["Factura","Recibo","Comprobante"],"collocations":["invoice number","invoice date","invoice amount","invoice processing"],"synonyms_en":["bill","billing statement","statement of charges"],"example_sentence":"I need you to send me the invoice before Friday.","example_es":"Necesito que me envíes la factura antes del viernes.","example_en":"I need you to send me the invoice before Friday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a loud voice shouting the invoice amount, en voz, the bill appears.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito que me envíes la factura antes del viernes.","en":"I need you to send me the invoice before Friday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Orden de compra","english_text":"Purchase order","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A document issued by a buyer to a seller specifying the items, quantities, and agreed prices for a purchase.","main_translations_es":["Pedido de compra","Orden de adquisición","Solicitud de compra"],"collocations":["issue a purchase order","purchase order number","receive a purchase order","purchase order form"],"synonyms_en":["order form","buying request","procurement order"],"example_sentence":"I need to send the purchase order to the supplier before Friday.","example_es":"Necesito enviar la orden de compra al proveedor antes del viernes.","example_en":"I need to send the purchase order to the supplier before Friday.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a purchase order as a clipboard with the word ''orden'' printed on a shopping list.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito enviar la orden de compra al proveedor antes del viernes.","en":"I need to send the purchase order to the supplier before Friday."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reembolso","english_text":"Reimbursement","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A repayment of money that has been spent or lost, typically to cover incurred expenses.","main_translations_es":["devolución","reintegro","restitución"],"collocations":["reimbursement claim","reimbursement policy","reimbursement request","reimbursement form"],"synonyms_en":["refund","compensation","repayment"],"example_sentence":"I requested the reimbursement for my purchase because the product was defective.","example_es":"Solicité el reembolso de mi compra porque el producto estaba defectuoso.","example_en":"I requested the reimbursement for my purchase because the product was defective.","mnemonic_en":"When the REEMBURSING elf hands you a REEMBOLSO, you get a reimbursement.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Solicité el reembolso de mi compra porque el producto estaba defectuoso.","en":"I requested the reimbursement for my purchase because the product was defective."}]},{"spanish_text":"Baja médica","english_text":"Sick leave","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of time when an employee is permitted to be absent from work due to illness.","main_translations_es":["incapacidad laboral","permiso médico","licencia por enfermedad"],"collocations":["take sick leave","apply for sick leave","on sick leave","sick leave policy"],"synonyms_en":["medical leave","time off for illness","health leave"],"example_sentence":"After the surgery, he needed a sick leave of two weeks.","example_es":"Después de la operación, necesitó una baja médica de dos semanas.","example_en":"After the surgery, he needed a sick leave of two weeks.","mnemonic_en":"When you feel baja, the medic says take sick leave.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Después de la operación, necesitó una baja médica de dos semanas.","en":"After the surgery, he needed a sick leave of two weeks."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vacaciones","english_text":"Annual leave","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Paid time off from work that an employee is entitled to each year.","main_translations_es":["Descanso","Periodo vacacional","Tiempo libre"],"collocations":["take annual leave","annual leave entitlement","annual leave balance","annual leave request"],"synonyms_en":["vacation","paid time off","holiday"],"example_sentence":"I am going to take my annual leave next week.","example_es":"Voy a tomar mis vacaciones la próxima semana.","example_en":"I am going to take my annual leave next week.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a yearly vacation where a giant leaf falls, reminding you of annual leave during vacaciones.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a tomar mis vacaciones la próxima semana.","en":"I am going to take my annual leave next week."}]},{"spanish_text":"Permiso de ausencia","english_text":"Leave of absence","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A period of time when someone is permitted to be away from work or school.","main_translations_es":["Licencia de ausencia","Permiso de ausencia","Licencia por ausencia"],"collocations":["take a leave of absence","apply for a leave of absence","grant a leave of absence","request a leave of absence"],"synonyms_en":["time off","sabbatical","break"],"example_sentence":"I requested a leave of absence to take care of my family.","example_es":"Solicité un permiso de ausencia para poder atender a mi familia.","example_en":"I requested a leave of absence to take care of my family.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a leaf drifting away when you get a permiso de ausencia.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Solicité un permiso de ausencia para poder atender a mi familia.","en":"I requested a leave of absence to take care of my family."}]},{"spanish_text":"Período de prueba","english_text":"Probation period","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A designated span of time during which an employee''s performance is evaluated before confirming permanent employment.","main_translations_es":["Periodo de prueba","Plazo de prueba","Tiempo de prueba"],"collocations":["serve a probation period","complete a probation period","during the probation period","after the probation period"],"synonyms_en":["trial period","probationary phase","test period"],"example_sentence":"The new employee will start his probation period next week.","example_es":"El nuevo empleado comenzará su período de prueba la próxima semana.","example_en":"The new employee will start his probation period next week.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a probation officer handing a test (prueba) for the new period.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El nuevo empleado comenzará su período de prueba la próxima semana.","en":"The new employee will start his probation period next week."}]},{"spanish_text":"Objetivo trimestral","english_text":"Quarterly goal","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A target or objective set to be achieved within a three-month period.","main_translations_es":["Meta trimestral","Objetivo de tres meses","Propósito trimestral"],"collocations":["set a quarterly goal","achieve the quarterly goal","review the quarterly goal","track quarterly goals"],"synonyms_en":["quarterly objective","three-month target","quarterly target"],"example_sentence":"Our quarterly goal is to increase sales by 10%.","example_es":"Nuestro objetivo trimestral es aumentar las ventas en un 10 %.","example_en":"Our quarterly goal is to increase sales by 10%.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a goalpost with four quarters, each showing three months—your quarterly goal.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Nuestro objetivo trimestral es aumentar las ventas en un 10 %.","en":"Our quarterly goal is to increase sales by 10%."}]},{"spanish_text":"Indicador clave de rendimiento","english_text":"Key performance indicator","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A measurable value that shows how effectively an organization is achieving its key objectives.","main_translations_es":["Indicador clave de desempeño","Indicador de rendimiento clave","Indicador principal de rendimiento"],"collocations":["track key performance indicators","key performance indicator dashboard","key performance indicator metrics","key performance indicator framework"],"synonyms_en":["KPI","performance metric","business indicator"],"example_sentence":"The company''s key performance indicator shows a 15% improvement in productivity.","example_es":"El indicador clave de rendimiento de la empresa muestra una mejora del 15% en la productividad.","example_en":"The company''s key performance indicator shows a 15% improvement in productivity.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a key (clave) unlocking a performance gauge that indicates success.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El indicador clave de rendimiento de la empresa muestra una mejora del 15% en la productividad.","en":"The company''s key performance indicator shows a 15% improvement in productivity."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resultado medible","english_text":"Measurable outcome","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A result that can be quantified or assessed.","main_translations_es":["Resultado cuantificable","Resultado evaluable","Resultado medible"],"collocations":["achieve a measurable outcome","track measurable outcomes","set measurable outcomes","measure the outcome"],"synonyms_en":["quantifiable result","trackable result","tangible result"],"example_sentence":"Measurable outcome is essential to evaluate the project''s success.","example_es":"Resultado medible es esencial para evaluar el éxito del proyecto.","example_en":"Measurable outcome is essential to evaluate the project''s success.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a measuring tape saying measurable like the Spanish medible on a result board.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Resultado medible es esencial para evaluar el éxito del proyecto.","en":"Measurable outcome is essential to evaluate the project''s success."}]},{"spanish_text":"Crecimiento profesional","english_text":"Professional growth","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of developing skills, knowledge, and experience in one''s career.","main_translations_es":["Desarrollo profesional","Avance profesional","Progresión profesional"],"collocations":["professional growth opportunities","continuous professional growth","personal and professional growth","professional growth plan"],"synonyms_en":["career advancement","skill development","career progression"],"example_sentence":"Professional growth depends on continuous training.","example_es":"El crecimiento profesional depende de la capacitación continua.","example_en":"Professional growth depends on continuous training.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a professional planting a crescent‑shaped seed that sprouts tall, showing professional growth.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El crecimiento profesional depende de la capacitación continua.","en":"Professional growth depends on continuous training."}]},{"spanish_text":"Toma de decisiones","english_text":"Decision-making","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of identifying and choosing among alternatives.","main_translations_es":["Proceso de decisión","Toma de decisiones","Decisión"],"collocations":["decision-making process","decision-making skills","decision-making authority","decision-making style"],"synonyms_en":["choice process","judgment","determination"],"example_sentence":"Decision-making is crucial in project management.","example_es":"La toma de decisiones es crucial en la gestión de proyectos.","example_en":"Decision-making is crucial in project management.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a judge pulling a huge lever labeled Decision while shouting Toma de decisiones!","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La toma de decisiones es crucial en la gestión de proyectos.","en":"Decision-making is crucial in project management."}]},{"spanish_text":"Autorizar","english_text":"Authorize","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give official permission or authority to someone to perform an action.","main_translations_es":["Permitir","Aprobar","Dar autorización"],"collocations":["authorize a transaction","authorize access","authorize a payment"],"synonyms_en":["permit","grant permission","empower"],"example_sentence":"The manager must authorize the expense before it is made.","example_es":"El gerente debe autorizar el gasto antes de que se realice.","example_en":"The manager must authorize the expense before it is made.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an author stamping his book, saying autor, and granting permission – he authorizes.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El gerente debe autorizar el gasto antes de que se realice.","en":"The manager must authorize the expense before it is made."}]},{"spanish_text":"Asignar recursos","english_text":"Allocate resources","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To distribute or assign resources to particular tasks or purposes.","main_translations_es":["Distribuir recursos","Destinar recursos","Repartir recursos"],"collocations":["allocate resources wisely","allocate resources efficiently","allocate resources to projects","allocate resources for development"],"synonyms_en":["assign resources","distribute resources","apportion resources"],"example_sentence":"The manager decided to allocate resources to the research project.","example_es":"El gerente decidió asignar recursos al proyecto de investigación.","example_en":"The manager decided to allocate resources to the research project.","mnemonic_en":"Allocate resources by assigning her a pile of tools.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El gerente decidió asignar recursos al proyecto de investigación.","en":"The manager decided to allocate resources to the research project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Mantener el rumbo","english_text":"Stay on track","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"To continue doing something in the correct direction or according to a plan.","main_translations_es":["Seguir el rumbo","Mantener la dirección","No perder el norte"],"collocations":["stay on track with your goals","stay on track during the meeting","stay on track and avoid setbacks"],"synonyms_en":["keep focused","remain on course","stay focused"],"example_sentence":"To finish the project on time, we need to stay on track and not deviate.","example_es":"Para terminar el proyecto a tiempo, debemos mantener el rumbo y no desviarnos.","example_en":"To finish the project on time, we need to stay on track and not deviate.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a train saying ''está en track'' while it keeps the rumbo.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Para terminar el proyecto a tiempo, debemos mantener el rumbo y no desviarnos.","en":"To finish the project on time, we need to stay on track and not deviate."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desviarse del plan","english_text":"Go off track","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To deviate from the intended plan or course.","main_translations_es":["Salir del plan","Apartarse del plan","Desviarse del objetivo"],"collocations":["go off track during a meeting","go off track with the project","go off track easily"],"synonyms_en":["veer off","stray","deviate"],"example_sentence":"We must not go off track.","example_es":"No debemos desviarnos del plan.","example_en":"We must not go off track.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a goat (go) sprinting off the track, abandoning the plan.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No debemos desviarnos del plan.","en":"We must not go off track."}]},{"spanish_text":"Necesita revisión","english_text":"Needs revision","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"Requires further review or correction.","main_translations_es":["Requiere revisión","Precisa revisión","Debe revisarse"],"collocations":["This document needs revision","Your essay needs revision","The policy needs revision"],"synonyms_en":["requires editing","should be revised","needs editing"],"example_sentence":"The report needs revision before sending it.","example_es":"El informe necesita revisión antes de enviarlo.","example_en":"The report needs revision before sending it.","mnemonic_en":"He needs a re‑vision, like a doctor checking his eyes again.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El informe necesita revisión antes de enviarlo.","en":"The report needs revision before sending it."}]},{"spanish_text":"Urgente","english_text":"Urgent","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"adjective","definition_en":"requiring immediate attention or action","main_translations_es":["Apremiante","Inmediato","Prioritario"],"collocations":["urgent care","urgent matter","urgent request","urgent need"],"synonyms_en":["pressing","critical","immediate"],"example_sentence":"I need you to send me the report as soon as possible; it''s urgent.","example_es":"Necesito que me envíes el informe lo antes posible, es urgente.","example_en":"I need you to send me the report as soon as possible; it''s urgent.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a fire alarm shouting ''Urgente!'' demanding immediate action.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito que me envíes el informe lo antes posible, es urgente.","en":"I need you to send me the report as soon as possible; it''s urgent."}]},{"spanish_text":"Alta prioridad","english_text":"High priority","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Something that is considered very important and should be dealt with before other matters.","main_translations_es":["Prioridad alta","Máxima prioridad","Prioridad máxima"],"collocations":["high priority task","high priority issue","high priority item","high priority list"],"synonyms_en":["top priority","urgent","critical"],"example_sentence":"This project is of high priority for the company.","example_es":"Este proyecto es de alta prioridad para la empresa.","example_en":"This project is of high priority for the company.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tall (alta) priority banner flying high above the crowd","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Este proyecto es de alta prioridad para la empresa.","en":"This project is of high priority for the company."}]},{"spanish_text":"Baja prioridad","english_text":"Low priority","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"Something that is considered less important or urgent than other items.","main_translations_es":["Prioridad baja","Prioridad reducida","Prioridad menor"],"collocations":["set to low priority","treated as low priority","low priority task","low priority issue"],"synonyms_en":["minor importance","secondary priority","less urgent"],"example_sentence":"This ticket has low priority, so we can address it later.","example_es":"Este ticket tiene baja prioridad, así que podemos atenderlo más tarde.","example_en":"This ticket has low priority, so we can address it later.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a low (baja) priority task as a tiny flag at the bottom of the list.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Este ticket tiene baja prioridad, así que podemos atenderlo más tarde.","en":"This ticket has low priority, so we can address it later."}]},{"spanish_text":"Punto de contacto","english_text":"Point of contact","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or place that serves as the primary source of communication or information.","main_translations_es":["Persona de contacto","Contacto principal","Referente"],"collocations":["primary point of contact","main point of contact","single point of contact","designated point of contact"],"synonyms_en":["contact person","liaison","go-to person"],"example_sentence":"For any questions, please contact Maria, who will be your point of contact.","example_es":"Para cualquier duda, por favor contacte a María, quien será su punto de contacto.","example_en":"For any questions, please contact Maria, who will be your point of contact.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dot (punto) on a map marking the point of contact.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Para cualquier duda, por favor contacte a María, quien será su punto de contacto.","en":"For any questions, please contact Maria, who will be your point of contact."}]},{"spanish_text":"Compartir pantalla","english_text":"Share the screen","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To display one''s computer screen to others, typically during a video call or presentation.","main_translations_es":["Compartir la pantalla","Mostrar la pantalla","Proyección de pantalla"],"collocations":["share the screen with the team","share the screen during the meeting","share the screen on Zoom","share the screen for a presentation"],"synonyms_en":["display the screen","project the screen","show the screen"],"example_sentence":"I need to share the screen during the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito compartir pantalla durante la reunión.","example_en":"I need to share the screen during the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"When you COMPARTIR pizza, you SHARE the SCREEN.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito compartir pantalla durante la reunión.","en":"I need to share the screen during the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Silenciar el micrófono","english_text":"Mute the microphone","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To turn off or lower the microphone''s sound so it cannot be heard.","main_translations_es":["Desactivar el micrófono","Apagar el micrófono","Poner en silencio el micrófono"],"collocations":["Please mute the microphone","Remember to mute the microphone","He forgot to mute the microphone"],"synonyms_en":["silence the mic","turn off the mic","disable the microphone"],"example_sentence":"You can mute the microphone if you don''t want to be heard.","example_es":"Puedes silenciar el micrófono si no quieres que te escuchen.","example_en":"You can mute the microphone if you don''t want to be heard.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a mute button pressing the mic, turning the micrófono into complete silence","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Puedes silenciar el micrófono si no quieres que te escuchen.","en":"You can mute the microphone if you don''t want to be heard."}]},{"spanish_text":"Conectarse a la reunión","english_text":"Join the meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To connect to or participate in a scheduled meeting.","main_translations_es":["Unirse a la reunión","Entrar a la reunión","Conectar a la reunión"],"collocations":["join the meeting on time","join the meeting via Zoom","join the meeting early","join the meeting tomorrow"],"synonyms_en":["attend the meeting","participate in the meeting","enter the meeting"],"example_sentence":"I need to join the meeting at ten in the morning.","example_es":"Necesito conectarme a la reunión a las diez de la mañana.","example_en":"I need to join the meeting at ten in the morning.","mnemonic_en":"Juan joins the meeting, just like connecting a plug to a socket.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito conectarme a la reunión a las diez de la mañana.","en":"I need to join the meeting at ten in the morning."}]},{"spanish_text":"Abandonar la reunión","english_text":"Leave the meeting","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To exit or depart from a meeting.","main_translations_es":["Salir de la reunión","Irse de la reunión","Dejar la reunión"],"collocations":["to leave the meeting early","to leave the meeting abruptly","to leave the meeting without notice"],"synonyms_en":["exit the meeting","walk out","depart the meeting"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to leave the meeting because it''s getting late.","example_es":"Voy a abandonar la reunión porque ya es tarde.","example_en":"I''m going to leave the meeting because it''s getting late.","mnemonic_en":"A band on a reunion walks out, leaving the meeting.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a abandonar la reunión porque ya es tarde.","en":"I''m going to leave the meeting because it''s getting late."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tomar nota","english_text":"Take notes","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To write down information for later reference.","main_translations_es":["Anotar","Hacer anotaciones","Apuntar"],"collocations":["take notes during the lecture","take notes on the meeting","take notes for later"],"synonyms_en":["jot down","make a note","record"],"example_sentence":"During the class, you should take notes of everything the teacher says.","example_es":"Durante la clase, debes tomar nota de todo lo que el profesor dice.","example_en":"During the class, you should take notes of everything the teacher says.","mnemonic_en":"Take notes as you tomar a note from a bright red tomato.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Durante la clase, debes tomar nota de todo lo que el profesor dice.","en":"During the class, you should take notes of everything the teacher says."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hacer una demostración","english_text":"Give a demo","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To present a demonstration of something, typically showing how it works.","main_translations_es":["Realizar una demostración","Mostrar una demo","Presentar una demostración"],"collocations":["give a demo of the product","give a demo to the client","give a demo during the meeting"],"synonyms_en":["show a demo","present a demo","demonstrate"],"example_sentence":"I''m going to give a demo of the new software to the team.","example_es":"Voy a hacer una demostración del nuevo software para el equipo.","example_en":"I''m going to give a demo of the new software to the team.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself handing a demo DVD to a crowd, showing exactly what a demostración means.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a hacer una demostración del nuevo software para el equipo.","en":"I''m going to give a demo of the new software to the team."}]},{"spanish_text":"Próximos pasos","english_text":"Next steps","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A set of actions or tasks that should be taken after the current point.","main_translations_es":["Pasos siguientes","Siguientes pasos","Próximas acciones"],"collocations":["next steps in the process","next steps for implementation","next steps after the meeting","next steps to take"],"synonyms_en":["following steps","future actions","subsequent steps"],"example_sentence":"The next steps are to review the report and present the results.","example_es":"Los próximos pasos son revisar el informe y presentar los resultados.","example_en":"The next steps are to review the report and present the results.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a NEXT sign pointing to a staircase of STEPS labeled PROXIMO, showing the upcoming steps.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Los próximos pasos son revisar el informe y presentar los resultados.","en":"The next steps are to review the report and present the results."}]},{"spanish_text":"Prórroga","english_text":"Extension","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A continuation or prolongation of something, especially a period of time.","main_translations_es":["prórroga","aplazamiento","extensión"],"collocations":["extension cord","extension deadline","extension of a loan","extension service"],"synonyms_en":["prolongation","expansion","continuation"],"example_sentence":"The referee granted a five‑minute extension to the game.","example_es":"El árbitro concedió una prórroga de cinco minutos al partido.","example_en":"The referee granted a five‑minute extension to the game.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a pro rope being pulled longer, turning into an extension.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El árbitro concedió una prórroga de cinco minutos al partido.","en":"The referee granted a five‑minute extension to the game."}]},{"spanish_text":"Solución alternativa","english_text":"Workaround","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A method for overcoming a problem or limitation in a system.","main_translations_es":["Alternativa","Solución provisional","Método alternativo"],"collocations":["find a workaround","temporary workaround","implement a workaround","workaround solution"],"synonyms_en":["alternative solution","temporary fix","stopgap"],"example_sentence":"We implemented a workaround while the team fixes the bug.","example_es":"Implementamos una solución alternativa mientras el equipo corrige el error.","example_en":"We implemented a workaround while the team fixes the bug.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a worker circling a wall, using a solución alternativa to get the job done.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Implementamos una solución alternativa mientras el equipo corrige el error.","en":"We implemented a workaround while the team fixes the bug."}]},{"spanish_text":"Bloqueador","english_text":"Blocker","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A person or thing that prevents progress or blocks something.","main_translations_es":["Obstáculo","Inhibidor","Bloqueador"],"collocations":["ad blocker","traffic blocker","blocker issue","blocker task"],"synonyms_en":["obstacle","impediment","hindrance"],"example_sentence":"He installed an ad blocker to avoid intrusive ads.","example_es":"Instaló un bloqueador de anuncios para evitar la publicidad intrusiva.","example_en":"He installed an ad blocker to avoid intrusive ads.","mnemonic_en":"A blocker stops traffic by dropping a giant block, just like a Spanish bloqueador.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Instaló un bloqueador de anuncios para evitar la publicidad intrusiva.","en":"He installed an ad blocker to avoid intrusive ads."}]},{"spanish_text":"Disponibilidad inmediata","english_text":"Immediate availability","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"The state of being ready for use right away.","main_translations_es":["Disponibilidad al instante","Disponibilidad sin demora","Disponibilidad inmediata"],"collocations":["subject to immediate availability","with immediate availability","immediate availability of"],"synonyms_en":["ready now","instant access","prompt availability"],"example_sentence":"I have immediate availability to start working.","example_es":"Tengo disponibilidad inmediata para comenzar a trabajar.","example_en":"I have immediate availability to start working.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a flashing billboard shouting Immediate availability, echoing the Spanish word ''inmediata'' for instant.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Tengo disponibilidad inmediata para comenzar a trabajar.","en":"I have immediate availability to start working."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entorno de pruebas","english_text":"Test environment","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A setting or system used to conduct testing of software or processes.","main_translations_es":["Ambiente de pruebas","Entorno de test","Ambiente de test"],"collocations":["set up a test environment","test environment configuration","test environment variables","test environment setup"],"synonyms_en":["testing environment","sandbox","staging environment"],"example_sentence":"The team set up the test environment before releasing the new version.","example_es":"El equipo configuró el entorno de pruebas antes de lanzar la nueva versión.","example_en":"The team set up the test environment before releasing the new version.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a lab where every test has its own entorno sign, a test environment.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El equipo configuró el entorno de pruebas antes de lanzar la nueva versión.","en":"The team set up the test environment before releasing the new version."}]},{"spanish_text":"Entorno de producción","english_text":"Production environment","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The setting where software or a system is operated for real users, as opposed to testing or development.","main_translations_es":["Entorno de producción","Ambiente de producción","Entorno productivo"],"collocations":["deploy to production environment","production environment setup","production environment monitoring"],"synonyms_en":["live environment","operational setting","deployment environment"],"example_sentence":"The software was deployed to the production environment after testing.","example_es":"El software se desplegó en el entorno de producción después de las pruebas.","example_en":"The software was deployed to the production environment after testing.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a factory (producción) inside a garden (entorno) to recall Production environment.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El software se desplegó en el entorno de producción después de las pruebas.","en":"The software was deployed to the production environment after testing."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cadena de aprobación","english_text":"Approval chain","section_name":"Workplace Communication","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A sequence of individuals or steps required to give approval for a decision or document.","main_translations_es":["cadena de autorización","flujo de aprobación","cadena de validación"],"collocations":["establish an approval chain","approval chain process","manage the approval chain","approval chain hierarchy"],"synonyms_en":["authorization sequence","sign‑off chain","approval workflow"],"example_sentence":"For the project, we follow an approval chain before launching the product.","example_es":"Para el proyecto, seguimos una cadena de aprobación antes de lanzar el producto.","example_en":"For the project, we follow an approval chain before launching the product.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a chain of stamps giving approval on a document.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Para el proyecto, seguimos una cadena de aprobación antes de lanzar el producto.","en":"For the project, we follow an approval chain before launching the product."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- english-academic-english (107 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'Academic English', description = 'Upper-intermediate and advanced academic vocabulary for essays, reports, presentations, and formal discussion.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'english-academic-english';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-academic-english') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Hipótesis","english_text":"Hypothesis","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A proposed explanation for a phenomenon that can be tested through observation or experiment.","main_translations_es":["Suposición","Conjetura","Teoría"],"collocations":["test the hypothesis","form a hypothesis","null hypothesis","working hypothesis"],"synonyms_en":["theory","supposition","conjecture"],"example_sentence":"My hypothesis is that the rise in temperature affects bird migration.","example_es":"Mi hipótesis es que el aumento de la temperatura afecta la migración de las aves.","example_en":"My hypothesis is that the rise in temperature affects bird migration.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hippo presenting a thesis on a lab table, the hippo''s hypothesis.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mi hipótesis es que el aumento de la temperatura afecta la migración de las aves.","en":"My hypothesis is that the rise in temperature affects bird migration."}]},{"spanish_text":"Variable","english_text":"Variable","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A symbol or quantity that can change or take on different values.","main_translations_es":["Variable","Cambiante","Inestable"],"collocations":["variable cost","variable rate","variable speed","variable temperature"],"synonyms_en":[],"example_sentence":"The temperature is variable in this region.","example_es":"La temperatura es variable en esta región.","example_en":"The temperature is variable in this region.","mnemonic_en":null,"cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La temperatura es variable en esta región.","en":"The temperature is variable in this region."}]},{"spanish_text":"Metodología","english_text":"Methodology","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A systematic set of methods and principles used in a particular field of study or practice.","main_translations_es":["Método","Procedimiento","Enfoque"],"collocations":["research methodology","methodology section","methodology of the study"],"synonyms_en":["approach","technique","procedure"],"example_sentence":"The methodology the researcher used ensured reliable results.","example_es":"La metodología que utilizó el investigador garantizó resultados fiables.","example_en":"The methodology the researcher used ensured reliable results.","mnemonic_en":"Methodology sounds like Met a dog O'' Lia, a methodical dog named Lia.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La metodología que utilizó el investigador garantizó resultados fiables.","en":"The methodology the researcher used ensured reliable results."}]},{"spanish_text":"Revisión bibliográfica","english_text":"Literature review","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A comprehensive summary and analysis of existing research and publications on a particular topic.","main_translations_es":["Revisión de la literatura","Estado del arte","Análisis bibliográfico"],"collocations":["conduct a literature review","comprehensive literature review","literature review section","literature review methodology"],"synonyms_en":["bibliographic survey","scholarly overview","research synthesis"],"example_sentence":"For my thesis, I conducted an exhaustive literature review of recent studies.","example_es":"Para mi tesis, realicé una revisión bibliográfica exhaustiva de los estudios recientes.","example_en":"For my thesis, I conducted an exhaustive literature review of recent studies.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a librarian revising a mountain of books, doing a literature review.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Para mi tesis, realicé una revisión bibliográfica exhaustiva de los estudios recientes.","en":"For my thesis, I conducted an exhaustive literature review of recent studies."}]},{"spanish_text":"Revisión por pares","english_text":"Peer review","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun"