icture a judge holding a scale saying eval uate while checking a Spanish evaluar exam.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El comité debe evaluar los resultados del experimento antes de publicar el informe.","en":"The committee must evaluate the experiment''s results before publishing the report."}]},{"spanish_text":"Criticar","english_text":"Critique","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A detailed analysis and assessment of something, especially a work of art, literature, or performance.","main_translations_es":["Reprochar","Censurar","Juzgar"],"collocations":["constructive critique","critical review","peer critique","artistic critique"],"synonyms_en":["review","evaluate","assess"],"example_sentence":"The critic decided to critique the new movie for its lack of originality.","example_es":"El crítico decidió criticar la nueva película por su falta de originalidad.","example_en":"The critic decided to critique the new movie for its lack of originality.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a critic sipping tea, shouting critique as he points to a sign that reads criticar.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El crítico decidió criticar la nueva película por su falta de originalidad.","en":"The critic decided to critique the new movie for its lack of originality."}]},{"spanish_text":"Argumentar","english_text":"Argue","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give reasons for or against something, often in a discussion or debate.","main_translations_es":["Discutir","Razonar","Debatir"],"collocations":["argue a point","argue with","argue about","argue that"],"synonyms_en":["debate","dispute","contend"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to know how to argue your ideas during the debate.","example_es":"Es importante saber argumentar tus ideas durante el debate.","example_en":"It''s important to know how to argue your ideas during the debate.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a courtroom where the law