 improve it.","main_translations_es":["Parafrasear","Reexpresar","Reformular"],"collocations":["rephrase the sentence","rephrase your question","rephrase for clarity"],"synonyms_en":["paraphrase","put differently","restated"],"example_sentence":"Could you rephrase the question to make it clearer?","example_es":"¿Podrías reformular la pregunta para que sea más clara?","example_en":"Could you rephrase the question to make it clearer?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a writer re-phrasing a sentence, like a sculptor reformulating a clay statue.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"¿Podrías reformular la pregunta para que sea más clara?","en":"Could you rephrase the question to make it clearer?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Afirmar","english_text":"Claim","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To assert that something is true, typically without providing proof.","main_translations_es":["Declarar","Aseverar","Sostener"],"collocations":["make a claim","file a claim","claim responsibility","claim that"],"synonyms_en":["assert","maintain","allege"],"example_sentence":"The witness claimed that he saw the suspect at the scene.","example_es":"El testigo afirmó que vio al sospechoso en la escena.","example_en":"The witness claimed that he saw the suspect at the scene.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a clay seal stamped with the Spanish word afirmar as you make a claim.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El testigo afirmó que vio al sospechoso en la escena.","en":"The witness claimed that he saw the suspect at the scene."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sugerir","english_text":"Suggest","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To propose an idea, plan, or course of action for consideration.","main_translations_es":["proponer","recomendar","aconsejar"],"collocations":["suggest a solution","suggest that","suggest an idea"],"synonyms_en":["propose","recommend","advise"],"example_sentence":"Could you suggest a good restaurant for dinner?","example_es":"¿Podrías sugerir un buen restaurante para cenar?","example_en":"Could you suggest a good restaurant for dinner?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a sugar jar that whispers suggestions.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"¿Podrías sugerir un buen restaurante para cenar?","en":"Could you suggest a good restaurant for dinner?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Señalar","english_text":"Indicate","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To point out or show something, making it known.","main_translations_es":["indicar","apuntar","marcar"],"collocations":["indicate that","indicate a preference","indicate the direction","indicate the results"],"synonyms_en":["show","point out","signal"],"example_sentence":"Please indicate the correct answer on the exam.","example_es":"Por favor, señale la respuesta correcta en el examen.","example_en":"Please indicate the correct answer on the exam.","mnemonic_en":"I indicate by waving a bright señal like a signal flag","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, señale la respuesta correcta en el examen.","en":"Please indicate the correct answer on the exam."}]},{"spanish_text":"Destacar","english_text":"Highlight","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To emphasize or make something stand out.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Sobresalir","Enfatizar"],"collocations":["highlight the main points","highlight a text","highlight a feature","highlight the issue"],"synonyms_en":["emphasize","underscore","spotlight"],"example_sentence":"I want to highlight the team''s achievements in the presentation.","example_es":"Quiero destacar los logros del equipo en la presentación.","example_en":"I want to highlight the team''s achievements in the presentation.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a high light shining on a star, making it destacar.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Quiero destacar los logros del equipo en la presentación.","en":"I want to highlight the team''s achievements in the presentation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Enfatizar","english_text":"Emphasize","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give special importance or attention to something.","main_translations_es":["Resaltar","Destacar","Poner énfasis"],"collocations":["emphasize the importance","emphasize the need","emphasize that","emphasize the point"],"synonyms_en":["highlight","stress","underscore"],"example_sentence":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality.","example_es":"El profesor quiso enfatizar la importancia de la puntualidad.","example_en":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a teacher in a theater shouting ''ENFA'' to emphasize the lesson.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El profesor quiso enfatizar la importancia de la puntualidad.","en":"The teacher wanted to emphasize the importance of punctuality."}]},{"spanish_text":"En consecuencia","english_text":"Consequently","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"As a result; therefore.","main_translations_es":["Por lo tanto","Así que","De ese modo"],"collocations":["Consequently, the project was delayed.","Consequently, we decided to cancel the event.","Consequently, the results were inconclusive.","Consequently, sales increased dramatically."],"synonyms_en":["as a result","therefore","hence"],"example_sentence":"Consequently, the project was cancelled.","example_es":"En consecuencia, el proyecto fue cancelado.","example_en":"Consequently, the project was cancelled.","mnemonic_en":"Picture dominoes, each consequence lands in (en) order—consequently.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En consecuencia, el proyecto fue cancelado.","en":"Consequently, the project was cancelled."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sin embargo","english_text":"However","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"It introduces a contrast or exception to what has just been said.","main_translations_es":["no obstante","aun así","con todo"],"collocations":["however you like","however you want","however possible"],"synonyms_en":["Nevertheless","Nonetheless","But"],"example_sentence":"I wanted to go to the park; however, it started to rain.","example_es":"Quería ir al parque, sin embargo empezó a llover.","example_en":"I wanted to go to the park; however, it started to rain.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a hay you VERify, though it''s a sin embargo moment.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Quería ir al parque, sin embargo empezó a llover.","en":"I wanted to go to the park; however, it started to rain."}]},{"spanish_text":"Además","english_text":"Furthermore","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In addition; used to introduce an additional point.","main_translations_es":["También","Encima","Aparte"],"collocations":["Furthermore, ...","Furthermore, the study shows","Furthermore, we find","Furthermore, it is important"],"synonyms_en":["also","moreover","in addition"],"example_sentence":"Furthermore, the project will be completed before the deadline.","example_es":"Además, el proyecto será completado antes de la fecha límite.","example_en":"Furthermore, the project will be completed before the deadline.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine adding more items to a list, because \"además\" sounds like \"add more\" meaning furthermore.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Además, el proyecto será completado antes de la fecha límite.","en":"Furthermore, the project will be completed before the deadline."}]},{"spanish_text":"Por el contrario","english_text":"Conversely","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a contrasting or opposite manner, used to introduce a statement that reverses the previous one.","main_translations_es":["En cambio","Al contrario","Por otro lado"],"collocations":["Conversely, the opposite is true","Conversely, if you increase the temperature, the pressure drops","Conversely, the results suggest a different trend"],"synonyms_en":["On the other hand","In contrast","Oppositely"],"example_sentence":"He doesn''t like coffee; conversely, he prefers tea.","example_es":"No le gusta el café; por el contrario, prefiere el té.","example_en":"He doesn''t like coffee; conversely, he prefers tea.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a courtroom where the lawyer flips the script, shouting Por el contrario, and you answer Conversely like a mirror","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No le gusta el café; por el contrario, prefiere el té.","en":"He doesn''t like coffee; conversely, he prefers tea."}]},{"spanish_text":"Del mismo modo","english_text":"Similarly","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In a similar way; in the same manner.","main_translations_es":["Igualmente","De la misma forma","De igual manera"],"collocations":["Similarly, ...","Similarly to","Similarly, the results show","Similarly, we can see"],"synonyms_en":["Likewise","In the same way","In a similar fashion"],"example_sentence":"Similarly, children must respect the rules.","example_es":"Del mismo modo, los niños deben respetar las reglas.","example_en":"Similarly, children must respect the rules.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine building a SAME LEGO set in the SAME way, just like del mismo modo","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Del mismo modo, los niños deben respetar las reglas.","en":"Similarly, children must respect the rules."}]},{"spanish_text":"No obstante","english_text":"Nonetheless","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"It means ''in spite of that'' or ''nevertheless''.","main_translations_es":["Sin embargo","A pesar de eso","Con todo"],"collocations":["Nonetheless, ...","Nonetheless, we must","Nonetheless, it is"],"synonyms_en":["Nevertheless","still","even so"],"example_sentence":"Nonetheless, he decided to continue with the project.","example_es":"No obstante, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","example_en":"Nonetheless, he decided to continue with the project.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a stubborn no obstinate man shouting Nonetheless to push forward","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No obstante, decidió continuar con el proyecto.","en":"Nonetheless, he decided to continue with the project."}]},{"spanish_text":"Por lo tanto","english_text":"Therefore","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"As a result; for that reason.","main_translations_es":["Así que","Por consiguiente","En consecuencia"],"collocations":["therefore, we conclude","therefore, it follows","therefore, the results show"],"synonyms_en":["Consequently","Thus","Hence"],"example_sentence":"He studied a lot for the exam; therefore, he got a good grade.","example_es":"Estudió mucho para el examen; por lo tanto, obtuvo una buena nota.","example_en":"He studied a lot for the exam; therefore, he got a good grade.","mnemonic_en":"I pour low tango sauce, therefore the dance stops.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Estudió mucho para el examen; por lo tanto, obtuvo una buena nota.","en":"He studied a lot for the exam; therefore, he got a good grade."}]},{"spanish_text":"En cambio","english_text":"In contrast","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a statement that differs from or opposes what has just been mentioned.","main_translations_es":["Por el contrario","A diferencia de","En contraste"],"collocations":["in contrast to","in contrast with","in contrast, however"],"synonyms_en":["by contrast","on the other hand","conversely"],"example_sentence":"I prefer tea; she, in contrast, prefers coffee.","example_es":"Yo prefiero el té; ella, en cambio, prefiere el café.","example_en":"I prefer tea; she, in contrast, prefers coffee.","mnemonic_en":"In contrast, picture a light switch saying ''en cambio'' as it flips to the opposite side.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Yo prefiero el té; ella, en cambio, prefiere el café.","en":"I prefer tea; she, in contrast, prefers coffee."}]},{"spanish_text":"Por ejemplo","english_text":"For instance","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"phrase","definition_en":"Used to introduce an example.","main_translations_es":["Por ejemplo","A modo de ejemplo","Ejemplo"],"collocations":["for instance, ...","for instance, consider","for instance, such as"],"synonyms_en":["e.g.","as an example","to illustrate"],"example_sentence":"For instance, if you study every day, you will improve your grades.","example_es":"Por ejemplo, si estudias todos los días, mejorarás tus notas.","example_en":"For instance, if you study every day, you will improve your grades.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a poor man holding a four as an example.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Por ejemplo, si estudias todos los días, mejorarás tus notas.","en":"For instance, if you study every day, you will improve your grades."}]},{"spanish_text":"Es decir","english_text":"That is to say","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a clarification or restatement of something previously said.","main_translations_es":["O sea","En otras palabras","Dicho de otro modo"],"collocations":["that is to say, the project is delayed","that is to say, in other words","that is to say, we need to act"],"synonyms_en":["in other words","i.e.","to put it another way"],"example_sentence":"I didn''t like the movie; that is to say, I found it boring.","example_es":"No me gustó la película; es decir, la encontré aburrida.","example_en":"I didn''t like the movie; that is to say, I found it boring.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a teacher holding a sign that reads ES and saying, ''That is to say''.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No me gustó la película; es decir, la encontré aburrida.","en":"I didn''t like the movie; that is to say, I found it boring."}]},{"spanish_text":"A grandes rasgos","english_text":"Broadly speaking","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce a general summary or overview of a topic.","main_translations_es":["En términos generales","En líneas generales","De manera general"],"collocations":["Broadly speaking, the results are positive.","Broadly speaking, we can conclude that...","Broadly speaking, the plan works.","Broadly speaking, it''s a good approach."],"synonyms_en":["generally","in general","overall"],"example_sentence":"Broadly speaking, the project involves developing a mobile app for task management.","example_es":"A grandes rasgos, el proyecto consiste en desarrollar una aplicación móvil para la gestión de tareas.","example_en":"Broadly speaking, the project involves developing a mobile app for task management.","mnemonic_en":"A broad map with a raspy goose speaking about big features.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"A grandes rasgos, el proyecto consiste en desarrollar una aplicación móvil para la gestión de tareas.","en":"Broadly speaking, the project involves developing a mobile app for task management."}]},{"spanish_text":"En primer lugar","english_text":"In the first place","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"Used to introduce the first reason or point in a discussion.","main_translations_es":["Primero","En primer término","Ante todo"],"collocations":["Why did you do that in the first place?","In the first place, we should consider the costs.","It wasn''t necessary in the first place."],"synonyms_en":["first of all","to begin with","initially"],"example_sentence":"In the first place, we must review the documents.","example_es":"En primer lugar, debemos revisar los documentos.","example_en":"In the first place, we must review the documents.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a prime (primer) athlete stepping into the first place on the podium.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En primer lugar, debemos revisar los documentos.","en":"In the first place, we must review the documents."}]},{"spanish_text":"En segundo lugar","english_text":"Secondly","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"Used to introduce the second item in a list or sequence of points.","main_translations_es":["En segundo término","En segundo punto","En segundo orden"],"collocations":["Firstly, ... Secondly, ...","Secondly, we need to...","Secondly, the results show..."],"synonyms_en":["In addition","Moreover","Also"],"example_sentence":"Secondly, we must consider the budget.","example_es":"En segundo lugar, debemos considerar el presupuesto.","example_en":"Secondly, we must consider the budget.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a runner in second place yelling ''Secondly!'' as if saying Spanish ''segundo''.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En segundo lugar, debemos considerar el presupuesto.","en":"Secondly, we must consider the budget."}]},{"spanish_text":"En términos generales","english_text":"In general terms","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something applies broadly or in a general sense.","main_translations_es":["En general","En términos generales","De forma general"],"collocations":["in general terms, ...","to put it in general terms","in general terms, the result is","in general terms, we can say"],"synonyms_en":["generally","overall","broadly speaking"],"example_sentence":"In general terms, the project will be completed by the end of the year.","example_es":"En términos generales, el proyecto será completado a finales de año.","example_en":"In general terms, the project will be completed by the end of the year.","mnemonic_en":"A general signs a contract titled In general terms on a big board.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En términos generales, el proyecto será completado a finales de año.","en":"In general terms, the project will be completed by the end of the year."}]},{"spanish_text":"En última instancia","english_text":"Ultimately","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"adverb","definition_en":"In the end, after all other considerations or events have taken place.","main_translations_es":["Al fin y al cabo","En definitiva","A fin de cuentas"],"collocations":["Ultimately, it comes down to","Ultimately, the decision rests with","Ultimately, we need to","Ultimately, the outcome depends on"],"synonyms_en":["in the end","finally","eventually"],"example_sentence":"Ultimately, we will decide whether the project will go ahead.","example_es":"En última instancia, decidiremos si el proyecto sigue adelante.","example_en":"Ultimately, we will decide whether the project will go ahead.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine the last ''última'' chapter flipping open, revealing the ultimate outcome.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En última instancia, decidiremos si el proyecto sigue adelante.","en":"Ultimately, we will decide whether the project will go ahead."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cabe señalar que","english_text":"It should be noted that","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a statement that the speaker wants to emphasize or draw attention to.","main_translations_es":["Cabe destacar que","Hay que señalar que","Es importante señalar que"],"collocations":["It should be noted that...","It should be noted that the data...","It should be noted that this is..."],"synonyms_en":["It is worth noting that","Note that","One should note that"],"example_sentence":"It should be noted that the report will be presented tomorrow.","example_es":"Cabe señalar que el informe será presentado mañana.","example_en":"It should be noted that the report will be presented tomorrow.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a note on a signal flag, reminding you it should be noted that.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Cabe señalar que el informe será presentado mañana.","en":"It should be noted that the report will be presented tomorrow."}]},{"spanish_text":"Se puede sostener que","english_text":"It can be argued that","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a statement that may be debated or supported with reasoning.","main_translations_es":["Se puede afirmar que","Se podría sostener que","Se puede decir que"],"collocations":["It can be argued that the data supports this","It can be argued that this is the case","It can be argued that there are alternatives","It can be argued that the policy is ineffective"],"synonyms_en":["One could argue that","It may be claimed that","It is debatable that"],"example_sentence":"It can be argued that the economy will grow next year.","example_es":"Se puede sostener que la economía crecerá el próximo año.","example_en":"It can be argued that the economy will grow next year.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a sturdy ''sostener'' shelf holding a debate sign, reminding you ''It can be argued that''.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Se puede sostener que la economía crecerá el próximo año.","en":"It can be argued that the economy will grow next year."}]},{"spanish_text":"Parece evidente que","english_text":"It seems evident that","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to indicate that something appears clear or obvious.","main_translations_es":["Resulta evidente que","Es evidente que","Se ve evidente que"],"collocations":["It seems evident that...","It seems evident that the data show...","It seems evident that we need to act","It seems evident that this is the case"],"synonyms_en":["It appears clear that","It looks obvious that","It seems obvious that"],"example_sentence":"It seems evident that the evidence supports his theory.","example_es":"Parece evidente que la evidencia apoya su teoría.","example_en":"It seems evident that the evidence supports his theory.","mnemonic_en":"It seems evident that a pair of evidence makes it obvious.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Parece evidente que la evidencia apoya su teoría.","en":"It seems evident that the evidence supports his theory."}]},{"spanish_text":"Está ampliamente aceptado","english_text":"It is widely accepted","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A statement indicating that something is generally approved or recognized by many people.","main_translations_es":["Se acepta ampliamente","Es de aceptación general","Goza de amplio reconocimiento"],"collocations":["widely accepted practice","widely accepted theory","widely accepted standard"],"synonyms_en":["It is generally accepted","It is commonly accepted","It is broadly accepted"],"example_sentence":"It is widely accepted that recycling helps the environment.","example_es":"Está ampliamente aceptado que el reciclaje ayuda al medio ambiente.","example_en":"It is widely accepted that recycling helps the environment.","mnemonic_en":"See a wide (wide) hallway where everyone nods, saying ''ampliamente aceptado''.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Está ampliamente aceptado que el reciclaje ayuda al medio ambiente.","en":"It is widely accepted that recycling helps the environment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Permanecer incierto","english_text":"Remain uncertain","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To stay in a state of uncertainty.","main_translations_es":["Seguir sin estar claro","Quedarse en duda","Mantenerse incierto"],"collocations":["remain uncertain about","remain uncertain whether","remain uncertain at this point"],"synonyms_en":["be unsure","stay unclear","remain doubtful"],"example_sentence":"The outcome of the trial will remain uncertain.","example_es":"El resultado del juicio seguirá permaneciendo incierto.","example_en":"The outcome of the trial will remain uncertain.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a RE-MAINING sign that reads IN-CERTAIN, swaying like an unsure flag.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El resultado del juicio seguirá permaneciendo incierto.","en":"The outcome of the trial will remain uncertain."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tener en cuenta","english_text":"Take into consideration","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To consider something carefully when making a decision.","main_translations_es":["Considerar","Tener presente","Tomar en cuenta"],"collocations":["take into consideration the costs","take into consideration the risks","take into consideration the feedback","take into consideration the circumstances"],"synonyms_en":["consider","keep in mind","take into account"],"example_sentence":"You should take into consideration the doctor''s recommendations before starting the treatment.","example_es":"Debes tener en cuenta las recomendaciones del médico antes de iniciar el tratamiento.","example_en":"You should take into consideration the doctor''s recommendations before starting the treatment.","mnemonic_en":"Take a ten, then consider it carefully.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Debes tener en cuenta las recomendaciones del médico antes de iniciar el tratamiento.","en":"You should take into consideration the doctor''s recommendations before starting the treatment."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sacar una conclusión","english_text":"Draw a conclusion","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to form a judgment or inference based on evidence","main_translations_es":["Llegar a una conclusión","Concluir","Formular una conclusión"],"collocations":["draw a conclusion from the data","draw a conclusion about","draw a conclusion based on the evidence","draw a conclusion that"],"synonyms_en":["reach a conclusion","make a deduction","infer"],"example_sentence":"After reviewing the data, we can draw a clear conclusion.","example_es":"Después de revisar los datos, podemos sacar una conclusión clara.","example_en":"After reviewing the data, we can draw a clear conclusion.","mnemonic_en":"Picture yourself drawing a final line that pulls out the answer, like you ''sacar'' a conclusion","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Después de revisar los datos, podemos sacar una conclusión clara.","en":"After reviewing the data, we can draw a clear conclusion."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llegar a una conclusión","english_text":"Reach a conclusion","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to arrive at a decision or judgment after considering the evidence","main_translations_es":["Sacar una conclusión","Concluir","Llegar a una decisión"],"collocations":["reach a conclusion about","reach a conclusion after","reach a conclusion that","reach a conclusion quickly"],"synonyms_en":["draw a conclusion","come to a conclusion","conclude"],"example_sentence":"After analyzing the data, we reached a conclusion.","example_es":"Después de analizar los datos, llegamos a una conclusión.","example_en":"After analyzing the data, we reached a conclusion.","mnemonic_en":"I reach, I ''llegar'' at the conclusion podium.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Después de analizar los datos, llegamos a una conclusión.","en":"After analyzing the data, we reached a conclusion."}]},{"spanish_text":"A modo de conclusión","english_text":"By way of conclusion","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"expression","definition_en":"A phrase used to introduce a final statement or summary.","main_translations_es":["En conclusión","Para concluir","En síntesis"],"collocations":["By way of conclusion, we can see that...","By way of conclusion, the study suggests...","By way of conclusion, it is evident that...","By way of conclusion, I recommend..."],"synonyms_en":["In conclusion","To sum up","In summary"],"example_sentence":"By way of conclusion, we can say that the project was a success.","example_es":"A modo de conclusión, podemos decir que el proyecto fue un éxito.","example_en":"By way of conclusion, we can say that the project was a success.","mnemonic_en":"Press the mode button to end, by way of conclusion.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"A modo de conclusión, podemos decir que el proyecto fue un éxito.","en":"By way of conclusion, we can say that the project was a success."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tesis","english_text":"Thesis","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A written document presenting the author''s research and findings, typically submitted for an academic degree.","main_translations_es":["Trabajo de investigación","Disertación","Monografía"],"collocations":["thesis statement","doctoral thesis","master''s thesis","thesis defense"],"synonyms_en":["dissertation","research paper","treatise"],"example_sentence":"I am working on my doctoral thesis.","example_es":"Estoy trabajando en mi tesis de doctorado.","example_en":"I am working on my doctoral thesis.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a student holding a thick test paper that says teh-sis as the thesis","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Estoy trabajando en mi tesis de doctorado.","en":"I am working on my doctoral thesis."}]},{"spanish_text":"Antítesis","english_text":"Counterargument","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A statement or set of reasons presented in opposition to another argument.","main_translations_es":["Contraposición","Oposición","Contraste"],"collocations":["present a counterargument","raise a counterargument","offer a counterargument","counterargument to"],"synonyms_en":["rebuttal","opposing view","contrary point"],"example_sentence":"His statement was a counterargument to the proposed theory.","example_es":"Su argumento era la antítesis de la teoría propuesta.","example_en":"His statement was a counterargument to the proposed theory.","mnemonic_en":"On a kitchen counter, the antí