,"in the interest of conciseness","conciseness and clarity"],"synonyms_en":["brevity","succinctness","terse style"],"example_sentence":"Conciseness is essential when drafting brief reports.","example_es":"La concisión es esencial al redactar informes breves.","example_en":"Conciseness is essential when drafting brief reports.","mnemonic_en":"A tiny cactus says concisión while staying short and sharp.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La concisión es esencial al redactar informes breves.","en":"Conciseness is essential when drafting brief reports."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ampliar","english_text":"Elaborate on","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give more detail or expand upon something.","main_translations_es":["Extender","Desarrollar","Expandir"],"collocations":["elaborate on the details","elaborate on the plan","elaborate on his statement"],"synonyms_en":["expound upon","go into detail","provide details"],"example_sentence":"Could you elaborate on your explanation of the process?","example_es":"¿Podrías ampliar tu explicación sobre el proceso?","example_en":"Could you elaborate on your explanation of the process?","mnemonic_en":"Picture a lab that expands—ampliar the lab—to elaborate on the experiment.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"¿Podrías ampliar tu explicación sobre el proceso?","en":"Could you elaborate on your explanation of the process?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Resumir","english_text":"Summarize","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To give a brief statement of the main points of something.","main_translations_es":["Sintetizar","Abreviar","Compendiar"],"collocations":["summarize the main points","summarize the findings","summarize the report","summarize briefly"],"synonyms_en":["condense","recap","give an overview"],"example_sentence":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","example_es":"Por favor, resume el artículo en tres frases.","example_en":"Please summarize the article in three sentences.","mnemonic_en":"Summarize feels like a résumé being trimmed, just as the Spanish Resumir means to condense.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, resume el artículo en tres frases.","en":"Please summarize the article in three sentences."}]},{"spanish_text":"Parafrasear","english_text":"Paraphrase","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A restatement of a text or passage using different words, especially to achieve greater clarity.","main_translations_es":["Reformular","Expresar con otras palabras","Decir de otra manera"],"collocations":["to paraphrase the text","in other words","to paraphrase the author","as a paraphrase"],"synonyms_en":["restate","reword","put in other words"],"example_sentence":"Can you paraphrase what I said to make it clearer?","example_es":"¿Puedes parafrasear lo que dije para que sea más claro?","example_en":"Can you paraphrase what I said to make it clearer?","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a pair of phrase books dancing, each saying para-phrase as they paraphrase.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"¿Puedes parafrasear lo que dije para que sea más claro?","en":"Can you paraphrase what I said to make it clearer?"}]},{"spanish_text":"Citar","english_text":"Cite","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To quote or refer to a source as evidence or support.","main_translations_es":["Citar","Mencionar","Referenciar"],"collocations":["cite a source","cite evidence","cite references","cite in APA style"],"synonyms_en":["quote","reference","mention"],"example_sentence":"The article cites several experts on climate change.","example_es":"El artículo cita a varios expertos sobre el cambio climático.","example_en":"The article cites several experts on climate change.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a chef sprinkling citations like a chef saying citar to flavor a dish","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El artículo cita a varios expertos sobre el cambio climático.","en":"The article cites several experts on climate change."}]},{"spanish_text":"Referenciar","english_text":"Reference","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A source of information that is cited or consulted.","main_translations_es":["Citar","Mencionar","Aludir"],"collocations":["reference letter","reference point","make reference to","for reference"],"synonyms_en":["citation","source","mention"],"example_sentence":"It is important to reference all sources in your research paper.","example_es":"Es importante referenciar todas las fuentes en tu trabajo de investigación.","example_en":"It is important to reference all sources in your research paper.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a referee handing out a reference sheet, just like you referenciar a source.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante referenciar todas las fuentes en tu trabajo de investigación.","en":"It is important to reference all sources in your research paper."}]},{"spanish_text":"Notas a pie de página","english_text":"Footnotes","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Notes placed at the bottom of a page that give additional information or citations.","main_translations_es":["Notas al pie","Notas de pie de página","Referencias al pie"],"collocations":["in the footnotes","footnotes section","footnotes and endnotes","footnotes reference"],"synonyms_en":["endnotes","annotations","reference notes"],"example_sentence":"The footnotes explain the technical terms of the article.","example_es":"Las notas a pie de página explican los términos técnicos del artículo.","example_en":"The footnotes explain the technical terms of the article.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine tiny feet writing notes at the bottom of a page.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Las notas a pie de página explican los términos técnicos del artículo.","en":"The footnotes explain the technical terms of the article."}]},{"spanish_text":"Apéndice","english_text":"Appendix","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A supplementary section at the end of a book or document, or a small organ attached to the large intestine.","main_translations_es":["Anexo","Suplemento","Apéndice"],"collocations":["in the appendix","appendix A","see the appendix","appendix section"],"synonyms_en":["addendum","supplement","annex"],"example_sentence":"The appendix of the book contains additional information about the history.","example_es":"El apéndice del libro contiene información adicional sobre la historia.","example_en":"The appendix of the book contains additional information about the history.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a tiny appendix attached to a book, just like the Spanish apéndice sticks onto the page.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El apéndice del libro contiene información adicional sobre la historia.","en":"The appendix of the book contains additional information about the history."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resumen ejecutivo","english_text":"Executive summary","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A brief overview of a document''s main points, usually placed at the beginning.","main_translations_es":["Síntesis ejecutiva","Informe ejecutivo","Resumen de gestión"],"collocations":["prepare an executive summary","include an executive summary","the executive summary outlines","executive summary section"],"synonyms_en":["summary","overview","brief"],"example_sentence":"The executive summary of the report highlights the main findings.","example_es":"El resumen ejecutivo del informe destaca los principales hallazgos.","example_en":"The executive summary of the report highlights the main findings.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a boss (executive) giving a quick sum—''re-sum-en'' as the executive summary.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El resumen ejecutivo del informe destaca los principales hallazgos.","en":"The executive summary of the report highlights the main findings."}]},{"spanish_text":"Pregunta de investigación","english_text":"Research question","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A question that guides the focus and direction of a research study.","main_translations_es":["Cuestión de investigación","Pregunta de estudio","Interrogante de investigación"],"collocations":["formulate a research question","address the research question","answer the research question","research question formulation"],"synonyms_en":["investigative query","study question","inquiry"],"example_sentence":"The research question of my thesis is how climate change affects biodiversity.","example_es":"La pregunta de investigación de mi tesis es cómo afecta el cambio climático a la biodiversidad.","example_en":"The research question of my thesis is how climate change affects biodiversity.","mnemonic_en":"A researcher knocks on a door marked PRETTY GUNTA, demanding the answer to his question.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La pregunta de investigación de mi tesis es cómo afecta el cambio climático a la biodiversidad.","en":"The research question of my thesis is how climate change affects biodiversity."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ámbito de estudio","english_text":"Scope of the study","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"The range or extent of topics covered by the study.","main_translations_es":["Campo de estudio","Área de estudio","Rama de estudio"],"collocations":["the scope of the study includes","within the scope of the study","the scope of the study was limited","scope of the study determines"],"synonyms_en":["research scope","study range","extent of the study"],"example_sentence":"The scope of the study is molecular biology.","example_es":"El ámbito de estudio de la investigación es la biología molecular.","example_en":"The scope of the study is molecular biology.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a scope zooming over the study''s ambient field.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El ámbito de estudio de la investigación es la biología molecular.","en":"The scope of the study is molecular biology."}]},{"spanish_text":"Línea de investigación","english_text":"Research line","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A specific area or focus within a broader field of study or investigation.","main_translations_es":["Área de investigación","Campo de investigación","Tema de investigación"],"collocations":["establish a research line","follow a research line","new research line","research line in biology"],"synonyms_en":["research focus","study area","investigative track"],"example_sentence":"My research line focuses on artificial intelligence.","example_es":"Mi línea de investigación se centra en la inteligencia artificial.","example_en":"My research line focuses on artificial intelligence.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a scientist drawing a bright red research line across a map, like a Spanish línea","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Mi línea de investigación se centra en la inteligencia artificial.","en":"My research line focuses on artificial intelligence."}]},{"spanish_text":"Marco conceptual","english_text":"Conceptual framework","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A set of ideas and concepts that provides a structure for understanding or analyzing something.","main_translations_es":["Marco teórico","Estructura conceptual","Esquema conceptual"],"collocations":["within the conceptual framework","conceptual framework of","conceptual framework for","under the conceptual framework"],"synonyms_en":["theoretical model","conceptual model","theoretical framework"],"example_sentence":"The researcher presented a new conceptual framework to understand urban migration.","example_es":"El investigador presentó un nuevo marco conceptual para entender la migración urbana.","example_en":"The researcher presented a new conceptual framework to understand urban migration.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a FRAME (marco) that holds a CONCEPT, a conceptual framework.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El investigador presentó un nuevo marco conceptual para entender la migración urbana.","en":"The researcher presented a new conceptual framework to understand urban migration."}]},{"spanish_text":"Vacío de investigación","english_text":"Research gap","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A research gap is an area or topic that has not yet been studied or is insufficiently explored in existing literature.","main_translations_es":["laguna de investigación","hueco de investigación","brecha de investigación"],"collocations":["identify a research gap","address the research gap","fill the research gap","research gap analysis"],"synonyms_en":["knowledge gap","investigative void","unexplored area"],"example_sentence":"The study identifies a research gap in the relationship between diet and mental health.","example_es":"El estudio identifica un vacío de investigación en la relación entre la dieta y la salud mental.","example_en":"The study identifies a research gap in the relationship between diet and mental health.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a vacant (vacío) research lab with a big hole (gap) in the data.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El estudio identifica un vacío de investigación en la relación entre la dieta y la salud mental.","en":"The study identifies a research gap in the relationship between diet and mental health."}]},{"spanish_text":"Hallazgo clave","english_text":"Key finding","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A significant or important result discovered in a study or investigation.","main_translations_es":["Descubrimiento importante","Resultado principal","Conclusión esencial"],"collocations":["key finding of the study","key finding suggests","key finding highlights","key finding reveals"],"synonyms_en":["major discovery","principal result","main conclusion"],"example_sentence":"The key finding of the study was the relationship between diet and cardiovascular health.","example_es":"El hallazgo clave del estudio fue la relación entre la dieta y la salud cardiovascular.","example_en":"The key finding of the study was the relationship between diet and cardiovascular health.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a golden key finding a hidden hallazgo in a dusty chest","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El hallazgo clave del estudio fue la relación entre la dieta y la salud cardiovascular.","en":"The key finding of the study was the relationship between diet and cardiovascular health."}]},{"spanish_text":"Trabajo seminal","english_text":"Seminal work","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A highly influential piece of research or writing that forms the basis for later developments.","main_translations_es":["Obra seminal","Estudio pionero","Trabajo fundamental"],"collocations":["seminal work on","seminal work in","seminal work that","seminal work has"],"synonyms_en":["groundbreaking study","foundational research","pioneering work"],"example_sentence":"This article is a seminal work in the field of evolutionary biology.","example_es":"Este artículo es un trabajo seminal en el campo de la biología evolutiva.","example_en":"This article is a seminal work in the field of evolutionary biology.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a seed (seminal) sprouting a giant work of art.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Este artículo es un trabajo seminal en el campo de la biología evolutiva.","en":"This article is a seminal work in the field of evolutionary biology."}]},{"spanish_text":"Contribución original","english_text":"Original contribution","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A contribution that is new, unique, or created for the first time.","main_translations_es":["Aporte original","Contribución inicial","Aportación original"],"collocations":["make an original contribution","original contribution to the field","significant original contribution","original contribution was recognized"],"synonyms_en":["novel input","unique offering","fresh contribution"],"example_sentence":"His original contribution to the project was essential.","example_es":"Su contribución original al proyecto fue fundamental.","example_en":"His original contribution to the project was essential.","mnemonic_en":"Think of an original piece as a ''contribución'' to the exhibit.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Su contribución original al proyecto fue fundamental.","en":"His original contribution to the project was essential."}]},{"spanish_text":"Líneas futuras","english_text":"Further avenues","section_name":"Academic English","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"Additional possible paths or options for exploration.","main_translations_es":["Nuevas vías","Posibles caminos","Opciones futuras"],"collocations":["explore further avenues","open further avenues","pursue further avenues"],"synonyms_en":["additional paths","new directions","other possibilities"],"example_sentence":"We will explore further avenues to improve the project.","example_es":"Exploraremos nuevas líneas futuras para mejorar el proyecto.","example_en":"We will explore further avenues to improve the project.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a road of future lines, a further avenue stretching into tomorrow.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Exploraremos nuevas líneas futuras para mejorar el proyecto.","en":"We will explore further avenues to improve the project."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- english-news-and-society (104 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'News and Society', description = 'Advanced vocabulary for current affairs, social issues, media, technology, and global events.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'english-news-and-society';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-news-and-society') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Titular","english_text":"Headline","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A headline is a brief, attention‑grabbing title that appears at the top of a news article or other written piece.","main_translations_es":["encabezado","título","cabecera"],"collocations":["headline news","catchy headline","headline story","make headlines"],"synonyms_en":["title","heading","banner"],"example_sentence":"The headline in the newspaper announced the team''s victory.","example_es":"El titular del periódico anunciaba la victoria del equipo.","example_en":"The headline in the newspaper announced the team''s victory.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a head with a line of headlines stitched across its crown like a title.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El titular del periódico anunciaba la victoria del equipo.","en":"The headline in the newspaper announced the team''s victory."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cobertura mediática","english_text":"Media coverage","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The reporting of an event or topic by various media outlets.","main_translations_es":["Cobertura de prensa","Cobertura informativa","Cobertura periodística"],"collocations":["extensive media coverage","media coverage of the event","receive media coverage","limited media coverage"],"synonyms_en":["press coverage","news reporting","media attention"],"example_sentence":"The media coverage of the accident was extensive and continuous.","example_es":"La cobertura mediática del accidente fue extensa y constante.","example_en":"The media coverage of the accident was extensive and continuous.","mnemonic_en":"The media spreads a blanket (cobertura) over the story.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La cobertura mediática del accidente fue extensa y constante.","en":"The media coverage of the accident was extensive and continuous."}]},{"spanish_text":"Artículo de fondo","englis