dcasting of an event as it happens.","main_translations_es":["Cobertura en vivo","Transmisión en directo","Cobertura en tiempo real"],"collocations":["live coverage of the event","live coverage on TV","live coverage updates","live coverage broadcast"],"synonyms_en":["real-time reporting","on‑air reporting","instant coverage"],"example_sentence":"The live coverage of the concert will be streamed on our website.","example_es":"La cobertura en directo del concierto se transmitirá en nuestro sitio web.","example_en":"The live coverage of the concert will be streamed on our website.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cover (cobertura) being broadcast live, like a TV show unfolding in real time.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La cobertura en directo del concierto se transmitirá en nuestro sitio web.","en":"The live coverage of the concert will be streamed on our website."}]},{"spanish_text":"Actualización","english_text":"Update","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A change that adds new information or improves something to make it current.","main_translations_es":["Actualización","Puesta al día","Renovación"],"collocations":["software update","latest update","update the record","update your status"],"synonyms_en":["Refresh","Upgrade","Revise"],"example_sentence":"The update of the software improved the device''s performance.","example_es":"La actualización del software mejoró el rendimiento del dispositivo.","example_en":"The update of the software improved the device''s performance.","mnemonic_en":"Update feels like saying actual, so picture installing the latest actual news as an actualización.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La actualización del software mejoró el rendimiento del dispositivo.","en":"The update of the software improved the device''s performance."}]},{"spanish_text":"Encuesta de opinión","english_text":"Opinion poll","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A survey that asks people for their views on a particular topic.","main_translations_es":["Encuesta de opinión","Sondeo de opinión","Encuesta de percepción"],"collocations":["conduct an opinion poll","opinion poll results","national opinion poll","opinion poll survey"],"synonyms_en":["survey","poll","public poll"],"example_sentence":"The opinion poll showed that the majority supports the measure.","example_es":"La encuesta de opinión mostró que la mayoría apoya la medida.","example_en":"The opinion poll showed that the majority supports the measure.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a poll where everyone shouts their opinión like a noisy encuesta","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La encuesta de opinión mostró que la mayoría apoya la medida.","en":"The opinion poll showed that the majority supports the measure."}]},{"spanish_text":"Participación electoral","english_text":"Voter turnout","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The percentage or number of eligible voters who actually cast a ballot in an election.","main_translations_es":["Participación en las elecciones","Tasa de participación","Participación de los votantes"],"collocations":["low voter turnout","increase voter turnout","voter turnout rates","boost voter turnout"],"synonyms_en":["electoral participation","voting rate","ballot participation"],"example_sentence":"Voter turnout in the last election was 70%.","example_es":"La participación electoral en las últimas elecciones fue del 70%.","example_en":"Voter turnout in the last election was 70%.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine voters turning out, the same as participación electoral in a bustling poll.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La participación electoral en las últimas elecciones fue del 70%.","en":"Voter turnout in the last election was 70%."}]},{"spanish_text":"Campaña electoral","english_text":"Election campaign","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A coordinated effort by a candidate or political party to win votes in an upcoming election.","main_translations_es":["Campaña electoral","Campaña de elecciones","Campaña política"],"collocations":["run an election campaign","launch an election campaign","election campaign strategy","election campaign finance"],"synonyms_en":["political campaign","campaign trail","voting drive"],"example_sentence":"The election campaign began last week and the debates are already being heard.","example_es":"La campaña electoral comenzó la semana pasada y ya se están escuchando los debates.","example_en":"The election campaign began last week and the debates are already being heard.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a field (campo) full of voters electing a leader during the campaign.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La campaña electoral comenzó la semana pasada y ya se están escuchando los debates.","en":"The election campaign began last week and the debates are already being heard."}]},{"spanish_text":"Debate público","english_text":"Public debate","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A public debate is an open discussion where participants exchange differing views on a topic in front of an audience.","main_translations_es":["Foro público","Discusión pública","Debate abierto"],"collocations":["public debate on","open public debate","national public debate"],"synonyms_en":["open discussion","public discourse","forum"],"example_sentence":"The public debate on climate change attracted thousands of viewers.","example_es":"El debate público sobre el cambio climático atrajo a miles de espectadores.","example_en":"The public debate on climate change attracted thousands of viewers.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a public square where a de-bate of speakers shout the word public.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El debate público sobre el cambio climático atrajo a miles de espectadores.","en":"The public debate on climate change attracted thousands of viewers."}]},{"s