do terreno en varios países de América Latina.","en":"Populism has gained ground in several Latin American countries."}]},{"spanish_text":"Gobernanza","english_text":"Governance","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act or system of governing, or the way an organization or society is managed and controlled.","main_translations_es":["Gestión","Administración","Dirección"],"collocations":["corporate governance","good governance","governance structure","governance framework"],"synonyms_en":["administration","management","rule"],"example_sentence":"The governance of the company is based on transparency and employee participation.","example_es":"La gobernanza de la empresa se basa en la transparencia y la participación de los empleados.","example_en":"The governance of the company is based on transparency and employee participation.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a governor handing a SA map, showing his governance","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La gobernanza de la empresa se basa en la transparencia y la participación de los empleados.","en":"The governance of the company is based on transparency and employee participation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Transparencia","english_text":"Transparency","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The quality of being clear, open, or easily understood, or the condition of allowing light to pass through so that objects behind can be seen.","main_translations_es":["Claridad","Limpidez","Visibilidad"],"collocations":["transparency in government","financial transparency","transparency and accountability","transparency report"],"synonyms_en":["openness","clarity","candor"],"example_sentence":"Government transparency is essential for citizens'' trust.","example_es":"La transparencia del gobierno es esencial para la confianza de los ciudadanos.","example_en":"Government transparency is essential for citizens'' trust.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a clear glass that lets all transparencia shine through, showing everything inside.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La transparencia del gobierno es esencial para la confianza de los ciudadanos.","en":"Government transparency is essential for citizens'' trust."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rendición de cuentas","english_text":"Accountability","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The obligation to accept responsibility for one''s actions and decisions.","main_translations_es":["Responsabilidad","Justificación","Transparencia"],"collocations":["accountability measures","accountability framework","accountability for actions"],"synonyms_en":["responsibility","answerability","liability"],"example_sentence":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","example_es":"La rendición de cuentas es fundamental para la transparencia en el gobierno.","example_en":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a ledger where each cuenta is an account you must hand over, making you fully accountable","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La rendición de cuentas es fundamental para la transparencia en el gobierno.","en":"Accountability is essential for transparency in government."}]},{"spanish_text":"Corrupción","english_text":"Corruption","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Dishonest or fraudulent conduct by those in power, often involving bribery or the misuse of authority for personal gain.","main_translations_es":["Corrupción","Deshonestidad","Mala conducta"],"collocations":["corruption scandal","corruption charges","fight against corruption","corruption in politics"],"synonyms_en":["dishonesty","bribery","graft"],"example_sentence":"Corruption in the government has decreased thanks to the new laws.","example_es":"La corrupción en el gobierno ha disminuido gracias a las nuevas leyes.","example_en":"Corruption in the government has decreased thanks to the new laws.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a corrupt ion sneaking into the core of power.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La corrupción en el gobierno ha disminuido gracias a las nuevas leyes.","en":"Corruption in the government has decreased thanks to the new laws."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desigualdad","english_text":"Inequality","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A condition of being unequal, especially in status, rights, or opportunities.","main_translations_es":["Desigualdad","Desigualdad social","Desigualdad económica"],"collocations":["income inequality","gender inequality","social inequality","racial inequality"],"synonyms_en":["disparity","imbalance","unequal treatment"],"example_sentence":"Salary inequality between men and women remains a serious problem.","example_es":"La desigualdad salarial entre hombres y mujeres sigue siendo un problema grave.","example_en":"Salary inequality between men and women remains a serious problem.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a broken scale labeled Desigualdad, its pans uneven, showing inequality.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La desigualdad salarial entre hombres y mujeres sigue siendo un problema grave.","en":"Salary inequality between men and women remains a serious problem."}]},{"spanish_text":"Movilidad social","english_text":"Social mobility","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The movement of individuals or groups within or between social classes in a society.","main_translations_es":["Movilidad social","Ascenso social","Movilidad de clase"],"collocations":["intergenerational social mobility","enhance social mobility","promote social mobility"],"synonyms_en":["class movement","upward mobility","intergenerational mobility"],"example_sentence":"Social mobility is a key indicator of equal opportunity in a society.","example_es":"La movilidad social es un indicador clave de la igualdad de oportunidades en una sociedad.","example_en":"Social mobility is a key indicator of equal opportunity in a society.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a social ladder on a moving bus called movilidad climbing upward","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La movilidad social es un indicador clave de la igualdad de oportunidades en una sociedad.","en":"Social mobility is a key indicator of equal opportunity in a society."}]},{"spanish_text":"Costo de vida","english_text":"Cost of living","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The amount of money required to cover basic expenses such as housing, food, taxes, and healthcare in a specific location.","main_translations_es":["Costo de vida"],"collocations":["cost of living index","cost of living adjustment","cost of living expenses","cost of living in"],"synonyms_en":["living expenses","household costs","daily expenses"],"example_sentence":"The cost of living in Madrid is very high.","example_es":"El costo de vida en Madrid es muy alto.","example_en":"The cost of living in Madrid is very high.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine paying the cost (costo) of a lively (living) party.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El costo de vida en Madrid es muy alto.","en":"The cost of living in Madrid is very high."}]},{"spanish_text":"Inflación","english_text":"Inflation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A general increase in prices and a corresponding decline in the purchasing power of money.","main_translations_es":["Alza de precios","Aumento de precios","Crecimiento de precios"],"collocations":["inflation rate","inflationary pressure","inflation-adjusted","inflation targeting"],"synonyms_en":["price rise","cost increase","rising prices"],"example_sentence":"Inflation has increased the cost of food.","example_es":"La inflación ha aumentado el costo de los alimentos.","example_en":"Inflation has increased the cost of food.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a balloon inflating as ''inflación'' lifts prices.","cloze_distrac