 its supply chain to reduce costs.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a chain of crates delivering supplies, linking the Spanish ''cadena'' to the English supply chain.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La empresa está optimizando su cadena de suministro para reducir costos.","en":"The company is optimizing its supply chain to reduce costs."}]},{"spanish_text":"Interrupción","english_text":"Disruption","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A disturbance or interruption that prevents something from continuing smoothly.","main_translations_es":["Corte","Parada","Suspensión"],"collocations":["cause disruption","disruption of services","major disruption","disruption in the market"],"synonyms_en":["disturbance","interruption","upheaval"],"example_sentence":"The disruption of the power supply left the city without electricity.","example_es":"La interrupción del suministro eléctrico dejó a la ciudad sin luz.","example_en":"The disruption of the power supply left the city without electricity.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a loud crash disrupting a quiet room, like an Interrupción breaking the silence.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La interrupción del suministro eléctrico dejó a la ciudad sin luz.","en":"The disruption of the power supply left the city without electricity."}]},{"spanish_text":"Escalada","english_text":"Escalation","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A rapid increase or intensification, especially of a conflict, problem, or situation.","main_translations_es":["Subida","Ascenso","Trepar"],"collocations":["escalation of conflict","price escalation","rapid escalation","escalation clause"],"synonyms_en":["increase","rise","amplification"],"example_sentence":"The escalation of the conflict surprised everyone.","example_es":"La escalada del conflicto sorprendió a todos.","example_en":"The escalation of the conflict surprised everyone.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a climber on an escalada rope that suddenly becomes a rising chart, showing escalation.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La escalada del conflicto sorprendió a todos.","en":"The escalation of the conflict surprised everyone."}]},{"spanish_text":"Alto el fuego","english_text":"Ceasefire","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A temporary suspension of fighting between opposing sides.","main_translations_es":["Cese del fuego","Alto al fuego","Alto al combate"],"collocations":["call for a ceasefire","agree to a ceasefire","observe a ceasefire","hold a ceasefire"],"synonyms_en":["truce","armistice","halt to fighting"],"example_sentence":"Ceasefire, before more people get hurt.","example_es":"Alto el fuego, antes de que más personas resulten heridas.","example_en":"Ceasefire, before more people get hurt.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a ceasefire where commanders yell ''Alto el fuego!'' to halt the fire.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Alto el fuego, antes de que más personas resulten heridas.","en":"Ceasefire, before more people get hurt."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sanción","english_text":"Sanction","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A penalty imposed for violating a law, rule, or regulation.","main_translations_es":["Castigo","Multa","Penalización"],"collocations":["impose sanctions","economic sanctions","sanctioned by the UN","sanction a law"],"synonyms_en":["penalty","approval","authorization"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to impose a sanction of ten thousand euros on the club for violating the rules.","example_es":"El comité decidió imponer una sanción de diez mil euros al club por incumplir las normas.","example_en":"The committee decided to impose a sanction of ten thousand euros on the club for violating the rules.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a judge stamping a document with a red sanction stamp that reads Sanción","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió imponer una sanción de diez mil euros al club por incumplir las normas.","en":"The committee decided to impose a sanction of ten thousand euros on the club for violating the rules."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ayuda humanitaria","english_text":"Humanitarian aid","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Assistance given to people in need, especially during crises or disasters, to alleviate suffering and protect life and health.","main_translations_es":["Asistencia humanitaria","Socorro humanitario","Apoyo humanitario"],"collocations":["provide humanitarian aid","humanitarian aid efforts","humanitarian aid organization","humanitarian aid funding"],"synonyms_en":["relief assistance","humanitarian assistance","disaster relief"],"example_sentence":"Humanitarian aid arrived in the area affected by the earthquake.","example_es":"La ayuda humanitaria llegó a la zona afectada por el terremoto.","example_en":"Humanitarian aid arrived in the area affected by the earthquake.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a human handing out aid while yelling Ayuda to the crowd.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La ayuda humanitaria llegó a la zona afectada por el terremoto.","en":"Humanitarian aid arrived in the area affected by the earthquake."}]},{"spanish_text":"Desplazamiento forzado","english_text":"Forced displacement","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The involuntary movement of people from their homes or habitual residence, usually caused by conflict, persecution, or natural disasters.","main_translations_es":["Desplazamiento forzado","Desplazamiento involuntario","Desplazamiento obligado"],"collocations":["forced displacement crisis","forced displacement of populations","address forced displacement","prevent forced displacement"],"synonyms_en":["forced migration","involuntary relocation","compulsory eviction"],"example_sentence":"The forced displacement of thousands of families has created a humanitarian crisis.","example_es":"El desplazamiento forzado de miles de familias ha creado una crisis humanitaria.","example_en":"The forced displacement of thousands of families has created a humanitarian crisis.","mnemonic_en":"A force shoves the word des off a map, creating forced displacement.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El desplazamiento forzado de miles de familias ha creado una crisis humanitaria.","en":"The forced displacement of thousands of families has created a humanitarian crisis."}]},{"spanish_text":"Derechos humanos","english_text":"Human rights","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Fundamental rights and freedoms that belong to every person simply because they are human.","main_translations_es":["Derechos fundamentales","Derechos civiles","Derechos de la persona"],"collocations":["human rights violations","human rights activist","human rights law","human rights organization"],"synonyms_en":["civil liberties","fundamental rights","basic freedoms"],"example_sentence":"Human rights must be respected worldwide.","example_es":"Los derechos humanos deben ser respetados en todo el mundo.","example_en":"Human rights must be respected worldwide.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a human holding a shield labeled derechos to guard his rights.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Los derechos humanos deben ser respetados en todo el mundo.","en":"Human rights must be respected worldwide."}]},{"spanish_text":"Libertad de expresión","english_text":"Freedom of speech","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The right to express one''s opinions publicly without censorship or restraint.","main_translations_es":["Libertad de expresión","Derecho a la libre expresión","Libertad de opinión"],"collocations":["freedom of speech is essential","protect freedom of speech","advocate for freedom of speech","freedom of speech rights"],"synonyms_en":["free speech","speech freedom","right to speak"],"example_sentence":"Freedom of speech is a fundamental right in a democracy.","example_es":"La libertad de expresión es un derecho fundamental en una democracia.","example_en":"Freedom of speech is a fundamental right in a democracy.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a free dome where a liberty flag waves and everyone shouts Libertad","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La libertad de expresión es un derecho fundamental en una democracia.","en":"Freedom of speech is a fundamental right in a democracy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Estado de derecho","english_text":"Rule of law","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The principle that all individuals and institutions, including the government, are bound by and accountable to publicly known laws.","main_translations_es":["Estado de la ley","ordenamiento jurídico","régimen de derecho"],"collocations":["uphold the rule of law","rule of law principles","rule of law framework","rule of law and democracy"],"synonyms_en":["legal order","lawful governance","juridical system"],"example_sentence":"In a rule of law system, all citizens are subject to the same legislation.","example_es":"En un Estado de derecho, todos los ciudadanos están sujetos a la misma legislación.","example_en":"In a rule of law system, all citizens are subject to the same legislation.","mnemonic_en":"A ruler sits on a law book inside a grand Estado, showing the rule of law.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"En un Estado de derecho, todos los ciudadanos están sujetos a la misma legislación.","en":"In a rule of law system, all citizens are subject to the same legislation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reforma","english_text":"Reform","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A change made to improve a system, institution, or practice.","main_translations_es":["Modificación","Cambio","Reajuste"],"collocations":["tax reform","education reform","healthcare reform"],"synonyms_en":["improvement","change","overhaul"],"exa