a la reforma laboral atrajo a miles de personas.","example_en":"The demonstration against the labor reform attracted thousands of people.","mnemonic_en":"A MANI shows a DEMO, so it becomes a DEMONSTRATION.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La manifestación contra la reforma laboral atrajo a miles de personas.","en":"The demonstration against the labor reform attracted thousands of people."}]},{"spanish_text":"Activismo","english_text":"Activism","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Activism is the practice of organized efforts to promote or oppose social, political, or environmental change.","main_translations_es":["Activismo","Activismo social","Activismo político"],"collocations":["grassroots activism","environmental activism","political activism","social activism"],"synonyms_en":["advocacy","campaigning","social action"],"example_sentence":"Youth activism has driven significant changes in environmental policy.","example_es":"El activismo juvenil ha impulsado cambios significativos en la política ambiental.","example_en":"Youth activism has driven significant changes in environmental policy.","mnemonic_en":"Picture an activist shouting activo while marching, showing activism is the active movement.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El activismo juvenil ha impulsado cambios significativos en la política ambiental.","en":"Youth activism has driven significant changes in environmental policy."}]},{"spanish_text":"Movilización","english_text":"Mobilization","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The act of assembling and preparing troops or resources for active service.","main_translations_es":["Movilización","Despliegue","Activación"],"collocations":["mass mobilization","resource mobilization","mobilization effort","mobilization plan"],"synonyms_en":["deployment","activation","mustering"],"example_sentence":"The mobilization of resources was key to the project''s success.","example_es":"La movilización de los recursos fue clave para el éxito del proyecto.","example_en":"The mobilization of resources was key to the project''s success.","mnemonic_en":"A mobile van leads the parade, showing the power of mobilization.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La movilización de los recursos fue clave para el éxito del proyecto.","en":"The mobilization of resources was key to the project''s success."}]},{"spanish_text":"Conciencia pública","english_text":"Public awareness","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the state of being informed or conscious about a particular issue among the general public","main_translations_es":["conciencia colectiva","conciencia social","conciencia ciudadana"],"collocations":["raise public awareness","public awareness campaign","increase public awareness","public awareness of"],"synonyms_en":["public knowledge","community awareness","public consciousness"],"example_sentence":"The campaign raised public awareness about climate change.","example_es":"La campaña aumentó la conciencia pública sobre el cambio climático.","example_en":"The campaign raised public awareness about climate change.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a public plaza with a giant ''aware-ness'' billboard that reads ''conciencia'' for everyone to see.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La campaña aumentó la conciencia pública sobre el cambio climático.","en":"The campaign raised public awareness about climate change."}]},{"spanish_text":"Narrativa","english_text":"Narrative","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A spoken or written account of connected events; a story.","main_translations_es":["Relato","Historia","Crónica"],"collocations":["narrative structure","narrative voice","narrative arc","narrative perspective"],"synonyms_en":["story","account","tale"],"example_sentence":"The narrative of the novel captures the essence of the era.","example_es":"La narrativa de la novela captura la esencia de la época.","example_en":"The narrative of the novel captures the essence of the era.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a narrator writing a story, his narrativa becomes the narrative.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La narrativa de la novela captura la esencia de la época.","en":"The narrative of the novel captures the essence of the era."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sesgo mediático","english_text":"Media bias","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A tendency of journalists or news outlets to present information in a way that favors a particular perspective or agenda.","main_translations_es":["Parcialidad mediática","Sesgo de los medios","Tendencia mediática"],"collocations":["media bias affects public opinion","combat media bias","perceived media bias","media bias in reporting"],"synonyms_en":["press bias","news bias","journalistic bias"],"example_sentence":"Media bias affects the way we perceive the news.","example_es":"El sesgo mediático afecta la forma en que percibimos las noticias.","example_en":"Media bias affects the way we perceive the news.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a TV news tilt, a media bias – a slanted sesgo on the screen.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El sesgo mediático afecta la forma en que percibimos las noticias.","en":"Media bias affects the way we perceive the news."}]},{"spanish_text":"Verificación de hechos","english_text":"Fact-checking","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of verifying the accuracy of information or claims.","main_translations_es":["Chequeo de datos","Contraste de hechos","Comprobación de hechos"],"collocations":["fact-checking process","fact-checking organization","fact-checking tools","fact-checking report"],"synonyms_en":["verification","source verification","truth verification"],"example_sentence":"Fact-checking is essential to combat misinformation.","example_es":"La verificación de hechos es esencial para combatir la desinformación.","example_en":"Fact-checking is essential to combat misinformation.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a detective checking facts and stamping each hecho with a green check.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La verificación de hechos es esencial para combatir la desinformación.","en":"Fact-checking is essential to combat misinformation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Difundirse","english_text":"Spread rapidly","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To become widely known or distributed quickly.","main_translations_es":["propagarse","extenderse","diseminarse"],"collocations":["spread like wildfire","spread quickly","spread fast","spread at a rapid pace"],"synonyms_en":["propagate quickly","disseminate fast","snowball"],"example_sentence":"The rumor spread rapidly throughout the neighborhood.","example_es":"El rumor se difundió rápidamente por todo el vecindario.","example_en":"The rumor spread rapidly throughout the neighborhood.","mnemonic_en":"A fast‑spreading fire is a ''difund'' of flames racing across the forest.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El rumor se difundió rápidamente por todo el vecindario.","en":"The rumor spread rapidly throughout the neighborhood."}]},{"spanish_text":"Volverse viral","english_text":"Go viral","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"to become widely circulated on the internet, especially through rapid sharing.","main_translations_es":["Hacerse viral","Convertirse en viral","Tornar viral"],"collocations":["go viral on social media","go viral overnight","go viral quickly","go viral instantly"],"synonyms_en":["spread rapidly","catch on online","become a hit"],"example_sentence":"The video went viral within hours.","example_es":"El video se volvió viral en cuestión de horas.","example_en":"The video went viral within hours.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a goat (go) turning into a virus, spreading wildly like a viral video.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El video se volvió viral en cuestión de horas.","en":"The video went viral within hours."}]},{"spanish_text":"Repercusiones","english_text":"Repercussions","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Unintended or indirect consequences of an action or event, often negative.","main_translations_es":["Consecuencias","Efectos","Resultados"],"collocations":["face the repercussions","have repercussions","repercussions of","suffer the repercussions"],"synonyms_en":["consequences","effects","ramifications"],"example_sentence":"The repercussions of the decision will be felt for years.","example_es":"Las repercusiones de la decisión se sentirán durante años.","example_en":"The repercussions of the decision will be felt for years.","mnemonic_en":"Hear re-per-cus-iones echo and picture the fallout spreading like ripples.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Las repercusiones de la decisión se sentirán durante años.","en":"The repercussions of the decision will be felt for years."}]},{"spanish_text":"Consecuencia imprevista","english_text":"Unintended consequence","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"An outcome that was not intended or expected.","main_translations_es":["Resultado inesperado","Efecto inesperado","Repercusiones no previstas"],"collocations":["as an unintended consequence","the unintended consequence","unintended consequence of","unintended consequence for"],"synonyms_en":["unforeseen result","unexpected outcome","unintended result"],"example_sentence":"The unintended consequence of his policy was an unexpected rise in inflation.","example_es":"La consecuencia imprevista de su política fue un aumento inesperado de la inflación.","example_en":"The unintended consequence of his policy was an unexpected rise in inflation.","mnemonic_en":"An unexpected accident creates a \"con-sequence\" chain, like a surprise domino effect.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La consecuencia imprevista de su política fue un aumento inesperado de la inflación.","en":"The unintended consequence of his policy was an unexpected rise in inflation."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resiliencia","english_text":"Resilience","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The ability to recover quickly from difficulties or to adapt in the face of adversity.","main_translations_es":["Capacidad de recuperación","Fortaleza mental","Elasticidad"],"collocations":["building resilience","resilience in the face of adversity","show resilience","resilience training"],"synonyms_en":["toughness","hardiness","flexibility"],"example_sentence":"The community''s resilience allowed it to recover quickly after the earthquake.","example_es":"La resiliencia de la comunidad le permitió recuperarse rápidamente después del terremoto.","example_en":"The community''s resilience allowed it to recover quickly after the earthquake.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a resilient rubber band snapping back, echoing resiliencia in a storm.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La resiliencia de la comunidad le permitió recuperarse rápidamente después del terremoto.","en":"The community''s resilience allowed it to recover quickly after the earthquake."}]},{"spanish_text":"Capacidad de adaptación","english_text":"Adaptability","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The ability to adjust to new conditions or changes.","main_translations_es":["Flexibilidad","Capacidad de ajuste","Aptitud para adaptarse"],"collocations":["adaptability is key","high adaptability","demonstrate adaptability","adaptability skills"],"synonyms_en":["flexibility","versatility","adjustability"],"example_sentence":"His adaptability allowed him to overcome the changes at work.","example_es":"Su capacidad de adaptación le permitió superar los cambios en el trabajo.","example_en":"His adaptability allowed him to overcome the changes at work.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a flexible cap that adapts to any shape, showing the adaptability of capacidad.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Su capacidad de adaptación le permitió superar los cambios en el trabajo.","en":"His adaptability allowed him to overcome the changes at work."}]},{"spanish_text":"Interdependencia","english_text":"Interdependence","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"the mutual reliance between two or more entities, where each depends on the others.","main_translations_es":["Mutua dependencia","Dependencia recíproca","Interrelación"],"collocations":["mutual interdependence","economic interdependence","global interdependence","interdependence theory"],"synonyms_en":["mutual reliance","reciprocal dependence","co‑dependence"],"example_sentence":"The interdependence among Latin American countries is reflected in their trade agreements.","example_es":"La interdependencia entre los países latinoamericanos se refleja en sus acuerdos comerciales.","example_en":"The interdependence among Latin American countries is reflected in their trade agreements.","mnemonic_en":"Picture two friends leaning on each other, their bond is interdependence like inter and depend together.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La interdependencia entre los países latinoamericanos se refleja en sus acuerdos comerciales.","en":"The interdependence among Latin American countries is reflected in their trade agreements."}]},{"spanish_text":"Consenso científico","english_text":"Scientific consensus","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"General agreement among scientists about a particular scientific finding or theory.","main_translations_es":["acuerdo científico","consenso de la comunidad científica","posicionamiento científico"],"collocations":["reach a scientific consensus","scientific consensus on climate change","widely accepted scientific consensus","the scientific consensus is that"],"synonyms_en":["expert agreement","research consensus","scientific agreement"],"example_sentence":"The scientific consensus indicates that climate change is primarily caused by human activity.","example_es":"El consenso científico indica que el cambio climático es causado principalmente por la actividad humana.","example_en":"The scientific consensus indicates that climate change is primarily caused by human activity.","mnemonic_en":"Scientists sit (siéntate) together, forming a scientific consensus.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El consenso científico indica que el cambio climático es causado principalmente por la actividad humana.","en":"The scientific consensus indicates that climate change is primarily caused by human activity."}]},{"spanish_text":"Debate ético","english_text":"Ethical debate","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A discussion that examines moral principles and values.","main_translations_es":["Discusión ética","Debate moral","Diálogo ético"],"collocations":["engage in an ethical debate","participate in an ethical debate","ethical debate on climate change","ethical debate surrounding AI"],"synonyms_en":["moral discussion","ethical discussion","moral debate"],"example_sentence":"The ethical debate about genetic editing is very controversial.","example_es":"El debate ético sobre la edición genética es muy controvertido.","example_en":"The ethical debate about genetic editing is very controversial.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize an ethical debate with participants holding big signs that read ético.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El debate ético sobre la edición genética es muy controvertido.","en":"The ethical debate about genetic editing is very controversial."}]},{"spanish_text":"Brecha generacional","english_text":"Generation gap","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A difference in attitudes, values, and experiences between people of different generations.","main_translations_es":["brecha generacional","diferencia generacional","distancia generacional"],"collocations":["bridge the generation gap","close the generation gap","widen the generation gap","generation gap issues"],"synonyms_en":["age divide","intergenerational divide","youth‑adult divide"],"example_sentence":"The generation gap between young people and their parents is evident in their use of technology.","example_es":"La brecha generacional entre los jóvenes y sus padres se hace evidente en el uso de la tecnología.","example_en":"The generation gap between young people and their parents is evident in their use of technology.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a huge gap where a generation falls into a brecha, a crack separating the old from the young.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La brecha generacional entre los jóvenes y sus padres se hace evidente en el uso de la tecnología.","en":"The generation gap between young people and their parents is evident in their use of technology."}]},{"spanish_text":"Presión social","english_text":"Social pressure","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The influence exerted by a group or society on an individual''s behavior or decisions.","main_translations_es":["presión social","presión de grupo","presión colectiva"],"collocations":["under social pressure","succumb to social pressure","resist social pressure","social pressure to conform"],"synonyms_en":["peer pressure","societal pressure","group pressure"],"example_sentence":"Social pressure led him to quit his job.","example_es":"La presión social lo llevó a dejar su trabajo.","example_en":"Social pressure led him to quit his job.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a social crowd pressing ion batteries, showing social pressure.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La presión social lo llevó a dejar su trabajo.","en":"Social pressure led him to quit his job."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cohesión social","english_text":"Social cohesion","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The bonds, shared values, and sense of belonging that hold members of a society together.","main_translations_es":["Cooperación social","Solidaridad social","Integración social"],"collocations":["promote social cohesion","strengthen social cohesion","enhance social cohesion","social cohesion initiatives"],"synonyms_en":["community solidarity","social unity","social integration"],"example_sentence":"Social cohesion is essential for the community''s development.","example_es":"La cohesión social es fundamental para el desarrollo de la comunidad.","example_en":"Social cohesion is essential for the community''s development.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a social gathering where people tie a rope called ''cohesión'' to stay tightly connected.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La cohesión social es fundamental para el desarrollo de la comunidad.","en":"Social cohesion is essential for the community''s development."}]},{"spanish_text":"Sentimiento de pertenencia","english_text":"Sense of belonging","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A feeling of being accepted and valued as part of a group or community.","main_translations_es":["Sentido de pertenencia","Sensación de pertenencia","Pertenencia"],"collocations":["foster a sense of belonging","enhance the sense of belonging","create a sense of belonging","sense of belonging"],"synonyms_en":["feeling of inclusion","community feeling","belongingness"],"example_sentence":"The sense of belonging he feels in his community motivates him to participate actively.","example_es":"El sentimiento de pertenencia que experimenta en su comunidad lo motiva a participar activamente.","example_en":"The sense of belonging he feels in his community motivates him to participate actively.","mnemonic_en":"I feel a sense of belonging like a censo of people holding hands.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El sentimiento de pertenencia que experimenta en su comunidad lo motiva a participar activamente.","en":"The sense of belonging he feels in his community motivates him to participate actively."}]},{"spanish_text":"Marginalización","english_text":"Marginalization","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of treating a person or group as insignificant or peripheral.","main_translations_es":["Exclusión","Segregación","Marginación"],"collocations":["social marginalization","economic marginalization","cultural marginalization","political marginalization"],"synonyms_en":["social exclusion","ostracism","peripheralization"],"example_sentence":"The marginalization of rural communities hinders their access to basic services.","example_es":"La marginalización de las comunidades rurales dificulta su acceso a servicios básicos.","example_en":"The marginalization of rural communities hinders their access to basic services.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a margin line shoving a crowd to the side, showing marginalization.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La marginalización de las comunidades rurales dificulta su acceso a servicios básicos.","en":"The marginalization of rural communities hinders their access to basic services."}]},{"spanish_text":"Empoderamiento","english_text":"Empowerment","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"The process of giving someone authority, confidence, or power to act or make decisions.","main_translations_es":["Capacitación","Fortalecimiento","Autonomía"],"collocations":["women''s empowerment","employee empowerment","community empowerment","empowerment program"],"synonyms_en":["authority","enablement","self-determination"],"example_sentence":"The empowerment of women is essential for sustainable development.","example_es":"El empoderamiento de las mujeres es fundamental para el desarrollo sostenible.","example_en":"The empowerment of women is essential for sustainable development.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a glowing power button marked empower‑ment as you shout the Spanish word empoderamiento.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El empoderamiento de las mujeres es fundamental para el desarrollo sostenible.","en":"The empowerment of women is essential for sustainable development."}]},{"spanish_text":"Justicia climática","english_text":"Climate justice","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"Climate justice is the principle of ensuring fair and equitable treatment of all people in the distribution of climate change impacts and responsibilities.","main_translations_es":["Equidad climática","Justicia ambiental del clima"],"collocations":["climate justice movement","climate justice framework","climate justice initiatives"],"synonyms_en":["environmental justice","climate equity","environmental equity"],"example_sentence":"Climate justice demands that rich countries cut their emissions to protect the most vulnerable.","example_es":"La justicia climática exige que los países ricos reduzcan sus emisiones para proteger a los más vulnerables.","example_en":"Climate justice demands that rich countries cut their emissions to protect the most vulnerable.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a courtroom in a stormy climate where justice rains down on the earth.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La justicia climática exige que los países ricos reduzcan sus emisiones para proteger a los más vulnerables.","en":"Climate justice demands that rich countries cut their emissions to protect the most vulnerable."}]},{"spanish_text":"Justicia social","english_text":"Social justice","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A principle of fairness that seeks equitable distribution of resources, rights, and opportunities within a society.","main_translations_es":["Justicia social","Equidad social","Igualdad social"],"collocations":["social justice movement","social justice issues","social justice advocacy","social justice initiatives"],"synonyms_en":["equity","fairness","equal rights"],"example_sentence":"The movement fights for social justice in the community.","example_es":"El movimiento lucha por la justicia social en la comunidad.","example_en":"The movement fights for social justice in the community.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a just sea where all people share social waves.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El movimiento lucha por la justicia social en la comunidad.","en":"The movement fights for social justice in the community."}]},{"spanish_text":"Responsabilidad compartida","english_text":"Shared responsibility","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A situation in which two or more parties are jointly accountable for an outcome.","main_translations_es":["Responsabilidad conjunta","Responsabilidad mutua","Responsabilidad colectiva"],"collocations":["shared responsibility for","shared responsibility between","shared responsibility model","shared responsibility approach"],"synonyms_en":["joint accountability","collective duty","mutual obligation"],"example_sentence":"Shared responsibility between parents and teachers is essential for the student''s success.","example_es":"La responsabilidad compartida entre los padres y los maestros es esencial para el éxito del estudiante.","example_en":"Shared responsibility between parents and teachers is essential for the student''s success.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine two people sharing a heavy bag of duty—shared responsibility","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La responsabilidad compartida entre los padres y los maestros es esencial para el éxito del estudiante.","en":"Shared responsibility between parents and teachers is essential for the student''s success."}]},{"spanish_text":"Tema candente","english_text":"Hot-button issue","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun","definition_en":"A controversial or emotionally charged topic that provokes strong opinions.","main_translations_es":["Asunto polémico","Cuestión delicada","Tema controvertido"],"collocations":["raise a hot‑button issue","address a hot‑button issue","hot‑button issue in politics"],"synonyms_en":["controversial topic","contentious issue","sensitive subject"],"example_sentence":"Climate change has become a hot‑button issue in international politics.","example_es":"El cambio climático se ha convertido en un tema candente en la política internacional.","example_en":"Climate change has become a hot‑button issue in international politics.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a red button on fire, the hot button that sparks every heated debate","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El cambio climático se ha convertido en un tema candente en la política internacional.","en":"Climate change has become a hot‑button issue in international politics."}]},{"spanish_text":"Amplia repercusión","english_text":"Far-reaching impact","section_name":"News and Society","part_of_speech":"noun phrase","definition_en":"A significant or extensive effect or influence.","main_translations_es":["Gran repercusión","Amplio alcance","Extensa influencia"],"collocations":["has a far‑reaching impact","far‑reaching impact on society","with far‑reaching impact","far‑reaching impact on the economy"],"synonyms_en":["wide-ranging effect","significant influence","extensive consequences"],"example_sentence":"The new law will have a far-reaching impact on the country''s economy.","example_es":"La nueva ley tendrá una amplia repercusión en la economía del país.","example_en":"The new law will have a far-reaching impact on the country''s economy.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a far‑reaching arm amplifying a massive ripple, a repercussion that spreads across the world.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"La nueva ley tendrá una amplia repercusión en la economía del país.","en":"The new law will have a far-reaching impact on the country''s economy."}]}]'::jsonb) as x(
  spanish_text text, english_text text, section_name text, part_of_speech text, definition_en text,
  main_translations_es jsonb, collocations jsonb, synonyms_en jsonb, example_sentence text, example_es text, example_en text, mnemonic_en text, cloze_distractors_en jsonb, examples jsonb
)
where c.deck_id = dk.id
  and lower(c.spanish_text) = lower(x.spanish_text)
  and lower(c.english_text) = lower(x.english_text);

-- english-advanced-phrasal-verbs (110 cards)
update public.decks set
  title = 'Advanced Phrasal Verbs', description = 'A large deck of phrasal verbs and common advanced uses to improve fluency and natural expression.',
  language_from = 'es', language_to = 'en'
where slug = 'english-advanced-phrasal-verbs';

update public.cards c set
  section_name = x.section_name, part_of_speech = x.part_of_speech, definition_en = x.definition_en,
  main_translations_es = coalesce(x.main_translations_es, '[]'::jsonb),
  collocations = coalesce(x.collocations, '[]'::jsonb),
  synonyms_en = coalesce(x.synonyms_en, '[]'::jsonb),
  example_sentence = x.example_sentence, example_es = x.example_es, example_en = x.example_en,
  mnemonic_en = coalesce(x.mnemonic_en, c.mnemonic_en),
  cloze_distractors_en = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.cloze_distractors_en, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                              then x.cloze_distractors_en else c.cloze_distractors_en end,
  examples = case when jsonb_array_length(coalesce(x.examples, '[]'::jsonb)) > 0
                  then x.examples else c.examples end
from (select id from public.decks where slug = 'english-advanced-phrasal-verbs') dk
cross join jsonb_to_recordset('[{"spanish_text":"Mencionar","english_text":"Bring up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to mention or raise a topic for discussion","main_translations_es":["Citar","Aludir","Referir"],"collocations":["bring up a topic","bring up an issue","bring up a child","bring up the subject"],"synonyms_en":["raise","mention","broach"],"example_sentence":"During the meeting, Juan brought up the budget issue.","example_es":"Durante la reunión, Juan mencionó el problema del presupuesto.","example_en":"During the meeting, Juan brought up the budget issue.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a man (men) being lifted up, so you bring him up to mention the story.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Durante la reunión, Juan mencionó el problema del presupuesto.","en":"During the meeting, Juan brought up the budget issue."}]},{"spanish_text":"Llevar a cabo","english_text":"Carry out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to perform or execute a task or plan","main_translations_es":["realizar","ejecutar","desarrollar"],"collocations":["carry out a plan","carry out an experiment","carry out the investigation","carry out duties"],"synonyms_en":["execute","perform","implement"],"example_sentence":"The committee decided to carry out the investigation next week.","example_es":"El comité decidió llevar a cabo la investigación la próxima semana.","example_en":"The committee decided to carry out the investigation next week.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a carrier delivering a cargo to a cape (cabo) – you carry out the mission.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El comité decidió llevar a cabo la investigación la próxima semana.","en":"The committee decided to carry out the investigation next week."}]},{"spanish_text":"Encontrarse con","english_text":"Come across","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to find or meet something or someone by chance","main_translations_es":["Toparse con","Tropezar con","Dar con"],"collocations":["come across as","come across something","come across unexpectedly"],"synonyms_en":["encounter","find","stumble upon"],"example_sentence":"I came across an old friend at the market.","example_es":"Me encontré con un viejo amigo en el mercado.","example_en":"I came across an old friend at the market.","mnemonic_en":"I come across (como cruz) a friend and we meet.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me encontré con un viejo amigo en el mercado.","en":"I came across an old friend at the market."}]},{"spanish_text":"Idear","english_text":"Come up with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To think of or produce an idea, plan, or solution.","main_translations_es":["concebir","inventar","elaborar"],"collocations":["come up with an idea","come up with a solution","come up with a plan","come up with a name"],"synonyms_en":["think of","devise","invent"],"example_sentence":"We need to come up with a solution before the day ends.","example_es":"Necesitamos idear una solución antes de que termine el día.","example_en":"We need to come up with a solution before the day ends.","mnemonic_en":"I see a lightbulb rise as I idear and come up with a new plan.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesitamos idear una solución antes de que termine el día.","en":"We need to come up with a solution before the day ends."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reducir","english_text":"Cut down on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to reduce the amount or frequency of something","main_translations_es":["Disminuir","Recortar","Ajustar"],"collocations":["cut down on sugar","cut down on expenses","cut down on smoking"],"synonyms_en":["reduce","curtail","scale back"],"example_sentence":"I need to cut down on sugar consumption.","example_es":"Necesito reducir el consumo de azúcar.","example_en":"I need to cut down on sugar consumption.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a red cutter shrinking a pile, so you cut down on it.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito reducir el consumo de azúcar.","en":"I need to cut down on sugar consumption."}]},{"spanish_text":"Eliminar","english_text":"Do away with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To eliminate or get rid of something.","main_translations_es":["Borrar","Suprimir","Quitar"],"collocations":["do away with poverty","do away with the old system","do away with unnecessary rules"],"synonyms_en":["eliminate","abolish","remove"],"example_sentence":"The government decided to do away with import taxes.","example_es":"El gobierno decidió eliminar los impuestos a la importación.","example_en":"The government decided to do away with import taxes.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a dough (do) being tossed away, eliminating it.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El gobierno decidió eliminar los impuestos a la importación.","en":"The government decided to do away with import taxes."}]},{"spanish_text":"Resolver","english_text":"Figure out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To understand or solve something by thinking about it.","main_translations_es":["Resolver","Solucionar","Despejar"],"collocations":["figure out the problem","figure out how","figure out why","figure out the solution"],"synonyms_en":["solve","determine","work out"],"example_sentence":"I need to figure out this problem before the meeting.","example_es":"Necesito resolver este problema antes de la reunión.","example_en":"I need to figure out this problem before the meeting.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a figure wielding a resolver wrench to crack the puzzle.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Necesito resolver este problema antes de la reunión.","en":"I need to figure out this problem before the meeting."}]},{"spanish_text":"Rellenar","english_text":"Fill in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To complete something by adding missing information.","main_translations_es":["Completar","Llenar","Ingresar"],"collocations":["fill in the blanks","fill in the form","fill in the details"],"synonyms_en":["complete","fill out","enter"],"example_sentence":"Please fill in the form before the deadline.","example_es":"Por favor, rellena el formulario antes de la fecha límite.","example_en":"Please fill in the form before the deadline.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a reel near a paper and you fill in the blanks on it.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Por favor, rellena el formulario antes de la fecha límite.","en":"Please fill in the form before the deadline."}]},{"spanish_text":"Cumplir hasta el final","english_text":"Follow through","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To continue an action or task until it is completed.","main_translations_es":["Cumplir hasta el final","Llevar a cabo","Ver hasta el final"],"collocations":["follow through on","follow through with","see it through","carry out"],"synonyms_en":["carry out","see it through","complete"],"example_sentence":"It''s important to follow through with the projects we start.","example_es":"Es importante cumplir hasta el final con los proyectos que iniciamos.","example_en":"It''s important to follow through with the projects we start.","mnemonic_en":"Think of a ‘full’ line you must ‘through’ to the end, like Cumplir hasta el final.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Es importante cumplir hasta el final con los proyectos que iniciamos.","en":"It''s important to follow through with the projects we start."}]},{"spanish_text":"Transmitir","english_text":"Get across","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To communicate or convey an idea, feeling, or message so that it is understood.","main_translations_es":["Comunicar","Transmitir","Pasar"],"collocations":["get the point across","get the message across","make sure it gets across"],"synonyms_en":["convey","communicate","express"],"example_sentence":"The teacher managed to get the idea across clearly.","example_es":"El profesor logró transmitir la idea de manera clara.","example_en":"The teacher managed to get the idea across clearly.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a goat (get) crossing a bridge, shouting the news across the river like you transmit.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El profesor logró transmitir la idea de manera clara.","en":"The teacher managed to get the idea across clearly."}]},{"spanish_text":"Salirse con la suya","english_text":"Get away with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb phrase","definition_en":"To succeed in doing something that is disapproved of or illegal without being punished.","main_translations_es":["Salir impune","Escapar sin castigo","Quedarse con la razón"],"collocations":["get away with murder","get away with cheating","can''t get away with that","get away with it"],"synonyms_en":["escape punishment","avoid consequences","pull off"],"example_sentence":"Juan tried to rob the store, but the police caught him before he could get away with it.","example_es":"Juan intentó robar la tienda, pero la policía lo atrapó antes de que pudiera salirse con la suya.","example_en":"Juan tried to rob the store, but the police caught him before he could get away with it.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a cat that gets away with the fish, sneaking out (salir) triumphantly.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Juan intentó robar la tienda, pero la policía lo atrapó antes de que pudiera salirse con la suya.","en":"Juan tried to rob the store, but the police caught him before he could get away with it."}]},{"spanish_text":"Arreglárselas","english_text":"Get by","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to manage to survive or cope with a situation, often with limited resources.","main_translations_es":["Apañarse","Sobrevivir","Librarse"],"collocations":["get by on a salary","get by with difficulty","just get by","get by in life"],"synonyms_en":["manage","survive","cope"],"example_sentence":"With so little money, I have to get by.","example_es":"Con tan poco dinero, tengo que arreglármelas.","example_en":"With so little money, I have to get by.","mnemonic_en":"A clever guy arranges tools to get by.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Con tan poco dinero, tengo que arreglármelas.","en":"With so little money, I have to get by."}]},{"spanish_text":"Superar","english_text":"Get over","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To recover from or move beyond something, such as an illness, difficulty, or emotional upset.","main_translations_es":["Vencer","Sobrepasar","Sobreponerse"],"collocations":["get over it","get over a cold","get over the loss","get over the hurdle"],"synonyms_en":["recover from","move past","overcome"],"example_sentence":"I had to get over my fear of flying.","example_es":"Tuve que superar mi miedo a volar.","example_en":"I had to get over my fear of flying.","mnemonic_en":"Visualize a superhero goat leaping over a wall, shouting Get over, to remember Superar","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Tuve que superar mi miedo a volar.","en":"I had to get over my fear of flying."}]},{"spanish_text":"Ceder","english_text":"Give in","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to surrender or yield to someone or something","main_translations_es":["rendirse","ceder","conceder"],"collocations":["give in to pressure","give in to temptation","give in easily","give in finally"],"synonyms_en":["yield","surrender","succumb"],"example_sentence":"After a long argument, he decided to give in to his demands.","example_es":"Después de mucho discutir, decidió ceder a sus demandas.","example_en":"After a long argument, he decided to give in to his 