r","Respetar","Venerar"],"collocations":["look up to someone","look up to his father","look up to role models","look up to as an inspiration"],"synonyms_en":["admire","respect","esteem"],"example_sentence":"I have always looked up to my grandfather for his wisdom.","example_es":"Siempre he admirado a mi abuelo por su sabiduría.","example_en":"I have always looked up to my grandfather for his wisdom.","mnemonic_en":"I look up to her, I admire her.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Siempre he admirado a mi abuelo por su sabiduría.","en":"I have always looked up to my grandfather for his wisdom."}]},{"spanish_text":"Compensar","english_text":"Make up for","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To compensate for something; to offset or counterbalance it.","main_translations_es":["Resarcir","Reparar","Compensar"],"collocations":["make up for lost time","make up for a mistake","make up for the damage","make up for the loss"],"synonyms_en":["compensate","offset","atone for"],"example_sentence":"The raise makes up for the extra time he worked.","example_es":"El aumento de sueldo compensa el tiempo extra que trabajó.","example_en":"The raise makes up for the extra time he worked.","mnemonic_en":"A compass (compensar) corrects the wrong direction, making up for the mistake.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"El aumento de sueldo compensa el tiempo extra que trabajó.","en":"The raise makes up for the extra time he worked."}]},{"spanish_text":"Seguir adelante","english_text":"Move on","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to continue or proceed to the next thing, especially after a difficulty or interruption","main_translations_es":["Continuar","Seguir","Avanzar"],"collocations":["move on to","move on from","move on with","move on quickly"],"synonyms_en":["continue","press forward","go ahead"],"example_sentence":"After the breakup, she decided to move on with her life.","