h_text":"Soportar","english_text":"Put up with","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to tolerate or endure something or someone","main_translations_es":["aguantar","tolerar","soportar"],"collocations":["put up with the noise","can''t put up with his attitude","put up with the heat"],"synonyms_en":["tolerate","endure","stand"],"example_sentence":"I can''t put up with the constant noise.","example_es":"No puedo soportar el ruido constante.","example_en":"I can''t put up with the constant noise.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a supportive porter who puts up with every heavy load, just like the Spanish soportar.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"No puedo soportar el ruido constante.","en":"I can''t put up with the constant noise."}]},{"spanish_text":"Descartar","english_text":"Rule out","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To eliminate or exclude something as a possibility.","main_translations_es":["Excluir","Eliminar","Desestimar"],"collocations":["rule out the possibility","rule out a diagnosis","rule out any chance","rule out the hypothesis"],"synonyms_en":["exclude","eliminate","dismiss"],"example_sentence":"Doctors must rule out other causes before confirming the diagnosis.","example_es":"Los médicos deben descartar otras causas antes de confirmar el diagnóstico.","example_en":"Doctors must rule out other causes before confirming the diagnosis.","mnemonic_en":"Imagine a ruler striking out a card, discarding it—so you rule out the option.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Los médicos deben descartar otras causas antes de confirmar el diagnóstico.","en":"Doctors must rule out other causes before confirming the diagnosis."}]},{"spanish_text":"Toparse con","english_text":"Run into","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To meet or encounter someone or something unexpectedly.","main_translations_es":["Encontrarse con","Tropezar con","Chocar con"],"collocations":["run into trouble","run into an old friend","run into a problem","run into obstacles"],"synonyms_en":["encounter","bump into","meet unexpectedly"],"example_sentence":"I ran into my old friend at the supermarket.","example_es":"Me topé con mi viejo amigo en el supermercado.","example_en":"I ran into my old friend at the supermarket.","mnemonic_en":"Picture a spinning top that runs into a wall, reminding you of run into.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Me topé con mi viejo amigo en el supermercado.","en":"I ran into my old friend at the supermarket."}]},{"spanish_text":"Reservar","english_text":"Set aside","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"To reserve something for later use or a specific purpose.","main_translations_es":["Apartar","Guardar","Hacer una reserva"],"collocations":["set aside money","set aside time","set aside differences","set aside for later"],"synonyms_en":["reserve","allocate","put aside"],"example_sentence":"I will set aside time to study.","example_es":"Voy a reservar tiempo para estudiar.","example_en":"I will set aside time to study.","mnemonic_en":"I set aside a seat for the reservation, like reserving a spot.","cloze_distractors_en":[],"examples":[{"es":"Voy a reservar tiempo para estudiar.","en":"I will set aside time to study."}]},{"spanish_text":"Montar","english_text":"Set up","section_name":"Advanced Phrasal Verbs","part_of_speech":"verb","definition_en":"to arrange or establish something, such as equipment, a system, or an event.","main_translations_es":["Instalar","Armar","Configurar"],"collocations":["set up a meeting","set up the equipment","set up shop","set up a system"],"synonyms_en":["establish","arrange","install"],"example_sentence":"Let''s set up the tent before it starts raining.","example_es":"Vamos a montar la carpa antes de que empiece a llover.","example_en":"Let''s set up the tent before it starts raining.","mnemonic_en":"Mount